title: butter coconut pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour in large bowl. Stir in eggs. Add coconut and remaining ingredients, stirring well. Pour into pie shell. Bake at 325° for 35-40 minutes or until pie is set.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs, dressing, water and cinnamon.
Stir in carrots and nuts.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan (greased and floured).
Cook 35 minutes in a 350° preheated oven.
Cool and frost.

title: play dough
directions: Mix dry ingredients with oil.
Add food coloring to water. Add water very slowly until dough is play consistency.

title: salmon fondue
directions: Drain salmon and save liquid.
Break salmon.
Add onions and pepper and toss lightly.
Trim bread.
Cut diagonally.
Arrange in casserole dish and cover with salmon and bread.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and salmon liquid and let set for 30 minutes.
Bake at 350° until puffed and brown, about 1 hour.

title: triple chocolate pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend all ingredients and beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Bake in tube pan or Bundt pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool right side up for about 25 minutes, then remove from pan.

title: chocolate mousse pie
directions: Icing:
Same as cake except use unsweetened chocolate instead of semi-sweet.

title: old-fashioned butterscotch
directions: Boil ingredients until a spoonful dropped into cold water will become brittle.
Remove from heat and put in a generously buttered 9-inch pan.
Cool slightly.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Toss all ingredients lightly but thoroughly.
Wash mushrooms. Brush mushroom caps inside and out with garlic butter.
Heat butter in 10-inch skillet.
Add onion juice and all ingredients. Bake at 375° about 20 minutes.

title: lemon ice cream
directions: In large bowl, beat egg yolks.
Stir in sweetened condensed milk, ReaLemon juice and food coloring.
Fold in whipping cream. Put into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan or other 2-quart container.
Cover. Freeze 6 hours or until firm.
Serve with warm Blueberry 'N Spice Sauce.

title: corn balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and flour to make a real thick paste.
Drop by teaspoon into deep, hot shortening.
Let brown, then turn and brown on other side.
Drain on paper towels.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Add salt and noodles to broth and cook.
Add soup and 2 (1/2-inch) slices of cheese.
Cook until melts. May add onion, celery or different vegetables if desired. Put in casserole dish.
Place croutons or bread crumbs on top and bake until brown.

title: carolyn's pork chops in applesauce gravy
directions: Brown pork chops in skillet.
After they are browned, put into baking dish.
Pour off fat and add rest of 5 ingredients to browned bits in skillet.
Blend thoroughly and cook until thickened.
Add applesauce and lemon juice.
Mix well and pour over meat.
Bake for 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 400° uncovered. Delicious!

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel and slice apples in a buttered 9-inch square pan. Sprinkle spices, lemon juice and water.
Mix sugar and flour in bowl; work in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Spread over fruit. Bake uncovered in preheated oven at 350° for about an hour or until fruit is tender and mixture is slightly browned.
Serve warm with whipped cream.
Serves 4.

title: zucchini squash bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in 2 loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour, or until brown and toothpick comes out clean.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: pastry for fried pies
directions: Blend flour, salt and shortening until coarse as meal.
Add egg, vinegar and water; mix well.
Roll in ball.
Refrigerate for a few hours.
Roll out on floured surface.
Cut in circles and fill with fruit of choice.
Also good for making dumplings.

title: lemony barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients; simmer for 5 minutes.
Baste pork, beef or chicken with this.

title: wild rice salad
directions: Cook rice according to package directions, substituting seasoned salt.
Drain well; cool.
Spoon into large bowl; add chicken, grapes, water chestnuts and mayonnaise.
Toss gently with a fork.
Cover and chill.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: potato frittata
directions: Steam potatoes just until tender; transfer to 8-inch pan.
In bowl, beat together remaining ingredients.
Heat over medium heat. Add egg mix to potatoes.
Cook, stirring frequently to keep even. When eggs are no longer runny, lift edge of Frittata and let any extra uncooked egg get underneath.
Invert onto plate and let sit before slicing in two.
(Great side dish.)

title: pineapple-milnot pie
directions: Cook pineapple, sugar and eggs until thick.
Stir while cooking.
Add Jell-O.
Cool completely.
Stir whipped Milnot into mixture; pour into 2 baked pie shells.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Stir together dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Stir in buttermilk until all are combined.
(Dough will be sticky.)
Knead dough about 10 times on a flour-dusted board.
Shape into an oval loaf with flour-dusted hands.
Place in an ungreased pan.
Cut a deep cross in loaf.
Bake in a 375° oven for 45 to 50 minutes, until golden brown.

title: cucumbers and homemade cream
directions: Peel cucumbers and onions; slice (as many as you desire). Salt well.
Place in bowl with a dish over top with something heavy on the dish.
Refrigerate for 1 hour; drain.
Using your own judgement, mix enough mayonnaise and evaporated milk to thin the mayonnaise a little.
Add vinegar and sugar to taste.
Pour over cucumbers and mix well.
Keep mixing until mayonnaise mixture is thinned from the juice of the cucumbers and cucumbers and onions are well-coated.
Will keep in refrigerator several days.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions. Drain and place in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Brown meat with onions, garlic, salt and pepper. Add spaghetti sauce and heat. Pour this mixture over spaghetti noodles. Combine soup and water or milk and pour over sauce mixture. Cover the top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: jerky
directions: Soak meat
overnight
to 24 hours).
Start oven at 180° for 1
hour,
then set oven at 140° for 7 hours.
Best to use belly
meat
(thin).
Hang on top of oven rack (use toothpick). Use something to hold oven door open, just a crack, to let moisture
escape.
Check
last
hour
or
so
to keep from overdrying.

title: light strawberry cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Coat a 9-inch spring-form pan with nonstick spray.
In a medium bowl, mix the crumbs and margarine. Press onto the bottom and 2 inches up the sides of the pan; set aside.
Using an electric mixer, beat the Ricotta until smooth. Add 3/4 cup of the sugar, the flour, egg yolks, lemon peel and vanilla; mix well.
Blend in the sour cream.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Combine fat, beef and onion in skillet; cook until meat is lightly browned.
Drain; add salt and pepper.
Stir in catsup and tomato sauce; heat thoroughly.
Turn into an 8-inch square or 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cut cheese into thin strips and spread over meat.
Top with biscuits or rolls.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.

title: fruit dish
directions: Drain fruit except for peaches.
Mix all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: katie's punch
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; add frozen lemonade, pineapple juice and water.
Just before serving, add ginger ale and pour over sherbet.
It is better to refrigerate the pineapple juice and ginger ale beforehand.
Orange juice gives it a different taste but makes it go farther.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Cook chicken and debone; chop. Save broth. Cook vermicelli in 1 1/2-quarts of chicken broth (do not drain).
Saute onions and peppers in butter.
Put Ro-Tel through blender and add broth. Cook 10 minutes. Add Velveeta, chicken and all other ingredients to broth mixture until cheese melts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fudge ribbon cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Use a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Cream 2 tablespoons butter with cream cheese, 1/4 cup sugar and cornstarch.
Add egg, milk and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Set aside.
Grease and flour bottom of pan.
Place in a mixing bowl 1/2 cup butter, 2 cups sugar, salt, baking powder and 1 cup milk. Blend; beat 1 1/2 minutes at low speed.
Add 1/3 cup milk, 2 eggs, Choco Bake and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat 1 1/2 minutes.
Spread half of batter in pan.
Spoon cheese mixture over batter.
Spread to cover.
Top with remaining batter.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes. Cool.
Frost.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Put in layers; refrigerate for 8 hours.
Mix as serving.

title: chicken with olives and lemon
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Coat chicken with spices, pepper, garlic and cilantro.
Place in baking dish and pour lemon juice over it.
Sprinkle chicken with flour and mix to coat the chicken pieces.
Add olives, lemon wedges and broth to dish.
Bake for about an hour.
Serve with rice or couscous.

title: rabbit in sour cream and mustard sauce
directions: Shake the rabbit pieces with flour, 1 teaspoon salt and pepper.
In a large casserole or Dutch oven, saute the rabbit in lard or oil over medium heat until browned on all sides, about 10 minutes. During this browning, add onion and garlic.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Mix the soup and milk together in bowl.
Pour about half of this mixture in the bottom of a greased baking dish; layer the broccoli, onion rings and water chestnuts, ending with soup and cheese on top.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes, or until cheese is melted.

title: tuna sandwich on toast
directions: Mash tuna, cheese and horseradish together and spread on toast.
Top with lettuce.

title: blender coconut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place all ingredients in a blender and blend 1 minute.
Pour into a greased and floured 9-inch pan.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: sarah's sugar crisps
directions: In a large saucepan, melt shortening over low heat.
Remove and let cool.
Add sugar, molasses and egg.
Beat well.
Sift together remaining dry ingredients; add to first mixture.
Mix well and chill thoroughly (at least 2 hours).
Form in 1-inch balls.
Roll in additional sugar.
Place on greased baking sheets 2-inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: chesapeake bay clam chowder
directions: Boil clams in shell.
Let cool.
Extract and mince clams. Add chicken broth to clam broth, along with all ingredients, except biscuits; simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Drop small pieces of biscuits into broth.
Cook 15 more minutes.
Let cool and serve. Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: cornbread
directions: Pour the oil into an iron skillet.
Heat until oil is hot. Pour in batter.
Bake at 390° for about 40 minutes, or until done.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 425° for 29 to 30 minutes.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Drain all canned vegetables and toss together in a large bowl. Add the next four ingredients to the vegetables.
Bring the sugar plus the next five ingredients to a boil.
This makes the dressing.
Cool and pour over the vegetable mixture.
Refrigerate. Keeps up to two weeks.

title: easy sausage quiche
directions: One and one-half cup chopped ham may be substituted for sausage.

title: golden corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs well.
Add sugar, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Beat in milk and butter.
Stir in corn.
Pour into greased quart baking dish.
Set in pan of hot water 1-inch deep.
Bake 60 to 70 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Remove from heat after mixed well.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Cook until soft fall forms.
Pour into buttered dish and cool.

title: chicken pie
directions: Pour mixture into a pie crust; top with the other pie crust. Seal around the edges.
Poke holes in top crust with a fork.
Bake until brown at 350°.

title: feather beds (rolls)
directions: Cook potato in water until tender.
Drain and reserve 3/4 cup mashed potato (set aside 1/2 cup).

title: hillbilly chili
directions: Brown meat with onion, pepper and celery in skillet; drain off fat.
In a 6-quart Dutch oven, combine sauces and seasonings.
Add meat and beans, if desired.
Cook until thick.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Mix cocoa, oleo, sugar and milk and bring to a boil, stirring frequently.
Turn off heat, then add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper and let cool.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Put beans and vegetables in a large bowl.
Mix the vinegar, sugar, oil, salt and pepper and pour over the beans and vegetables.
Refrigerate.

title: pat's cherry dessert
directions: Mix together.
Cool in refrigerator or freeze.

title: caponata(italian hors d'oeuvre)
directions: Saute eggplants in olive oil; drain.
In same oil, saute celery, garlic and tomato pulp.
Add eggplant, olives and capers. Dissolve sugar in vinegar; add to mixture.
Add tomato juice. Cook about 1/2 hour, uncovered.
Place in hot canning jars and seal.
Chill in refrigerator before using.
Serve with crackers for cocktails or with an antipasto before dinner.
Makes 2 or 3 pints.

title: dumplings
directions: Combine mix and milk; stir until mix is just moistened.
Drop by tablespoonful into hot stew or broth or hot fruit sauce. Cover; steam, without lifting cover, for 12 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix everything except stuffing mix.
Layer 1/2 stuffing mix (dry) on bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Next, layer all the chicken mixture.
Top with the rest of stuffing mix.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° until hot, about 50 minutes.

title: christmas morning rolls
directions: Arrange rolls in greased 9 x 13 pan.
Sprinkle dry pudding mix over rolls.
Cook butter and remaining ingredients over low heat until sugar dissolves and mixture bubbles.
Pour over rolls.
Cover lightly with foil and let stand on counter overnight.
Next morning, bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes, then invert carefully on serving dish.

title: chattanooga cheese ball
directions: Dice smoked beef.
Grate smoked cheese.
Add all ingredients and mix well with hands.
Form into two large balls and roll in chopped pecans.

title: bread pudding
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole break bread into small pieces.
Heat milk and butter in saucepan.
Do not boil.
Cream eggs, sugar, vanilla, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt in bowl.
Add hot mixture and mix well.
Pour all ingredients over bread pieces.
Stir. Sprinkle top with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bake in 350° oven for about 50 minutes.

title: chicken fried steak
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Sprinkle on both sides of meat. Combine egg and 2 tablespoons milk in dish.
Dip steaks in egg mixture.
Dredge in cracker crumbs.
Pour oil into frypan.
Fry until brown.
Cover.
Reduce heat and simmer, turning occasionally, 15 minutes or until tender.
Remove steak and make gravy with remaining flour, broth and milk.
Cook until thick.
Serve with steak.

title: chicken cheddar rice bake
directions: Melt margarine in pan. Blend flour and chicken bouillon cubes. Gradually stir in milk, stirring until mixture comes to a boil. Remove from heat. Stir in chicken and mushrooms.

title: strawberry pizza(dessert)
directions: Mix the flour, powdered sugar and margarine; pat into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 325°.
Cool.

title: pork chops and potatoes
directions: Brown chops. Put together wet ingredients and parsley in 2-quart casserole. Alternate layers of potatoes. Sprinkle with salt, pepper and sauce.
Put browned chops on top.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 375° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: mexicorn casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Stir in Cheez Whiz.
Put in an 8 x 11-inch baking dish.
Make stuffing according to directions on box.
Add drained corn.
Put on top of meat mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven until heated thoroughly.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Soften cheese at room temperature.
Chop dried beef in food processor.
Add to cheese.
Add Worcestershire sauce and garlic salt to taste.
Mix in ball and refrigerate.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix all together; pour in pie crusts.
Refrigerate.
Makes 2 pies.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add mashed bananas and eggs. Sift flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to creamed ingredients. Pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Freezes well.

title: blueberry crunch cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add dry ingredients sifted together.
Add milk and egg beaten together, berries and lemon rind.
Put in 9 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan.

title: caesar chicken
directions: Wash chicken breasts and place into a bowl.
Pour salad dressing over chicken and cover all sides of each breast well. Put in fridge for at least 1 hour.
Cover cookie sheet with tinfoil.
Place chicken breasts on cookie sheet; sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Slice tomato; place one slice on each breast.
Bake for 5 more minutes.
Serve on a bed of brown rice.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Stir shortening to soften.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Add bananas and 1/2 of buttermilk.
Mix until all flour is dampened. Beat 2 minutes.
Add rest of buttermilk and eggs.
Beat 2 minutes. Fold in walnuts.
Use 2 (9-inch) pans.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: spanish steak and rice
directions: Cut steaks into 1 1/2-inch strips.
Cut green pepper into strips.
Prepare rice mix according to package.
In a large skillet, brown half the meat at a time in hot oil.
Return all meat to pan.
Add pepper.
In screw-top jar, mix catsup, cornstarch, sugar, 1 cup cold water and 1 teaspoon of salt.
Shake to blend; add to skillet.
Cook and stir until mixture bubbles. Cook and stir 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir in hot rice; heat through.

title: lois' cheese ball
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients and 1/2 cup pecans.
Form a ball.
Cover with 1/2 cup pecans.
Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together; add shortening and eggs.
Mix with rolled oats.
Add mashed bananas to mixture last.
Drop cookies on cookie sheet; bake at 325° until brown.

title: zucchini squares
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Let cool, then cut in squares.

title: homemade pork sausage
directions: Combine and mix well.
I make 10 little rolls and freeze. When time to thaw, cut into slices and fry.
Memories of home.

title: vapada
directions: Boil chicken until done. Take chicken from water and let cool, then shred from bone into small pieces. Boil noodles in same water as chicken. Saute bell pepper, onion and butter. Add soup, tomatoes and Velveeta. Heat and stir until well blended and cheese is melted. Add shell noodles and shredded chicken. Serve.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes, unpeeled, until tender.
Let cool.
Cut in halves and then in slices about 1/2-inch wide.
Salt and pepper.

title: cookie crust fruit pizza
directions: Press dough onto pizza pan (large).
Bake at 350° until light golden.
Cool.

title: dill dip
directions: Hollow out round loaf of Hawaiian bread. Fill with dip.
Cut bread into cubes for dipping.

title: christmas cookies(cut-out)
directions: Cream the butter and sugar together.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients together and add gradually to creamed mixture. Chill dough for 2 to 3 hours. Roll to 1/4-inch thickness and cut.
Bake at 400° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Decorate with icing when cooled.

title: olive cheese ball
directions: Blend cream cheese, Blue cheese and butter.
Stir in olives and chives.
Chill slightly.
Form in ball.
Chill well.
Press chopped walnuts over ball.
Makes 3 cups.

title: hallelujah cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan or baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until brown.

title: corn and squash
directions: Saute onion in butter until soft.
Add corn and water and bring to boil.
Simmer 5 minutes, and stir in squash.
Cook until squash is crisp/tender, adding water if needed.

title: mamaw dena's drop cookies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients except for soda.
Add soda to soured milk.
Cream lard (or butter) and sugar.
Add eggs and mix, then add soured milk and mix again.
Stir into dry ingredients and add chocolate chips.
Mix and drop on ungreased cookie sheet by rounded teaspoonfuls.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with sugar and cool.

title: barbecue water chestnuts
directions: Drain chestnuts.
Cut bacon in 1/3 pieces.
Wrap bacon around chestnuts and secure with toothpicks.
Bake on a wire rack for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Mix flour, sugar and milk together.
Spread melted oleo in a dish; pour in batter.
Pour fruit with a little juice on top. Bake at 350° until done.
Good with ice cream.

title: punch
directions: Mix ingredients.
Add 2 large 7-Up (quart size).
Serves about 50.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix soups, rice, water and celery until lumps are out.
Add chicken.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan, covered, at 375° for 1 hour. Top with shredded cheese and French fried onions.
Put back in oven for 5 minutes until brown onions and melt cheese.

title: impossible veggie pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate (10-inch).

title: black-eyed pea salad
directions: Combine and chill several hours or overnight.

title: yum yum
directions: Break up angel food cake into pieces and place in bottom of large dish.
Place bananas on top of cake.	Prepare pudding according to package direction and spoon on top of bananas.
Add pineapple and then Cool Whip
on top.
If desired, drizzle pineapple juice down into mixture.	Refrigerate overnight.	Serves 12-15.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine ingredients and place in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Pour crust over chicken mixture.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, or until crust rises and browns.

title: spinach salad with poppy seed dressing
directions: Shake the preceding ingredients in jar with a lid.
Pour over:

title: roast chicken supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Rinse chicken off, including inside of cavity.
Brush olive oil all over bird, then sprinkle over the seasonings, saving paprika for last.
Insert onion and sage into cavity, then bake on a rack with a drip pan underneath for 25 to 30 minutes, back side down.
Turn over and cook 5 to 10 minutes. Serve with fresh vegetables and new potatoes.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown ground beef, bacon and onion.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 300° for 90 minutes.

title: company salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add marshmallows, stirring until melted.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Stir pineapple and bananas into gelatin mixture.
Spoon into an 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch glass dish.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: confetti casserole
directions: Baking Temperature: 375°.
Baking Time: 40 minutes.

title: parmesan cheese bites
directions: Combine flour, cheese and red pepper; cut in butter with a pastry blender until crumbly, but still dry.
Gently press mixture together with hands, working until blended and smooth, 2 to 3 minutes.
Shape into 2 (4 inch long) logs.
(Or roll into a 10 x 7 inch rectangle, 1/4 inch thick, on a lightly floured surface. Cut lengthwise into 8 strips and crosswise into 4 strips, forming 32 squares.)
Wrap in plastic wrap, chill 8 hours or freeze.
Freeze up to 3 months, if desired.
Thaw overnight in refrigerator. Preheat oven to 350°.
Slice logs 1/4 inch thick.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes on ungreased baking sheets until lightly browned.
Yield: 32 appetizers.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli into florets; add raisins, sunflower seeds and onion, cut up.
Mix mayonnaise and sugar and pour over salad.

title: chili
directions: Put all ingredients
in
crock-pot in the order listed. Stir once.
Cover and cook on high 3 to 4 hours.

title: chicken fried steak
directions: Combine flour, salt, paprika and pepper.
Set aside.
Dip steak in milk, then flour mixture, pressing to coat each side thoroughly. Pan-fry in oil 5 minutes per side.
Serve with gravy.
Makes 6 servings.

title: father roger's pork pie
directions: Meat filling:
Brown meats and onion.
Add seasonings after draining grease (reserve grease).
Cool.
Add cracker crumbs.
If mixture is dry, add some or all of reserved grease.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Sprinkle with cinnamon, add top crust, seal edges and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in bottom of pan.
Then spread chili over cream cheese.
Sprinkle taco seasoning over chili and salsa.
Then add green onions and olives.
Sprinkle cheese over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until bubbly.
Serve with taco chips.

title: barbecue sauce(club member: amanda speed)
directions: Combine all ingredients in heavy pan; simmer to a slow boil. Store leftover in refrigerator.

title: squash casserole supreme
directions: Mash squash.
Add all ingredients, except crumbs and butter. Put 1/2 of crumbs in bottom of casserole dish; cover with squash mixture.
Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Dot with butter.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: impossible cheesecake(light)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 1 1/4-inch pie plate lightly. Place all ingredients except topping in mixing bowl.
Mix on medium/high speed until smooth (2 minutes).
Pour into pie plate. Bake just until puffed and center is dry, about 30 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Beat eggs; add to milk.
Mix milk mixture with dry ingredients.
Cook slowly until thick.
Add vanilla and butter.
Pour into baked pie shell; cool.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: * large batch brownies *
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together well.
Add flour and mix well.
Add nuts.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan and bake until done, about 35 to 45 minutes, in a 350° oven.

title: soft sugar cookies(4 to 5 dozen)
directions: Cream shortening, margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Add 2 cups flour, salt and baking powder. Add 3 cups flour, alternately with orange juice.

title: bananas foster
directions: Melt butter and brown sugar in frypan.
Add sliced bananas and cook until bubbly.
Warm Triple Sec and brandy in another pan. Pour over banana mixture and light with match at once.
Pour over individual servings of ice cream.

title: hot sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and shape into meat balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: green tomato casserole
directions: Layer tomato and onion slices.
Sprinkle Season-All and Romano cheese over veggies and top with seasoned bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: string bean saute
directions: Snip ends off string beans and wash in cold water; snip string beans in half.
Boil string beans with salt for 3 to 5 minutes. Cool string beans with cold water.
Put oil in pan on high.
When oil is hot, put in garlic, quickly stirring and turning with spatula (about 30 seconds).
Add string beans, water, sugar, basil and salt; keep turning with spatula until heated (about 1 to 2 minutes).
Add parsley and serve.

title: "whatever" cake
directions: Put all ingredients in a mixing bowl and mix well. Spray pan with Pam.
Bake at 350°.
For Bundt pan, bake 1 hour, sheet cake, 35 minutes or 2 loaf pans, 25 to 30 minutes or until it pulls away from sides of pan. Turn out on wire racks to cool.
May frost with sour cream frosting.

title: boiled white turnips
directions: Wash and peel turnips.
Slice in 1/4-inch slices.
In kettle or pot, cover turnips with water, 1 teaspoon salt and salt pork. Boil 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.
Drain; season with salt, pepper and sugar.
Dress with plenty of margarine.

title: dark date nut bread
directions: Put soda and salt on dates.
Cover with boiling water.
Add shortening.
Let stand until cold.
Add sugar and egg.
Add flour gradually.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake in loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chuck wagon chili
directions: Cook bacon until crisp and drain.
Pour bacon grease in heavy Dutch oven or casserole and add beef.
Cover and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Add onion, garlic and water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients and bake for another hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cucumber spread
directions: Wring out excess cucumber juice in paper towel.
This process may need to be repeated several times.
Cream softened cheese with mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Add cucumber, onion and seasonings. Refrigerate several hours before serving.
Spread on bread or use as a dip to be served with table crackers.

title: zucchini jam
directions: Drain ground zucchini.
Boil pulp till clear (about 6 minutes).
Add sugar, lemon juice and pineapple with its juice. Boil 6 minutes.
Remove from heat and add orange Jell-o.
Stir well till dissolved.
Pour into containers and seal.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes.
Add smashed garlic, onions, cream cheese and sour cream.
Beat until smooth.
Put into large casserole and swirl top like meringue.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and chill until ready to use.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook onion and garlic in oil until tender.
Add tomatoes and seasoning; simmer until very thick (1 hour or more).
Makes enough sauce for 4 servings of pasta.

title: marinated shrimp
directions: Clean shrimp and place in large bowl.
Mix together lemon juice, 1 tablespoon sherry, cloves, salt, garlic and oil.
Pour over shrimp and marinate at least 1 hour.
In large skillet, melt butter.
Add almonds and cook until lightly browned.
Drain shrimp, reserving marinade.
Add shrimp to skillet and cook until pink and firm (do not overcook).
Transfer shrimp and almonds to a chafing dish.
Pour reserved marinade into skillet; bring to a boil and add remaining 1 tablespoon of sherry.
Stir.
Pour over shrimp in chafing dish.
Serve hot.
Makes 30 to 40 appetizers.

title: upside-down beef pie
directions: Brown onion and beef in iron skillet.
Cook until crumbly but not hard.
Drain grease well.
Add seasonings and soup and simmer until thickened.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk and mix well.
Pour batter over hot mixture in skillet.
Put skillet into oven and bake at 450° for 15 minutes or until top is golden brown.
Cover with warm serving plate. Invert and remove skillet.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well. Combine flour, soda, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt.
Add to creamed mixture, a small amount at a time.
Add nuts and oatmeal. Mix well.

title: cupcakes
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Add beaten egg.
Sift flour with baking powder and add alternately with milk to creamed mixture. Mix thoroughly.
Stir in lemon extract and blend well.
Fill greased muffin pans 1/2 full.
Bake 20 minutes in hot oven, 425°. Makes 12 to 14 cupcakes.

title: jacki's stuff
directions: Cook in slow cooker 4 to 9 hours.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix zucchini, eggs, oil and seasoning; add bag of cheese.
Mix all together in a 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole dish.
Add Bisquick and mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 50 minutes.
Uncover for 30 minutes.

title: quick coconut macaroons
directions: Combine ingredients and drop from teaspoon 1 inch apart on greased cookie sheet and press down with back of spoon. Bake at 350 degrees for 10-12 minutes or until golden brown. Remove from baking sheet at once. Cool on waxed paper. Makes about 1 1/2 doz. cookies.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix margarine, sugar and eggs.
Stir in flour, baking soda and salt (dough will be stiff).
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls, about 2-inches apart, onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until light brown, 8 to 10 minutes.
Centers will be soft.
Cool slightly and remove from cookie sheet.
Yields about 6 dozen cookies.

title: cauliflower saute
directions: Arrange cauliflower in a steamer basket.
Place over hot water. Cover and steam 8 minutes; drain and set aside.
Cook onion and garlic in olive oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium heat, stirring constantly, until tender.
Add cauliflower, snow peas and remaining ingredients.
Cook, stirring constantly, until heated. Yields 4 (1-cup) servings.

title: pina coladas
directions: Blend all the ingredients together until the cottage cheese is smooth.
Taste and add more lime juice, if required.
Serve in a chilled glass and decorate with a few frozen raspberries.

title: jam cake
directions: Mix all
and
bake
in
two
floured layer pans at 350° until center when pricked with toothpick comes out clean.
Use your favorite icing, caramel or white is delicious.

title: cream fluff white frosting(for three layer cake)
directions: Beat egg whites until they stand in a peak.
Mix karo, sugar, salt, and vanilla.
Bring mixture to a rolling boil, and boil for one minute.
Gradually add mixture to egg whites, beating constantly.
Beat frosting until it is the right consistency to spread.

title: baconized macaroni
directions: Cook
macaroni	and drain.
Make white sauce from milk, butter,
flour,
salt
and	pepper.
Cook
together,
stirring smooth
and
1 cup cream corn.
Put in buttered baking dish in layers
of	macaroni
and sauce mixture.
Put bacon on top and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until bacon is crisp.

title: diet pumpkin muffins
directions: Combine dry milk, cinnamon, flour, Sweet 'N Low and baking soda.
Set aside. Combine vanilla, eggs, pumpkin, carrots and raisins; mix well.
Add to dry mixture. Bake in muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 12 small muffins or 8 large, 6 or 4 for each serving.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Pour beans into casserole dish.
Stir in brown sugar.
Place bacon on top and cover with mixture of catsup and barbecue sauce. Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: ham casserole
directions: Lightly brown ham and onion in butter.
Stir in soup, milk and cheese.
Heat until cheese melts.
Blend sauce with macaroni.
Pour in 1 1/2-quart baking dish and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: potato cheese casserole
directions: Boil and grate potatoes.
Mix onion, cheese, butter and sour cream with potatoes.
Place in baking dish.
Crush corn flakes and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: maid-rite sandwiches
directions: Brown beef, onion and bay leaves together in skillet over low heat.
Add salt and pepper.
Drain.
Remove bay leaves.

title: holiday ham souffle(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Mix eggs and milk.
Layer a 9 x 13-inch glass casserole with 6 slices of bread, then top with cheese, ham, mustard and Cheddar cheese.
Top with the other 6 slices and pour the egg/milk mixture over all.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake for one hour at 350°.
If desired, you can brown 1 cup of corn flakes in butter and sprinkle over the casserole after 45 minutes, returning to the oven for another 15 minutes.

title: roast beef au barbecue sauce
directions: Roast beef as desired.
Cool or refrigerate.
Slice thin, removing all fat and gristle.
Save juice for sauce.

title: homestyle tuna or chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Line greased, 9-inch pan with crust and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour filling in pan. Top with second crust.
Seal and crimp edges. Slit top crust to vent and bake 40 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields about 6 servings.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix ingredients in order given, starting by creaming together butter and sugar.
Pour mixture into greased and floured loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: grandma betty's sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix hamburger, corn flakes, parsley, eggs, pepper, instant onion, ketchup, garlic powder and soy sauce together. Form into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: mocha toddie
directions: Combine coffee crystals and water.
Stir to dissolve.
Add chocolate syrup, rum or brandy and vanilla.
Store covered in refrigerator.

title: unbaked fruit cake
directions: Melt marshmallows in whipping cream over low heat.
Add all ingredients.
Press into a tube pan well greased with margarine. Cool overnight.

title: carolina relish
directions: Mix and let set overnight the cabbage, green sweet peppers, salt, onions, red sweet peppers and hot pepper.
The next day, rinse real well.
Put 1 quart of vinegar in large saucepan.
Add sugar, celery seed, mustard seed and turmeric powder.
Bring this mixture to a boil.
Add relish mix.
Get real hot, but do not boil. Pack into hot jars and seal.

title: salmon casserole
directions: Mix well.
Pour into buttered casserole covered with crushed corn flakes.
Dot with butter.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: sally's chili cornbread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Blend in eggs.
Stir in chilies, corn and cheeses.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to corn mixture.
Pour into greased 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Serve warm with chili and green salad.

title: squash relish
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook slow for 20 or 30 minutes.
Put in pint jars and seal.
Makes 6 pints.

title: jiffy mexican lasagne
directions: Combine beef, taco seasoning and tomato sauce in a bowl, cover with wax paper and cook on High setting in microwave oven 7 minutes (turn bowl a 1/2 turn after 3 1/2 minutes unless you have a turntable).
In 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish, layer half of meat mixture and arrange Mozzarella slices on top.
Combine Ricotta, egg and chilies and spread over cheese.
Arrange tortillas over the Ricotta mix.
Top tortillas with rest of the meat mixture.
Cover with waxed paper and cook in microwave 7 minutes. Turn after 3 1/2 minutes.
Remove waxed paper and sprinkle with Cheddar cheese, cook 2 minutes.
Spread with sour cream and olives and cook 1 minute.

title: hamburger roll-ups
directions: Heat soup, catsup and Worcestershire sauce.
Make Stove Top dressing as per box directions.
Make hamburger patties (medium thickness) out of hamburger.
Put spoonful of dressing on top of patty and put another patty on top of that and seal edges.
Round out into a little "bundle" with hands and place in a baking dish. Pour hot sauce on top of all bundles and bake at 350° for about 3/4 of an hour.
Enjoy.

title: russian salad
directions: Mix over low flame until dissolved the gelatin, boiling water, cream cheese and marshmallows.
Let cool.
Add other ingredients. Refrigerate and chill.

title: chinese chews
directions: Beat eggs with a fork.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spread on 11 x 15-inch cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until done when tested.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Layer chicken and cheese;
pour
wine and soup mixture. Melt 1/2 cup of butter
or
margarine and add to stuffing; mix well and spread over casserole.
Add
salt and pepper. Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 50 minutes.

title: chocolate bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees. Place chocolate in small heat-proof bowl. Scald half-and half; pour over chocolate. Let stand 5 minutes, then stir until smooth.
In another bowl, whisk together sugar and egg yolks. Add vanilla. Add chocolate mixture to egg mixture; whisk until smooth. Set aside.

title: yogurt pie
directions: For crust, crush crackers until fine.
Add baking powder, pecans and vanilla.
Beat egg whites until stiff; beat in sugar. Fold cracker mixture into egg whites.
Pour into buttered 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: chicken lo mein
directions: Heat oil in wok or 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat until hot.
Add chicken; stir-fry 4 to 5 minutes or until no longer pink in center; drain.
Stir in sauce and mixed vegetables.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, 5 to 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in pea pods. Serve over noodles.
Yields 6 servings.

title: praline candy
directions: In a large, heavy saucepan, pour buttermilk, sugar and soda together.
Stir until the sugar is thoroughly mixed.
Cook on medium heat, stirring constantly, until it turns brownish in color and reaches soft ball stage.
Remove from heat; add margarine, vanilla and pecans.
Beat mixture until it becomes glossy and starts to crystallize.
Quickly spoon out the candy into patties on waxed paper or greased cookie sheet.
Let cool.

title: unbeatable beets
directions: Blend flour and butter over low heat.
Stir in sugar, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce. Add drained beets.
Serves 6.

title: goldenrod toast
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; add flour.
Stir and add milk.
Stir to thicken.
Add chopped eggs.
Serve over toast.
Serves 4.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: In a medium soup kettle, bring stock to a boil.
While boiling, add broccoli stems; cook 15 minutes.
Saute onion and celery in butter until translucent.
Stir in flour slowly; cook 3 minutes on low heat.
Add onion and celery mixture to boiling broccoli and chicken stock, stirring constantly.
Lower heat and cook 15 minutes.
Add broccoli tops.
Cook 5 minutes.

title: triple bean salad
directions: Combine last six ingredients; place vegetables in a large mixing bowl and pour liquid mixture over them.
Toss lightly. Cover and chill overnight.
Just before serving, drain and toss lightly.
Store (with juice) in covered container in refrigerator.

title: ham and green noodle casserole
directions: Make the ground beef into four patties, placing in bottom of four coffee cans.
Next, slice the potatoes and onions, putting them on top of the patty.
Drain the green beans and carrots.
Add to the top of rest.
Next, put the ear of corn, salt and pepper to taste and a pat of butter.
Cover the can with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients;
add
raisins, then add all liquid ingredients and mix
well.	Pour into greased loaf pans.
Bake in 350° oven
for
40	to
60	minutes.
Makes approximately 3 large loaves.

title: tarragon chicken
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Add chicken.
Marinate for 1 hour.
Place chicken on broiler pan or grill, reserving marinade. Broil/grill, turning frequently and brushing with marinade.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Blend with peaches.
Fill pie crust. Dot with 2 tablespoons margarine.
Dash with extra spice if desired.
Cover with top crust.
Crimp edges.
Pierce top with fork.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: carrots au gratin
directions: Cook carrots in 1/2-inch boiling salted water 10 minutes. Combine crackers, onion salt, green pepper and pepper. Alternate layers of carrots and crumb mixture in greased 1-quart baking dish. If any carrot liquid is leftover, spoon over top. Pour butter over and sprinkle with cheese. Bake in preheated 425° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese melts. Makes 6 servings.

title: homemade salsa
directions: May be processed in food chopper. Chill 5 days before serving.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and onion together; drain.
Mix sausage mixture with rice.
Layer with Rice Krispies and cheese, dividing between 2 (2-quart) casserole dishes.
Mix together eggs, milk and soup and spoon over tops of casseroles.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes 2 (2-quart) casseroles.
Freezes well.

title: chicken soup
directions: Clean chicken thoroughly.
Combine in a deep saucepan with water and onions.
Bring to a boil and cook over medium heat for 1 1/2 hours.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook over low heat 1 hour longer or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken and strain soup.
Makes about 2 to 2 1/2 quarts soup.
Use the chicken in other dishes or serve with soup.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients with hands until well blended.
Form into balls about the size of a walnut.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: easy pound cake
directions: Mix all together.
Beat 10 minutes.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 30 minutes at 275°.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Mix sugar, cinnamon, salt and milk together in saucepan. Bring to soft ball stage. Remove from heat. Add vanilla and nuts. Stir until mixture is grainy and turn out on waxed paper. Separate nuts when cool and store.

title: meeting dessert
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold water and set aside.
Combine egg yolks, sugar, salt and milk.
Cook in double boiler until mixture coats the spoon. Stir in gelatin.
Cool.
Fold in 1/2 pint whipping cream.
Butter a 9 x 13 pan.
Crumble or slice cake and line pan with half.
Spread half of custard on top.
Cover with remaining half of cake and custard.
Whip other 1/2 pint of cream; spread over filling.
Garnish with cherries or shaved chocolate. Refrigerate.
Keeps well.
Serves 12.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour and shortening and add salt with pastry blender until crumbly. Add ice water; mix to soft-ball stage. Roll out, being careful not to overwork.

title: egg custard
directions: Place milk and margarine together in a boiler and let come to a boil. Remove from heat. Beat eggs, sugar and nutmeg or vanilla with mixer until foamy. Add this to the milk mixture. Pour into a lightly baked pie crust and bake at 450° until pie starts to brown. Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 20 minutes. Allow to cool before cutting.

title: peanut butter crisscrosses
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream the first 6 ingredients together.
Combine baking soda, salt, and flour.
Mix with the wet ingredients.
Spoon to cookie sheet and using a fork, crisscross on each cookie before baking.
Bake for about 10 minutes.

title: cocktail fruits demer
directions: Preparation of Cocktail: Mix ingredients as follows: Mayonnaise, sour cream, whipped cream, ketchup, mango chutney, curry powder, cognac, Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco sauce. Chill sauce in refrigerator for at least 1 hour.

title: oven cooked chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken pieces with garlic salt and paprika.
Mix eggs and milk together.
In separate bowl pour bread crumbs.
Roll pieces of chicken in bread crumbs, dip into egg mixture, then roll again in bread crumbs and place into greased baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes, remove and turn each piece, then bake for another 30 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Blend together.
Put in baking pan and bake at 250° until done.

title: auntie jane's easy apple crisp
directions: Pare apples and slice very thin.
Arrange in an 8-inch baking dish.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Mix flour, cinnamon and oats. Combine sugar and flour mixtures.
Crumble over apples and press down.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate mousse pie
directions: Melt chocolate chips in pan.
Add the eggs, vanilla and 1/2 of the Cool Whip.
Freeze.
Top with rest of Cool Whip.
Sounds too easy to be true!

title: raspberry-cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Stir in cranberry, pineapple, wine and walnuts.
Chill until firm. Top with cream cheese and sour cream, blended together.
Spread on firmly set gelatin.

title: roast beef and gravy
directions: Bake beef 3/4 way done, then add onions, garlic, black pepper and salt.
When well done, mix gravy mix with beef broth and pour over roast beef.
Put back in oven 30 to 45 minutes.

title: amish friendship bread(this takes 10 days to make)
directions: Mix and set on counter; do not refrigerate.
Cover, but don't seal.

title: love biscuits
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls into small greased muffin tins.
Bake at 350° until slightly brown on top.

title: salmon cheese ball
directions: In bowl, combine all ingredients except parsley; chill until firm.
Shape into ball; roll in parsley. Makes 3 cups.
Serve with favorite crackers.

title: cracker toffee
directions: Line a cookie sheet with foil; spray with Pam.
Line cookie sheet with crackers (do not crumble).
In saucepan, melt butter, sugar and vanilla.
Heat until it starts to boil.
Once boiling, boil for 3 minutes exactly.
Pour over crackers and bake in a 350° oven for 3 minutes exactly! Take out of oven and sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
When they begin to melt, spread like frosting and immediately sprinkle nuts on top.
Refrigerate or freeze until firm.
Store in refrigerator.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix together sugar and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vinegar and food coloring; beat well.
Sift together the flour, cocoa, salt and soda.
Add alternately with buttermilk and vanilla; beat well.
Bake in three 9-inch pans or a 9 x 13-inch pan at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Mix together and put in bottom of 9 x 13-inch foil (bakes through better in foil) pan or 2 smaller pans, greased and floured.

title: inside-out chocolate cake
directions: Combine pudding, cake mix, milk and eggs in a bowl.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt cake pan.
Bake 50 minutes in a preheated 350° oven. Cool 15 minutes in pan.
Turn out on rack to cool.

title: anything goes quiche
directions: Bake pie shell in 450° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from oven, reduce heat to 325°.
(Pie shell should be hot when filling.)
Cook bacon.
Combine in bowl the eggs, milk, flour, salt and nutmeg.
Stir in bacon and cheese; mix well.
Pour in warm pie shell.
Cover edge of crust with foil.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 10 to 15 minutes more.
Serve with croissants and fruit.

title: angel corn bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add oil, eggs and buttermilk.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 450° until done, about 20 minutes.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and spices.
Cream until light.
Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Dredge fruit and nuts with 1/2 cup flour.
Beat eggs and add alternately with remaining flour until well blended.
Stir in dredged fruit, nuts and applesauce.
Pour into tube pan and bake at 300° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Turn out, cool and wrap.

title: pot roast
directions: Place piece of beef in pot; add mushroom soup, envelope of dried onion soup, chopped onion, chopped or pressed garlic, 2 cups red wine and 2 cups of water.
Add the crushed bay leaf, thyme and basil.
Cover and bake in 350° oven until tender (about 3 1/2 hours or so).

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Melt in small saucepan the butter; add Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder and celery salt.
Pour mixture over cereal mix.
The cereal mix should be in a large shallow roaster pan.
Mix this thoroughly with rubber spatulas until absorbed.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours, stirring every 1/2 hour with spatulas.
Turn oven off and leave it in oven until cold.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Mix all ingredients in large cooking pot.
Bring to a rolling boil and boil for 30 minutes.
Put in hot jars and seal.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then add oil and eggs.
Add apples, nuts, raisins and coconut with your hand.
Batter will be stiff.
Bake in greased and floured pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Prick holes in cake and glaze while cake is hot.
Freeze cake for 3 days and it will be better.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Form mixture into 40 meatballs, using a rounded teaspoonful for each.
Brown meatballs lightly in 1 tablespoon vegetable oil. Cover.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Drain excess fat. Combine 2/3 cup Heinz chili sauce and 2/3 cup red currant or grape jelly.
Pour over meatballs.
Heat, stirring, until jelly is melted.
Simmer 10 to 12 minutes.
Sauce will thicken somewhat. Baste occasionally.

title: cheddar sauce
directions: *You can use cottage cheese, Swiss cheese or Monterey Jack.

title: chocolate flourless cake
directions: In a double boiler, melt chocolate chips, then add butter and melt. Separate eggs and add 1/2 cup sugar to the yolks and mix. Beat the egg whites until soft peaks form.

Continue beating while adding remaining sugar until egg whites are shiny. Add chocolate mixture to the egg yolks and beat on high speed with hand mixer. Gently fold the egg whites into the chocolate mixture.
Pour into round 10-inch pan (pie or cake). Bake in a 375° oven for 45 minutes.

title: easy vegetable casserole
directions: Mix sour cream, soup, shredded cheese and salt and pepper to taste.
Pour mixture over veggies.
Crush the cheese Ritz crackers.
Mix with melted margarine.
Sprinkle mixture over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, covered, and 20 minutes uncovered, or until lightly browned.

title: almond dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together until creamy smooth.
Great dip for fresh fruit, apples, strawberries (whole).

title: barbecue relish
directions: Pare cucumbers and remove seeds.
Grind vegetables fine; sprinkle with salt.
Let stand 1 hour; drain.
Add sugar and vinegar mixture.
Boil 20 minutes and can hot.

title: lo-cal raspberry-almond coffee cake
directions: Combine raspberries and brown sugar.
Combine flour and next 4 ingredients in large bowl.
Combine yogurt and next 3 ingredients; stir well.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened. Spoon 2/3 batter into a 8-inch round cake pan coated with cooking spray and spread evenly.
Top with raspberry mixture.
Spoon remaining batter over raspberry.
Top with almonds.

title: apricot sour dream dessert
directions: Bring 1 cup apricot nectar to a boil.
Sprinkle on 1 package jello, stirring until gelatin has dissolved.
Stir in 1 cup cool apricot nectar.
Pour this mixture into a lightly oiled mold and chill until set.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in large bowl.
Mix well, then stir in potatoes.
Spoon into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake 5 more minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Boil sugar and evaporated milk for 7 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate chips, Hershey bars and marshmallow cream. Stir until mixed.
Add nuts.
Pour into greased pan; cool.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix ingredients in heavy baking dish.
Cover top completely with bacon strips.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: apple raisin loaf(for those on low cholesterol diets)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Mix together applesauce, milk, oil and chopped apples. In a separate bowl, combine oat bran, sugar, baking powder, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt. Add applesauce mixture to dry ingredients; mix just until dry ingredients are moistened. Stir in nuts and raisins. Transfer batter to 9 x 5-inch nonstick loaf pan. Bake for 40 to 45 minutes, until brown.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; remove from pan when through and break into bits.
Add onion and pepper to bacon drippings left in the pan; cook until soft.
Add bacon bits and remaining ingredients. Cook slowly for 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Remove bay leaf.

title: sensational shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Refrigerate.
Serve with chips or vegetable dippers.
Makes 3 cups.

title: jumbo raisin cookies
directions: Boil raisins in water for 5 minutes.
Cool.
Add vanilla. Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Combine with raisins.
Sift together remaining ingredients, except walnuts. Add together.
Mix and drop by large teaspoonfuls.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: fern's batter bread
directions: In large bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Blend in ginger and 1 tablespoon sugar; let stand in warm place until mixture begins to bubble.
Using an electric mixer, stir in remaining 2 tablespoons sugar, milk, salt, oil and 3 cups flour.
Blend in remaining cup of flour with spoon; knead on floured surface. Place dough in 2 well-greased one-pound coffee cans.
Place plastic lids on cans; let dough rise until lids are pushed off. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Delicious frozen and reheated.

title: pistachio hash
directions: In large bowl, mix all ingredients.
Cover and chill.

title: bacon and eggs to go
directions: Cook the bacon; set aside.
Crack egg into bowl.
Put butter in microwavable dish and melt in microwave, 20 to 25 seconds.
Mix butter, egg and milk in bowl until one texture.
Put egg mixture in microwave 60 seconds or until solid.
While preparing egg, put English muffin with cheese on both sides in toaster oven until melted.
When all cooked, put egg and bacon on English muffin and eat and enjoy.

title: meat loaf
directions: Soak bread in milk until it has soaked up all it will hold. Chop onion fine.
Mix bread, ground beef, onion, salt, egg and half of the tomato paste.
Shape into a loaf.
Top with the rest of the paste and bacon strips.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: jamaican easter bun
directions: Sift together dry ingredients, except sugar.
Beat eggs; mix with milk, sugar and oil.

Mix into dry ingredients, add fruits. Bake in greased loaf tin at 350° for 30 minutes, then reduce temperature to 300° and continue baking for 1/2 hour or more, until a knife inserted comes out clean.
Wrap with plastic wrap while still warm to retain moisture.
This will keep several weeks in refrigerator.
It is better if it sets a day or two before serving.
It also freezes very well.

title: beef chop suey
directions: Brown the onions and the ground round steak and let cook for a few minutes.
Add the tomatoes and chopped celery, adding water as needed.
Cook 20 minutes.
Add the cooked kidney beans.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Let cook for 30 to 40 minutes until everything is blended together.
Add thickening, if too thin.

title: bar cookies
directions: Cream together oleo, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix together flour, soda and salt.
Add to egg mixture.
Stir in oatmeal and chocolate chips.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes in a greased and floured 11 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Cool and cut.

title: quick and easy tea cakes
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar, beating well on medium speed of mixer.
Add eggs, beating well.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and nutmeg.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Mix well.
Stir in extract.
Drop dough by tablespoon onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.
Yield:
6 dozen.

title: sweet potato crisp(makes 8 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: pineapple cheese salad
directions: Bring pineapple, water and sugar to boil.
Add jello; let cool.
Place in the refrigerator until consistency of egg whites. Add nuts and cheese.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Congeal.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients and pour over Crispix.
Mix well and coat with powdered sugar.

title: meatballs
directions: Stir fry meatballs in soy sauce.
Melt chili sauce, jelly, and mustard in pan.
Mix all together in crock pot.
Heat on low and serve from crock pot.

title: banana split cake
directions: Prepare pudding as box directions but cut milk in half (should be thick). Add powdered sugar and melted butter to pudding mixture. Mix well.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Cook and bone chicken.
Cut or shred meat in small pieces. Line greased 9 X 13 pan with broken tortilla chips.
Spread chicken over tortillas.
Combine tomatoes with soup.
Pour over chicken.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Heat water to boiling.
Add potatoes and heat to boiling. Reduce heat; cover and cook until tender.
Drain and cool.
Cut potatoes into cubes; stir in onion, salad dressing, salt and pepper.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: peanut butter roll
directions: Mix powdered sugar, butter and vanilla with enough milk to make consistency of dough.
Roll thin; spread with peanut butter. Chill and slice in thin slices.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine contents of box of rice with hot water in 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Salt and pepper chicken and arrange on top of rice. Bake, covered, 1 1/4 hours at 375°.

title: mexican roll-ups
directions: Blend sour cream and cream cheese.
Add remaining ingredients (except tortillas) and mix well.
If tortillas are not flexible enough to roll easily, wrap in foil and warm in oven at 350° for 5 minutes.
Spread cheese mixture on tortillas.
Roll up and place seam-side down in dish.
Chill for several hours.
Slice into 1/2-inch sections and serve with picante sauce.

title: calories plus
directions: Mix together cherry pie filling, crushed pineapple and Eagle Brand milk, then add Cool Whip and pecans.
Chill.

title: texas hash
directions: Saute green peppers.
Brown beef with onion.
Cut tomatoes into large chunks.
Add all ingredients.
Stir in noodles last. Put into a greased baking dish.
Add extra tomato to cover.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Cover the dish while baking.

title: pretty good corn
directions: Place corn in a baking dish; add chopped onion and bell pepper and drained pimento.
Mix well.
Add margarine and sour cream. Mix again.
Add salt and pepper; mix again.
Bake in a preheated oven at 325° for 45 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: potatoes gourmet
directions: Cook potatoes; cool, peel and cube.
Combine butter and grated cheese; cook until cheese melts.
Combine potatoes, cheese mixture, sour cream, green onions, salt and pepper.
Put in greased 2-quart casserole.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: salami
directions: Blend all together.
Make into 12 to 14-inch roll.
Wrap in foil and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Punch holes in bottom of foil. Place on broiler rack with pan under half full of water.
Bake at 250° for 90 minutes.

title: sweet sour spareribs
directions: Brown ribs on both sides.
Drain fat.
Combine all remaining ingredients, except salt and pepper, in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until glossy.
Stir constantly.
Put ribs in small roaster and pour sauce over the top.
Salt and pepper.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: priceless pasta salad
directions: Mix pasta with yogurt, picante sauce and dressing.
Add chicken, peas and carrots and chopped onions and stir lightly. Garnish decoratively with the tomatoes and olives.
Also, it's great with shredded Cheddar for the non-dieter.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients with a spoon; pat out in long cake pan.
Mix the next 3 ingredients well; pour over dough.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and oil.
Mix dry ingredients and add to egg mixture.
Add pumpkin and blend well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from pan. Frost.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients and pour over Crispix.

(I melt the chocolate mixture in the microwave for 2 minutes and stir until mixed well, then dump the Crispix into a very large bowl or dishpan and then pour the chocolate mixture into it and stir it until each Crispix is covered, trying not to break it into crumbs.)
Put 2 cups of powdered sugar into a big brown paper bag and add the Crispix mixture.
Shake until coated and pour it into a container and begin eating.

title: sour cream noodles
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water for 7 minutes. Rinse in cold water and drain well.
Melt butter and mix with noodles.
Mix sour cream and cottage cheese together.
Add to noodles and mix well. Put in baking dish and sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake for 45 to 50 minutes in 300° oven.

title: peaches and cream pie
directions: Bake shell.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and water; cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, for 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove from heat; add peach gelatin and cool.
Add peaches.
Pour into shell.
Top with whipped cream just before serving.
Chill several hours.

title: turkey burger
directions: In bowl, mix all ingredients.
Shape into patties.
Spray broiler pan with cooking spray.
Broil 4 minutes on one side; turn and broil 5 to 6 minutes longer or until done.

title: zucchini pancakes
directions: Add cheese and Bisquick to zucchini to absorb liquid.
Add pepper to taste.
Mix and fry on low to medium heat until golden brown.

title: spicy rice and broccoli
directions: Cook rice.
Saute butter, celery and onion; set aside.
In large saucepan, melt soup, cheese and Pet milk.
Combine broccoli and cooked rice; salt and pepper to taste.
Add liquid mixture to broccoli and rice mixture, then add celery and onions.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese and pimento slices, if desired.
Bake at 325°, uncovered, for 30 minutes.

title: apricot salad
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to boil until sugar melts.
Add Jell-O and cream cheese.
Stir until cheese dissolves.
Let set until firm, then whisk with electric beater and fold in Cool Whip.

title: hershey's best brownies
directions: Blend oil, sugar and vanilla in large bowl.
Add eggs; beat well with spoon.
Combine dry ingredients; gradually add to egg mixture.
Stir in nuts, if desired.
Spread in greased square pan and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brownie begins to pull away from edges of pan.
Cool in pan.
Cut into squares.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Put sugar cookies in a pan very close together so they will bake together and form one crust.
Bake according to directions. Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla together and put on top of cookies.
Mix fruit and glaze together and put on rest of cake. Chill 30 minutes to an hour before serving.

title: drop cookies
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and butter until smooth.
Add oatmeal and flour, 1/2 cup at a time.
At the same time, add water off the raisin and soda mixture.
Add all the raisins and nuts.
Mix well.
Mix raisins and soda; let simmer in water enough to make 5 tablespoons.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 50 minutes.

title: bean soup
directions: Rinse beans.
Place in a saucepan and cover with water.
Bring to a boil.
Turn off heat and let beans soak overnight or for several hours.
In a large skillet, fry bacon until crisp.
Drain on paper towels.
Add green pepper, onions, cilantro, jalapeno and garlic to bacon drippings.
Saute until tender.
Add to beans along with crumbled bacon and water.
Cook until beans are tender. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Mix soup, 1/4 cup milk, pepper, vegetables and chicken in 9-inch pie plate. Mix remaining milk, egg and baking mix. Pour over chicken mixture. Bake 30 minutes or until golden brown. Serves 4.

title: see's fudge
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Combine in large saucepan the sugar and evaporated milk; bring to a boil for 10 minutes.
Let stand for 1 minute; stir until blended.
Pour into buttered pan or tin.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: crock-pot pizza
directions: Brown hamburger.
Cook and drain noodles.
Mix all ingredients together in a crock-pot.
Set on high for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: microwave ham and cheese casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1/2 cup of the cheese and croutons. Spoon into 1 1/2-quart microwavable casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup cheese.
Microwave on High 8 to 10 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Top with croutons.

title: green onion dip
directions: Let cream cheese sit out for a few minutes.
Drain pineapple and mix with cheese.
Chop green onions really fine and add.
Mix in about 1/2 cup pecans.
Roll in a ball or put in a bowl.
Cover with remaining pecans.
Use Hi Ho or any type crackers.

title: pepper hot corn bread
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients.
Pour 1/2 of the batter in a large skillet; sprinkle cheese on top.
Pour remaining batter on top of cheese.
Bake 35 minutes in a 400° oven.
Cool for 5 minutes and turn out on a plate.

title: ms. regina's battered fries
directions: Cut potatoes to desired thickness (shoestring, etc.).
Mix flour and meal; sprinkle Season-All seasoning into the flour and meal coating.
Dip potatoes into coating.
Deep fry until golden brown.
A delicious side dish with cold cuts (sandwiches, etc.).

title: funnel cakes
directions: Sift together flour, salt, soda, sugar and baking powder.
Mix separately the egg and milk.
Mix liquid and dry ingredients together and beat until smooth.
Heat 1 inch deep cooking oil to 375°.
Fill a small funnel with batter, holding finger over bottom.
Remove finger and let batter drop in a spiral motion into hot oil.
Fry until golden brown, turning once.
Drain on paper towel.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and serve hot.

title: stuffed cabbage("pigs in a blanket")
directions: Simmer
onions in a little margarine until soft.
Rinse rice thoroughly
and
simmer
until
slightly
tender.
Drop cabbage into
boiling water.
Mix meat, onion, rice, salt and pepper
very well.
Fill cabbage leaves with meat mixture and roll up.
Layer in
a
roasting
pan
and
cover with boiling water.
Salt top layer
lightly.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at
for 1 hour.
After baking full length of time, pour crushed tomatoes over it and bake for 1 hour more.

title: coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed and bake in 13X9 pan.
Let cool 15 minutes, then poke holes throughout cake.
In saucepan, combine milk, sugar and 1/2 c. coconut.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 1 minute.
Spoon over warm cake allowing liquid to soak through holes.
Cool completely.
Fold 1/2 c. coconut into the Cool Whip and spread over cake.
Sprinkle remaining coconut over cake.
Chill and keep refrigerated.

title: strawberry glaze
directions: Cook until thick; add red food coloring.
Cool.
Add 1 pint of sliced strawberries.
Serve over yellow cake squares in individual bowls.
Top with whipped topping.

title: supreme mustard chicken
directions: Split breasts in half lengthwise.
Cut away and discard any cartilage.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Heat butter in large heavy skillet and add breasts in one layer.
Cook over moderately low heat 3 to 4 minutes until lightly browned.
Turn and cook 7 to 8 minutes.
Transfer chicken to warm platter.
Add shallots and cook, stirring about 30 seconds.
Add wine and cook 1 minute. Add cream and cook down until reduced to about 3/4 cup.
Stir in mustard.
Return breasts to skillet and turn them in the sauce. Bring to a boil.
Sprinkle with chives and serve.
Rice goes well with this dish.

title: beef or deer chili
directions: Brown and drain meat before adding other ingredients.
Heat until very hot.
Cook 1 hour on low heat.

title: cream cheese and banana bread
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and sugar.
Add bananas and eggs. Combine dry ingredients and stir in just until moistened.
Fold in nuts if desired.
Put in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: chicken with armenian rice pilaf
directions: Rinse and pat dry chicken, either halves or quarters. Sprinkle with Crazy salt and rub generously with paprika.
Place in roasting pan and bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: punch slush
directions: *Choose Kool-Aid and Jell-O color according to color theme.

title: creamsicle drink
directions: Mix together in blender.
Pour into a tall glass with ice (crushed).

title: summer salad
directions: Mix
pineapple, cottage cheese; add dry jello.	Fold in Cool Whip and chill.

title: easy s'mores
directions: Find a long stick.
Spear 1 or 2 marshmallows onto stick. Hold over fire until marshmallows are soft and hot, but not burned.
Put marshmallows between 2 chocolate covered graham crackers.
Eat and enjoy.

title: cranberry fluff salad
directions: Combine berries, marshmallows, & sugar. Cover; let chill overnight. Add apples, grapes, walnuts, salt, & cool whip. Mix together and serve.

title: seven-layer gelatin salad
directions: In a bowl, dissolve 1 pkg. of gelatin in 3/4 cup boiling water. Add 3/4 cup cold water; stir. Spoon into a 13 x 9 in. dish coated with non-stick cooking spray. Refrigerate until almost set, about 40 minutes. In a bowl, dissolve another pkg. of gelatin in 1/2 cup boiling water. Add 1/2 cup cold water and 1/2 cup milk; stir. Spoon over the first layer. Refrigerate until almost set, about 40 minutes. Repeat five times, alternating plain gelatin with creamy gelatin, refrigerating between layers. Just before serving, spread top with whipped topping. This salad takes time to prepare since each layer must be set before the next one is added. You can change the colors to suit any occasion.

title: easy garden bake
directions: Grease pie plate; sprinkle zucchini, tomato, onion and cheese in plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth (15 seconds in blender on high).
Pour into plate.
Bake until center (with fork) comes out clean at 350° (approximately 35 minutes).
Cool 5 minutes.
Garnish with tomato and zucchini.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Saut onion and pepper in same pan.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Do this in a large pan.
Place in casserole and bake for one hour at 350°.

title: cracker candy
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line cookie sheet (needs lip) with aluminum foil.
Place crackers side by side on foil to cover entire pan.
Melt together butter and sugar; bring to boil.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Pour butter mixture over crackers and bake for 5 to 7 minutes until brown.
Sprinkle peanut butter and chocolate chips over hot crackers.
Wait a few minutes and using back of spoon, spread evenly to sides of pan.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours. Remove foil and break into pieces.

title: e-z peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into small balls.
Press onto baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: easy baked pork chops
directions: Brown chops in skillet.
Mix bouillon and soup together and pour over meat.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fat-free banana bread
directions: Blend ingredients and pour into loaf pan that has been sprayed with vegetable spray.
Bake at 350° until browned (30 to 45 minutes).

title: rolls
directions: Sprinkle yeast over the flours.
Combine eggs, milk, water, sugar and Crisco in a pan, stirring until shortening melts. Set pan off and cool just when you can set pan in hand.
Pour over flour.
Mix with hands (dough will be sticky). Cover and let rise 1 hour.
Punch dough down and refrigerate overnight or about 6 to 7 hours in the refrigerator.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Brown onions and meat; drain off grease.
Add rest of ingredients with 1 quart water.
Cook over medium heat for 3 hours.
The longer it cooks it tastes better.
I also added Worcestershire sauce and hot sauce to mine.

title: raspberry jello salad
directions: Mix dry jello with softened cream cheese.
Add boiling water. Chill until quite thick.
Whip cream (sweeten a little, if desired).
Add to thickened lemon jello mixture.
Mix well.
Pour over berry mixture already in mold.
Let set.

title: hot fudge sundae cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar and 2 tablespoons cocoa. Mix in milk, oil and vanilla with fork.
Stir in nuts.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa. Pour hot water over batter.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: sweet and sour chicken casserole
directions: Mix dressing, dried soup and preserves in a bowl.
Place chicken pieces in casserole dish; pour mix over chicken.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate bread pudding
directions: Pour milk over bread.
Add salt and sugar.
Beat eggs, add to bread mixture with butter, melted chocolate and vanilla.
Mix well. Pour into 1 1/2-quart greased casserole.
Sit casserole in pan and fill to 1-inch top of casserole.
Cover.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes until knife comes out clean.

title: soft caramels
directions: Melt butter in a 3-quart heavy saucepan.
Add sugar.
Stir thoroughly.
Add corn syrup; stir.
Gradually add milk.
Cook (stirring) to 240° (30 minutes) or soft ball.
Add vanilla.
Pour into a 9 x 18-inch pan.
Cool and score.
Can be dipped in chocolate.
Melt together chocolate chips and chocolate bar.
Keep hot; dip candy (using 2 forks) until well coated.
Place on cookie sheet or wax paper.
Chill.

title: apple crumb
directions: Peel and slice apples; boil until soft.
Drain all but 1/2 cup water.
Sweeten apples to taste.
Pour into casserole.
In another bowl, mix sugar and flour; cut in butter.
Sprinkle on top of apples.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: congo squares
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: mexicale fondue
directions: Put all ingredients in an ovenproof dish.
Melt in a 300° oven.
Keep warm while serving in a fondue dish.
Stir occasionally.
Serve with taco chips and bread sticks.

title: cheese soup
directions: Add and simmer on stove top.

title: angel food pineapple cake
directions: Mix pineapple (undrained), Cool Whip, pudding and vanilla.
Let stand for 5 minutes and then put between layers and on top.

title: upside-down breakfast
directions: Drain pineapple.
Cook bacon.
Heat butter in a 10-inch round glass dish at 400° until melted.
Arrange bacon slices on bottom of dish so they overlap.
Spoon pineapple over bacon.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Mix milk, egg and Bisquick.
Carefully spread over pineapple.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Run knife around edges and invert on heatproof plate right away.

title: all-american cobbler
directions: Mix other ingredients, except fruit, and pour over butter. Cover with fruit.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Scoop sherbet into chilled liquids in punch bowl at serving time.
Makes 30 punch cup servings.

title: custard sauce
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and salt; add gradually to scalded milk. Cook in double boiler, stirring, until mixture thickens.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak in thin strips.
Preheat browning dish on High (max power) for 7 minutes.
Smear oil over dish and all beef strips. Cook on High (max power) for 2 to 3 minutes, flipping strips after 1 minute, or when strips are brown.
Stir and add garlic.
Cook, covered, on 70 (Roast) for 7 minutes.
Dissolve cornstarch in soy sauce and add to meat.
If your browning dish is too small to hold meat and remaining ingredients, transfer to a 2-quart casserole.
Stir and blend in remaining ingredients.
Cook, covered, on High (max power) for 8 to 10 minutes or until vegetables are just tender.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving. Makes 4 servings.

title: good party cake
directions: Bake cake in a 15 x 11-inch pan and cool.
Make pudding with milk.
Beat cream cheese into hot pudding.
Cool slightly and spread on cooled cake.
Top with 1 pint of Cool Whip or heavy whipping cream (whipped).
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: apricot balls
directions: Mix all together and form into small balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Makes about 4 dozen.
Keeps in refrigerator for several days.
Can also be frozen.

title: linguine with garden clam sauce
directions: In large skillet melt oleo over medium heat.
Add zucchini and garlic, saute 2 minutes.
Add tomato and oregano, saute 2 minutes. Combine clam broth with enough water to equal 1 3/4 cups.
Stir in cornstarch until smooth.
Add to skillet with bouillon cubes and clams.
Stirring constantly, bring to a boil over medium heat. Boil 1 minute.
Toss with linguine and Parmesan cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: banana-chocolate chip muffins
directions: Slice bananas into blender and puree or mash with a fork. Beat pureed bananas, eggs, sugar, butter and vanilla until well blended.
Combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Make well in center of dry ingredients.
Pour in banana mixture.
Mix until just blended. Spoon into muffin tins that have been lined with paper muffin cups.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.
Do not overbake.
Some ovens are hotter (only bake 20 minutes).

title: fried pineapple tidbits
directions: Mix milk and egg; dip chunks into milk and egg mixture.
Roll in bread crumbs.
Deep fry.
