title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, flour and margarine.
Add vanilla.
Add buttermilk and mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes in 400° oven, then reduce heat to 300° and continue baking for 30 more minutes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix together pumpkin, sugar, eggs, cooking oil, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add salt, soda, flour and nuts (if desired).
Bake in Bundt pan in 350° oven for 70 to 75 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: eric's turnover fun
directions: Press each crescent a little larger than it comes from roll. Place some ham and cheese in the middle.
Fold over into turnover shape.
Sprinkle on seed.
Bake as directed on can.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: In a large saucepan, cook onion in oleo until tender. Stir in flour and pepper until smooth. Add milk all at once.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly, about 1 minute.
Add cheese and stir until melted. Remove from heat.
In medium saucepan, dissolve cubes in water. Add bay leaf.
Bring to a boil and add broccoli. Cook until done and do not drain. Add broccoli and liquid to cheese mixture. Stir until well blended. Remove bay leaf.
Makes 5 (1 cup) servings.

title: apple pound cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil; add eggs and beat well. Combine flour, soda and salt to oil mixture. Stir in vanilla, apples, coconut and walnuts and mix well. Spoon batter into an oiled 9-inch tube pan. Bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: squash pickles
directions: Layer vegetables and salt.
Let stand 1 to 8 hours.
Drain off excess liquid.
Heat all other ingredients.
Pour over vegetables and bring to a boil.
Put in jars and seal.

title: lorna's pickles
directions: Cover cucumbers, onion, peppers, garlic and salt with ice cubes and mix, let stand 3 hours then drain.
Add sugar, turmeric, celery seed, mustard seed and vinegar - bring to a boil.
Seal in hot jars.

title: strawberry-rhubarb pie
directions: Preheat the oven to 425°. In a large bowl, combine the strawberries and sugar. Mix well until the sugar dissolves. Have pie crusts ready in pie plate. Add the remaining ingredients to the strawberry mixture. Mix well and spoon into the pie crust. Place the top pie crust on top of filling. Cut slits in crust. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until the crust is golden and filling is bubbly. Allow to cool slightly before serving or chill until ready to serve. Makes 6 servings.

title: plum pudding
directions: Cream well the butter or margarine with confectioners sugar, adding during mixing about 1/3 cup brandy to right texture.
Spoon over pudding slices.

title: amish cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine; add milk-soda mixture, flour and vanilla. Bake 370° for 40 to 50 minutes. Take out and add topping.

title: old fashioned oatmeal cookies
directions: Simmer raisins and water until raisins are plump (20 to 30 minutes). Drain raisins.
Put liquid in cup and add enough water to make 1/2 cup.
Mix shortening, eggs, sugar and vanilla. Add raisin liquid.
Sift dry ingredients and add oats, nuts and raisins.
Drop by spoonful on cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.

title: chilled lemon souffle
directions: Mix yolks with sugar and lemon juice.
Stir gelatin and water together.
Place gelatin mixture in small pan of hot water, allowing to melt.
Cool slightly and mix with egg yolks.
In a large bowl, beat egg whites until stiff.
In another large bowl, beat cream until stiff.
Fold all ingredients together gently. Pour into souffle dish or crystal bowl.
Cover with plastic wrap and chill for 2 hours.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Combine sugar, salt, cinnamon, flour, eggs and butter.
Add rhubarb. Place in pie crust (9 or 10-inch). Bake 50 minutes at 375°.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix this batter by hand.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 350° for one hour and 15 minutes.

title: microwave brownies
directions: Melt margarine in 2-quart bowl on High for 1 minute or until melted.
Add sugar. Cool. Add eggs and vanilla.
Pour all dry ingredients into sugar mixture and blend in. Add nuts, if desired. Pour into a 9-inch glass cake pan. Cook on High for 4 1/2 to 5 1/2 minutes, turning 3 times. Cool before cutting.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Soften cream cheese (room temperature).
Mix all ingredients and refrigerate 24 hours before serving.
Dip gets hotter the longer it sits.

title: beef and corn casserole
directions: Cook noodles until almost tender; set aside.
Sear meat.
Add onion.
Cook until tender.
Add salt, soups, sour cream, corn and pimento.
Place in a greased casserole dish.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: aunt becky's cabbage roll casserole
directions: Layer a 9 x 13-inch casserole pan.
First, layer sauce. Second, layer cabbage.
Third, Mix uncooked rice and uncooked meat.
Continue layering until pan is full.
Top with crushed tomatoes.
Cover and cook at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until cabbage is cooked.

title: shoepeg corn salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients; stir well and pour over vegetables.
Toss gently; cover and chill 8 to 10 hours.
Drain.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: farmer's casserole
directions: Grease a square 2 quart baking dish.
Put potatoes in bottom of dish, then sprinkle with cheese, ham and green onions.
Combined rest of ingredients and pour over potatoe mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 55-60 minutes. Serves 6.

title: hamburger relish
directions: Tie spices up in a white cloth.
Put in mixture and let boil slow until thick.
Take out spices.
Can in hot jars.

title: chicken herbed rice
directions: Combine on stovetop in heavy saucepan; cover and bring to boil. Simmer 20 to 25 minutes.
Stir.
Or microwave in 2-quart casserole. Cover.
Cook on High for 5 minutes, Low 17 minutes.
Standing time 5 minutes.
Stir.

title: no bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar.
Add oleo and milk. Bring to a boil. Boil 1 minute. Remove from heat. Beat in oatmeal and vanilla. Drop on wax paper to desired size.
Cool and eat.

title: miniature meatballs
directions: Brown the onions in oil in a large skillet, then add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: quick and easy cherry cheese cake
directions: Combine Cool Whip, sugar and cream cheese with mixer until smooth.
Pour into pie crust and refrigerate.
Top with filling before serving.

title: ragout raleigh
directions: In a very heavy skillet, arrange half-strips of bacon over entire bottom.
Cut strips of round steak and put on top of bacon. Add salt and pepper.
Cover meat with sliced carrots and onions; top with potatoes.
Add salt, pepper and parsley flakes.
Cover and cook over low heat for 2 hours to 2 1/2 hours or until done.

title: date bread
directions: Blend sugar and oil, then add egg and beat until smooth.
Sift the flour with dry ingredients.
Add to the creamed mixture alternately with the milk.
Fold in the dates.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
When top springs back when pressed with finger, remove from oven and sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar with 1 tablespoon cinnamon.
Serve hot.
Serves 12.

title: dietetic peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine peanut butter and eggs. Add Sugar Twin and mix well.
Thoroughly mix in dry ingredients. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with tines of fork.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes or until done. Makes about 30 cookies.
Calories per cookie, 26.
Keeps better if refrigerated.

title: pecan pie(two pies)
directions: Mix all ingredients well by mixer.
Put in refrigerator overnight, then place the pecans in bottom of pie shell evenly. Pour filling on top of pecans and let sit for 5 to 8 minutes or until pecans come to the top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. You can keep and use this filling for 2 or 3 weeks by keeping in refrigerator, but mix well before using.

title: pepper steak
directions: Dip steak in flour and brown in large skillet.
Add all other ingredients and cook on low for 3 hours.
Add small amounts of water to keep from sticking.
Serves 6.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: Peel and cut apples in thick slices and arrange in overlapping rows in pie shell.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine sugar, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg and cut in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Spoon over apples and spread with sour cream. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and bake 20 to 25 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: chocolate pixies
directions: Melt chocolate.
Combine oil, chocolate and sugar.
Beat in 1 egg at a time, add vanilla.
Add sifted flour and dry ingredients. Chill several hours.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet after rolling in confectioners sugar.
Bake at 350° until done, 10 to 12 minutes.

title: monterey spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Meanwhile, beat egg.
Add sour cream, Parmesan cheese and garlic powder. Drain spaghetti; add to egg mixture with Monterey Jack.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix cake mix, flour and gelatin, break any lumps.
(I sift mine together in flour sifter.)
Add oil, water and strawberries, mixing thoroughly; add eggs one at a time.
Beat a minute or two; pour into two 9-inch cake pans or a sheet pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: low calorie hot dish
directions: Top of stove method:
Saute hamburger, add cabbage and onions. Cook 5 minutes.
Add rice, tomato soup and water or canned tomatoes.
Cook on low until all is done, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: supreme bean salad
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in large bowl, toss well.
Combine vinegar, sugar, oil, salt and pepper.
Boil stirring constantly. Pour over bean mixture.
Toss gently.
Chill 3 hours.
Contains 2.3 grams fat per serving.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift together the flour, salt, tartar and soda and stir into first mixture.
Form dough into 2-inch balls and roll each in a mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 tablespoons cinnamon.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Add all ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie crust, top with a crust and bake at 350°.

title: klip klops
directions: Soak bread in skim milk.
Add garlic powder, onion salt, ground beef and egg; mix thoroughly.
Form into 8 balls.
Combine water, bay leaf, salt and clove.
Bring to a boil.
Drop balls into boiling water and cook until beef is done (about 15 minutes). Drain before placing on platter.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Whip lemon juice and Eagle Brand milk until thick.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a prepared graham cracker crust.

title: tangy lemon squares
directions: In a large bowl, cream together butter and 1/2 cup powdered sugar until fluffy.
Add 2 cups of the flour, beating until blended.
Spread evenly over the bottom of a well-greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: south of the border tamale pie
directions: Cook sausage, add other ingredients.
Continue until all are heated.
Serve.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix ingredients and chill.

title: pizza fruit dessert
directions: Mix ingredients with mixer and spread with spoon on 2 greased pizza pans.
Bake at 325° for about 12 to 14 minutes.
Cool. Spread 12 ounces of Cool Whip on crusts.
Top with fruits such as strawberries, seedless grapes, mandarin oranges, blueberries, bananas, and pineapple tidbits.

title: grammy's chicken fried steak
directions: Pound steak with meat mallet and cut into serving pieces. Blend eggs with milk and seasonings.
Dip meat into egg mixture and coat with cracker crumbs.
Slowly brown each piece on both sides in hot oil.
Cover and simmer until meat is tender, about 1 hour. Make gravy with drippings.

title: perfect chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Shake flour in regular size (10 x 16-inch) Reynolds oven cooking bag.
Place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Add rice, butter, vegetables, broth and water; squeeze bag gently to blend ingredients.
Tie chicken legs with string. Brush chicken with oil; sprinkle with seasonings.
Place chicken in bag on top of rice.
Close bag with nylon tie.
Make 6 (1/2-inch) slits in top.
Bake 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until thigh joint moves easily when bag and leg are grasped with pot holder.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the margarine and Crisco, adding sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flavorings.
Add flour and milk.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until done, at 350°.

title: baretta's squash casserole
directions: Boil onion and squash together until tender.
Drain and mash slightly.
Set aside.
Grate carrot and mix with sour cream, 1/2 bag of stuffing, stuffing seasoning, soup and chicken broth.
Add squash and mix together.
Add margarine to remaining stuffing; microwave and mix together.
Add to top of casserole.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in mixer.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Use an oblong cake pan.

title: picnic potatoes
directions: Mix hash browns, melted margarine, sour cream, onion, soup, 1/2 cup grated cheese, salt and pepper in a large bowl.
Transfer to a 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish. Top with more Cheddar cheese or crumbled corn flakes. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix flour, soda and sugar.
Add pineapple and eggs.
Mix well with spoon.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: puppy cookies (non-food)
directions: Mix and knead dough until smooth.
Roll dough until 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutter.
Microwave for 5 to 6 minutes on Medium-high, then turn over and microwave for 3 minutes more or bake at 350° until brown.
Puppy will enjoy!

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Mix all ingredients except cheese. Pour in greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: snow-capped meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix lightly.
Place in a deep cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Pour off excess fat.
Spread with potato topping.

title: marjorie books' date pudding
directions: Combine ingredients in first batter and pour into greased pan.

title: mudder's chocolate pies
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa together in pan. Add eggs, milk and margarine to mixture. Cook on stove top until mixture becomes thick and add vanilla. Pour into pie crusts. Mix egg whites and sugar together in a separate bowl. Beat together until meringue is formed. Pour over the top of chocolate and bake until meringue begins to brown lightly. Makes 2 pies.

title: first communion punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in 6 cups boiling water; let cool.
Mix first 5 ingredients in large bowl.
Add sugar mixture.
Divide into 3 equal parts; can freeze.
When ready to use, take 1 part punch to 2 quarts ginger ale.

title: lemon marmalade
directions: Place lemon slices and water in large kettle; cover.
Bring to boiling; boil rapidly for 25 minutes.
Remove from heat; add sugar, stirring until dissolved.
Return to heat.
Boil rapidly, uncovered and without stirring, about 25 minutes, or until marmalade slides off spoon in 2 thick drops that run together. Remove from heat at once skim top.
If desired, add a few candied cherries for color.
Ladle marmalade into hot, sterilized jelly glasses or gift containers.
Cool until marmalade sets.
Top containers with thin layer of melted paraffin.
Cover with dry clean lids or aluminum foil; label.
Store in cool, dry place.

title: cucumber and onion slaw
directions: Put
cucumbers	and
onions
in shallow bowl.
Sprinkle with salt
and
let
stand 15 to 20 minutes.
In another bowl, combine cream or milk, sugar and vinegar.
Add enough water to thin mixture.
Add
more
sugar	and/or	vinegar
to
taste. Squeeze liquid from cucumbers and onions and add vegetables to cream mixture.
Chill and serve.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix in blender and pour into pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 65 minutes.

title: duroglas (mayonnaise) cake
directions: Mix salad dressing and warm water together; add to flour mixture.
Add food coloring and vanilla.
Beat until smooth. Batter will be thin.
Bake in slow oven at 325° for about 30 minutes.
Test by putting toothpick in center.
If it comes out clean, take out.
If not, leave in oven for another 5 minutes.

title: biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 500°.
Roll biscuit in your hands and cook in a cake pan for about 10 minutes.
You need to use real butter.

title: impossible pie
directions: Place all ingredients into a blender and blend well.
Pour mixture into a buttered 9-inch pie pan.
Pan will be full.
Bake for 30 minutes at 400° or until brown and set.
Allow to cool before serving.
The pie will make its own crust and golden topping.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Steam rice in water and salt.
Boil broccoli according to package directions.
Mix all ingredients together and cook 10 minutes.
Put into greased casserole dish; cover and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: frosted creams
directions: Mix ingredients, then spread on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°. Frost with powdered sugar glaze.
Cut into squares.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal in large mixing bowl.
Let stand at room temperature 10 minutes.
Add both sugars and margarine.
Add eggs and beat.
Add flour, baking soda, salt and cocoa.
Mix.
Add half the chocolate chips and blend in.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle remaining chocolate chips and walnuts over top.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: m&m's cookies
directions: Mix shortening, brown sugar and regular sugar.
Blend in vanilla and eggs.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt.
Add dry ingredients to sugar and egg mixture.
Blend well.
Stir in 1/2 cup of M&M's.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls of cookie dough 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Decorate tops with remaining M&M's.
Bake on center rack at 375° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove to wire racks.
Cool completely.

title: irish potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water about 30 minutes, until tender. Drain and mash.
Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add potatoes and remaining ingredients, except paprika.
Spoon mixture into a lightly buttered 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with paprika. Cover and store in refrigerator overnight.
Remove next day 15 minutes before baking.
Uncover and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook ground beef according to directions on taco seasoning package.
Drain and set aside to cool.
Chop lettuce, onion, green peppers, olives and tomatoes; mix well.
Crush tortilla chips; add to mixture.
Add kidney beans and ground beef.
Mix sour cream with Catalina dressing.
Pour over salad and mix well.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Serves 15 to 20 people,
For smaller portion, cut recipe in half.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Slice peeled cucumbers very thinly.
Sprinkle with salt.
Put weight on to press down for 2 to 3 hours.
Pour off liquid.
Mix vinegar, water and sugar.
Then add to cucumbers.

title: sugar and spice muffins
directions: Mix
ingredients together until moist.	Pour into muffin tins and sprinkle with topping:	combine 2 tablespoons sugar, 2 tablespoons flour and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.	Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: my favorite holiday pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 300° for about 1 hour.
Yields one 8-inch pie.

title: veal marsala
directions: Set out a large, heavy skillet having a tight fitting cover. Heat in skillet until lightly browned garlic and oil.
Wipe with a clean, damp cloth.
Pound and cut into six pieces.
Coat veal with a mixture of:
flour, salt and pepper.
Add veal to garlic and olive oil and slowly brown on both sides.
While veal is browning, combine Marsala wine, water, chopped parsley, salt and pepper. Slowly add Marsala mixture to browned veal.
Cover skillet and simmer very slowly for about 20 minutes or until veal is tender. If mixture tends to become too thick, add small amount of water.

title: guacamole(from pat danner's favorite recipes)
directions: Cut avocados in half, remove the seed and scoop out pulp with a spoon.
Mash pulp with a fork into a soft puree and add the lemon juice, salt, pepper, garlic, jalapeno peppers and hot sauce. Blend in cream cheese.
Makes approximately 2 cups.

title: almond cheesecake
directions: Almond Crust:
Preheat the oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients together in a bowl.
Transfer to a 9-inch spring-form cake pan.
Press the mixture on the bottom and sides of the pan. Bake this shell for 10 minutes in the oven.
Remove and set aside.

title: angel food cake
directions: Put into large bowl of Mixmaster the egg whites and salt. Beat on speed 10 until foamy, about 1/2 minute. Add cream of tartar. Continue beating on speed 10 or high until whites are stiff and stand at point, abut 2 1/2 to 3 minutes. Do not overbeat until dry. Sprinkle in rapidly the sifted sugar. While beating on speed 8, beat only until sugar is blended, about 1 minute. Scrape bowl gently toward beaters and up and over with a folding motion. Decrease speed to 2. Add vanilla extract and almond extract. Sprinkle in sifted flour mixture evenly and quickly. Beat only enough to blend, about 1 1/2 minutes, scraping bowl towards beaters in a folding motion to blend in quickly. Gently put into tube pan. Carefully cut through batter with a knife or spatula, going around in circular motion 6 times to release large air bubbles. Bake in preheated oven (375°) for 30 to 35 minutes until golden brown.

title: oatmeal fudge bars
directions: Heat oven to
Grease
jelly roll pan.
Mix brown sugar, margarine,	eggs
and
vanilla.
Stir in baking mix and oats. Heat
chips,
milk, 2 tablespoons margarine and salt in 2-quart saucepan over low heat until smooth.
Stir in nuts and vanilla. Press
about
oatmeal	mixture
in pan.
Spread chocolate mixture over oatmeal layer.
Drop remaining oatmeal mixture by tablespoon onto top.
Bake until light brown about 30 minutes. Cool completely.
Cut into bars about 2 x 1 inch. Makes 70 bars.

title: frozen frango bars
directions: Mix cookie crumbs and 1/2 cup margarine (or butter) and place in the bottom of 24 foil cupcake liners in muffin tins.

title: pasta with spinach
directions: About 30 minutes before serving:

title: instant hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Use 1/3 cup of this mixture for 1 cup of cocoa.
Just add hot water.

title: chicken salad supreme
directions: Combine and serve in lettuce cups with thin slices of chicken on top. Garnish with stuffed olives, sliced thin, or chopped ripe olives.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all together and add mayonnaise as desired.

title: hot tomato ketchup
directions: Mix all together.
Cook 2 to 2 1/2 hours until jelly like, stirring constantly.
Put in jars and seal.

title: lasagna
directions: Saute ground beef with garlic in skillet until crumbly.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Mix well.
Simmer, covered, for 20 minutes. Alternate layers of ground beef mixture, noodles and cheese in 8 x 11-inch dish, ending with ground beef.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in a casserole dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 1 hour until rice is tender.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in a med. size oven proof bowl for 30 mins. at 350 degrees.
Serve with Triscuits or thin sliced crusty bread.

title: pig stomach
directions: Mix last six ingredients together and stuff in stomach.
Put in roaster with an inch or two of water.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: custard sauce
directions: Time:
about 25 minutes before serving or early in day. Yield:
about 2 1/4 cups.

title: corned beef dinner
directions: Combine corned beef, soup, milk, cheese and onion.
Alternate layers of cooked macaroni and meat mixture in a deep 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325° or until casserole is bubbling all around outside edge.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix flour, jello and sugar, then add water.
Bring to a boil; continue cooking until mixture thickens.
While mixture is cooling, bake pie shell.
After shell is baked, put sliced strawberries into baked shell.
Pour strawberry mixture over berries.
Chill for about 3 hours before serving.

title: birds
directions: Cut round steak into 5 x 3-inch pieces.
Pound until 1/4-inch thick.
Place chopped onion and pepper in the middle of the pieces and sprinkle with the spices to taste.
Place hamburger with the onion and pepper.
Wrap the steak around the hamburger and close it up with toothpicks to make the Birds.
Melt shortening in a cast-iron skillet and brown the Birds.
Add water and simmer until tender.
Add a few drops of Kitchen Bouquet browning sauce. Remove Birds and thicken for gravy.

title: baked squash
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Put in casserole dish; bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Add all ingredients to beaten eggs.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: green and gold
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Add sliced carrots and lemon juice.
Stir until all carrots are coated with butter.
Cover skillet and let carrots steam over low to medium fire until softened.
Add washed spinach without draining.
Add 2 tablespoons water if carrots are dry.
Cover and steam vegetables until spinach is limp; about 6 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: sweet and sour meat balls
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° on cookie sheet for 25 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.

title: escalloped corn
directions: Mix in order given & put in buttered baking dish.
Bake in moderate oven for 45 minutes.

title: hot and sour soup
directions: Bring first 5 ingredients to a boil and simmer 10 minutes. Add remaining ingredients.
When soup clears, turn off heat and stir in 1 beaten egg.
Add a few drops of vegetable oil.
Garnish with finely chopped green onion.
Serves 4.

title: peanut butter crinkles
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together well.
Add dry ingredients and mix.
Roll into balls.
Roll in white sugar.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet for 5 to 7 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon soy grilled chicken
directions: Place chicken halves in large shallow pan.
Combine other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Let sit at room temperature for 1 hour, turning frequently.
Cook on grill, turning and basting 1 hour.

title: sensational shrimp spread
directions: Beat cheese until fluffy; gradually beat in lemon juice.
Stir in shrimp, onion, horseradish and pepper.
Chill to blend flavors. Serve on Melba rounds.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Mix by hand.
Place in greased pan.
Cook 20 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini parmigiana
directions: Simmer tomatoes, tomato paste and olive oil for 25 minutes. Saute zucchini in oil until soft.
Combine seasoned bread crumbs, parsley, Parmesan cheese and garlic.
In a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish, layer half the zucchini, bread mixture, tomato sauce and Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: shipwreck
directions: Brown ground beef.
Layer in greased casserole dish the ground meat, sliced potatoes (partially cooked), kidney beans and sliced onion rings.
Repeat with 2nd layer of each, then sprinkle rice over top, then add tomato sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: grandma's caramel candy
directions: Combine sugar, salt, butter and corn syrup in a heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil over low heat, stirring constantly. Add milk slowly.
Candy should remain at a boil.
Cook, without stirring, to 244° on candy thermometer or firm ball stage.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Pour into greased, shallow pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: delicious dinosaur eggs
directions: Gently tap egg until shell cracks all over.
Do not take off shells.
In medium bowl, stir water and Kool-Aid.
Add cracked eggs.
Cover bowl with plastic wrap and place in refrigerator. Leave for 1 to 2 days.
Remove eggs and peel shells off.
Your dinosaur eggs are ready to eat.
Great for children's parties.

title: cinnamon cake
directions: Cream oleo.
Add 1 cup of sugar.
Beat until thick and light in color.
Add the egg, beating well.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
Add to the butter or oleo mixture alternately with the milk.
Mix well.
Pour mixture into a greased 8-inch square pan.
Mix cinnamon and remaining sugar together and sprinkle on top.
Bake for 25 minutes or until a cake tester comes out clean.
Serve warm.

title: 1-2-3 broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions on box; drain.
Pour rice into baking dish.
Add all ingredients to rice.
Place in microwave; cook 10 to 20 minutes, until cheese is melted.

title: white fluffy icing
directions: In double boiler mix with hand mixer ten minutes.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Spread on cake.

title: chicken lickin
directions: Place chicken in baking pan.
Combine all ingredients, except cream.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: ruby's fried pie crust
directions: Blend together milnot, eggs and water add dry ingredients. Mix well. Roll and put saucer on it and cut around saucer.
Then put cooled fruit on each, fold over and mash around edges. Punch wholes with fork on top, then fry in deep fryer til golden brown. Make 50 pies.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, onion and salt until tender. Drain. Add remaining ingredients. Reserve enough cracker crumbs for top.
Pour in 1 1/2-quart casserole, well-greased.
Set in a pan of water.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until set.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain beans and carrots.
Add green pepper and onion rings to beans.

title: mystery cocoa cake
directions: The mystery ingredient gives the cake a coconut like texture.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat
eggs.
Add sugar and flour then buttermilk.
Cook on top of	stove
in a pot, stirring constantly so it will not scorch. Remove
from
stove.
Add flavoring.
Pour into baked pie crust. (A graham cracker pie crust is preferred by some.)

title: cabbage supreme
directions: In Dutch oven add small amount of water and cook cabbage 12 minutes.
Drain.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In saucepan, cook green pepper and onion in margarine until tender. Blend in flour, salt and pepper. Add milk.
Cook and stir.
Pour over cabbage. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 20 minutes. Combine mayonnaise, cheese and chili sauce.
Spoon over top and bake about 5 minutes more.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix together the chicken, cut in cubes, water chestnuts, sprouts, celery and onion.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix chicken, soup, picante sauce and 3/4 cup cheese.
Place 3 to 4 tablespoons in each tortilla.
Roll and place in ovenproof dish.
Spread remaining mixture on top, then top with remaining cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes or microwave 10 minutes on 80% power.
Serve with lettuce and sour cream.

title: lois' cheese cake
directions: Combine the crumbs with the sugar and melted butter or margarine. Press into two 8-inch round cake pans and save some for topping (1/4 cup is plenty).

title: old-time molasses cake
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Bake the batter at 325° to 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: squash puppies
directions: Cook squash in water for 20 minutes; drain.
Mash and drain again.
Combine squash and all other ingredients.
Drop by tablespoonfuls into hot oil and fry about 5 minutes or until brown.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen puppies.

title: broccoli cheese and rice
directions: Pour 1/2 cup milk, margarine and cheese in saucepan.
Melt cheese over medium heat, stirring constantly, until melted.
Pour over prepared broccoli and rice.
Mix thoroughly.
Add milk, a little at a time, until moist.
Heat, covered, in microwave 10 minutes on High and serve.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except margarine and crackers.
Place in 2-quart casserole.
Melt margarine.
Crumble crackers.
Place crackers on top of casserole.
Pour margarine over top.

title: easy cream puff dessert
directions: Boil together the water and margarine.
Add the flour and salt to the water mixture.
Stir over heat until smooth and sticks together in a lump.
Remove from heat.
Beat in the eggs, one at a time (electric mixer).
Spread on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes (approximately) until light brown and crust is done.
Let cool.

title: sweet potato salad
directions: Mix all together and spread in 9 x 9 x 2-inch dish.

title: taco salad
directions: Break up
fry
bread on plate.
Add meat sauce, then lettuce (or cabbage), tomatoes, carrots and cheese over all.
A whole meal!
May be as varied as you choose.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine buttermilk and eggs.
Add meal, salt, soda, onions, garlic, corn and peppers.
Pour half of mixture in a hot greased skillet.
Add cheese and meat.
Then pour remaining batter over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: date nut bread
directions: Put dates and baking soda in a bowl; pour boiling water over date mixture and let stand until cool.
Cream together the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Put in date mixture and flour.
Mix in nuts.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: wing dings
directions: Put chicken on foil-covered cookie sheet.
Mix ingredients and pour over chicken. Bake at 350° until done.
Turn several times while cooking.

title: apricot bars
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, brown sugar and oatmeal.
Cut in butter until well blended.
Press 2/3 of mixture in bottom of 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Cover with apricot jam.
Sprinkle with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool slightly; cut into squares.

title: cream of mushroom soup(from dried & fresh mushrooms)
directions: Sprinkle meat with salt, add cold water and let stand 1/2 hour before bringing to slow boil. Lower heat and simmer gently until meat is tender. Remove meat and reserve for another use. Do not strain broth.

title: carrot ring
directions: Add and mix all ingredients except peas. Put in a ring mold. Set mold in a medium pan with a little water. Put green peas or other green vegetables of your choice in the middle. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: heavenly cheese cake
directions: Dissolve sugar and yeast in cooled milk and set aside.
Mix flour and butter as for pie crust.
Add yeast and milk to egg yolks and mix well.
Add flour to make a soft dough.

title: english trifle
directions: Make tapioca; refrigerate.
Dissolve jello in water.
Stir in ice cream, fruit and nuts.
Pour equally into bowl or glass bowl. Refrigerate.
When almost set, layer half of cake in the glass bowl.
Spread 1/2 pudding over this.
Pour over partially set jello from bowl over tapioca.
Add remaining cake crumbs and finally a tapioca layer.
Refrigerate.
To serve, top with cream. Serves 12.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Combine and marinate for several hours in refrigerator.

title: pastillas de mani
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook over low heat, stirring constantly to avoid burning. Cook until it thickens. Sprinkle sugar on a bread board and spread the mixture with a rolling pin. Cut into desired pieces.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut steak into bite size pieces; brown in skillet.
Boil noodles until done; drain well.
Mix sour cream, mushroom soup and mushrooms with noodles.
Add steak; mix very well.
If stroganoff seems stiff or dry, you can add another can of mushroom soup or a little water.
Serve hot.
Freezes well.
Delicious as a leftover.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Cook and stir green pepper and mushrooms in margarine over low heat 5 minutes.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat and stir milk, broth and mushroom liquid; heat to boiling. Stir constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute chicken and pimento; heat. Serve over rice or noodles.
Serves 6.

title: strawberry balls(it's just not christmas unless we have strawberry balls)
directions: Melt butter in a 2-quart pan; stir in beaten eggs which have been combined with sugar.
Add chopped dates and cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add salt, vanilla and nuts.
Stir in Rice Krispies, mixing well.
Cool to lukewarm. Spray your hands with Pam, then shape mixture into 1-inch balls. Roll in gelatin and store in Tupperware in the refrigerator.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until brown.

title: no cook peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt margarine and peanut butter together.
Remove from heat. Add vanilla and sugar and mix all together.
Pour into lightly greased pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Melt chocolate bar in double boiler.
Pour into bowl with Cool Whip.
Stir, then pour into pie crust.
Refrigerate for 3 hours.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Stir in cream cheese with juice or cream.
Add salt. Gradually add enough 10x sugar to give a good spreading consistency; beat until creamy.
Makes enough for 1 1/2 dozen cupcakes or 2 layer cake.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Heat juice to boiling; add paste mixture and boil until clear. Put aside to cool.
In a bowl, put pineapple tidbits, cheese and nuts.
Stir in sauce when cooled.
Add marshmallows.
Cool and serve.
If set overnight, marshmallows become soggy.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil 1 minute the sugar, milk, butter and cocoa.
Remove from heat. Add oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla. Drop by tablespoon on greased sheet.
Let set until firm.

title: reese's tarts
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Slice and quarter cookies.
Place quarter cookie in mini muffin pan.
Bake 3 to 4 minutes or until cookies puff up.
Push Reese's cup into cookie.
Bake additional 4 to 5 minutes.
Remove from oven and place pecan half on top of each.

title: treet and beans
directions: Dice Treet; mix ingredients in pan. Heat to taste.

title: broccoli-pea casserole
directions: Drain broccoli and peas well.
Cook broccoli according to directions.
Arrange half of cooked broccoli in 2-quart casserole. Cover with peas.

title: rocky road brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F.
Grease 8 in. square pan.
Mix butter and cocoa in pan over low heat, stirring till smooth.
Take from heat and add sugar, egg, flour, buttermilk, and vanilla.
Stir till smooth.
Pour in pan and bake for 25 min. or until toothpick comes out clean.
(Do not overbake.)
Take out of oven, put marshmallow, pecans, and chip on cake.
Put back in oven for another 3 - 5 min. till melted.

title: after-the-holidays salad(servings:  4)
directions: In a mixing bowl, toss first six ingredients.
In a small bowl, combine all remaining ingredients except lettuce.
Pour over turkey and mix gently.
Chill.
Serve on a bed of lettuce, if desired.
Yields 4 servings.
The fruit, nuts and seasonings give the salad a unique flavor.

title: mom's pecan pie
directions: Beat egg whites, adding sugar slowly, until very stiff.
Add vanilla.
Mix crumbled crackers and chopped pecans together, then fold into egg whites.
Pour into a greased glass pie pan and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Will be light brown.
Let cool and serve topped with Cool Whip, sprinkled with chopped pecans.

title: lemonade
directions: Mix together water, sugar and lemonade mix.
Wash and slice lemon and oranges.
Lay orange and lemon slices on top of lemonade.
Stir and chill.
Oranges and lemons can be reused 2 more times with new mixture.

title: low calorie swiss steak
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Cut steak into four pieces. Pound flour mixture into steak.
In heavy skillet, melt margarine. Add meat and brown on both sides.
Add remaining ingredients. Reduce heat and simmer for one hour.
Serves 4, 315 calories per serving.

title: sinfully delicious
directions: Mix the flour, margarine and nuts.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350°.
Cool completely.

title: baked onion dip
directions: Mix and place in baking dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20-30 minutes.
(Or until warm and bubbly) Serve with Wheat Thins.
Use sweet onions like Vidalia or Texas sweet.

title: monkey bread
directions: Thaw rolls out of package for 10 minutes.
Quarter each roll. Melt margarine and mix with pudding, cinnamon and sugar.
Dip each roll in mixture.
Place in Bundt pan alternating with nuts.
Let rise on counter overnight.
Bake in a 375° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix juices with flour and sugar.
Add eggs; mix and heat slowly.
Cook on low heat until thick.
Let cool.
Add 1/2 to 1 cup Cool Whip.
Serve with assorted fruits.

title: hearty cornbread
directions: Mix wet ingredients together in a large bowl.
Add dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Spoon into 12 greased muffin tins and bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 400°.
Or bake in a 9 x 9-inch greased pan for 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Mix and set aside.
(Refrigerate until served.)
Good to make ahead; it's better when set 24 hours.
Will keep a week to 10 days. Serves 12.

title: rotel sauce(dip)
directions: Brown sausage; drain and pour into crock-pot.
Add tomatoes and cubed cheese.
Cook on high for about 1/2 hour.
Turn down to low heat and simmer until desired thickness.
Serve warm.

title: dinosaur nests
directions: Place butter in a large microwave-safe bowl.
Cook on High until butter is melted, about 1 minute.
Add marshmallows, cook on High until marshmallows are puffy and melt when stirred, about 45 seconds to 1 minute.
Stir in chocolate chips until melted and smooth.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups of the chow mein noodles.
On baking sheets, drop chocolate mixture in small mounds (about 2 tablespoons each) flattening to make a nest.
Press 3 peanut candies into each nest.
Stick remaining noodles into sides and tops of nest.
Cover and refrigerate until firm, about 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Scald milk with salt, sugar and butter.
Add to potatoes and beat well.
Beat egg yolks; add to potato mixture.
Stir in raisins, nutmeg and nuts.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into mixture.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with marshmallows. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes until set.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, soda and salt; sift.
Add nuts to flour mixture.
Mix well; set aside.
Melt butter in saucepan; remove from heat.
Add sugar.
Blend well, then cool slightly.
Add egg and vanilla.
Blend well into mixture.
Add flour mixture in small amounts, mixing well with each addition.
Mix in butterscotch chips.
Spread dough in greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool in pan; cut into brownies.
Yields 16 brownies.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Combine soups and tomatoes together. In a greased casserole dish, layer the following ingredients in order listed in 1/2 portions: Chicken, onion, combined soups and tomatoes, corn chips and cheese. Repeat the layers with the remaining 1/2 portion. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: biscotti
directions: Cream together butter and sugar. Add eggs 1 at a time. Mix in extract and anise seed. Add dry ingredients and blend well. Add nuts. The dough will be very stiff. Divide dough in half and form each into a thick log the length of a large cookie sheet. Flatten and pat into shape. Bake in preheated 350° oven for approximately 30 minutes, until light golden brown. Cool slightly and slice into 1/2-inch cookies. Return to oven and toast on side if you prefer a crisper biscotti.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Brown onion and paprika in oil.
Add broth, chicken and pimiento.
Bring to a boil.
Add spaghetti.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes. Do not drain.
Add 1 cup cheese and sliced olives.
Mix well. Serve with remaining cheese sprinkled on top.

title: chicken paprika(serves 4 to 5)
directions: Salt chicken parts.
In heavy 1-quart saucepan, fry onion, tomato and paprika.
Heat until light haze forms.
Add chicken and lightly brown.
Add water; cook about 1/2 hour or until chicken is done.
Remove chicken.
In bowl, stir flour into sour cream with wire whisk, then add to mixture.
Simmer 6 to 8 minutes until sauce is thick and smooth.
Return chicken.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve over noodles.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Mix all salad ingredients with raisins and nuts.
Toss with a little lemon juice to coat apples.

title: garbanzo with yogurt
directions: First, brown bread until golden and brown.
Then cut into small pieces.
Beat garlic with salt; put pine nuts with Crisco until golden.
Put meat in pan and fry.
Mix everything with meat except bread.
Put bread in the pan, then mix garlic with yogurt. Place on top of bread.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients first, then add rest of ingredients.
Bake in greased and floured pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: diabetic cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients; bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen soft cookies.
Raisins and nuts may be added.

title: church casserole
directions: Put half of meat in bottom of casserole.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Layer half of sliced onions, carrots and potatoes.
Add the rest of meat and other half of vegetables, ending with potatoes.
Pour soup over top and add 1/2 soup can of milk.
Put in oven at 300°.
Bake for 2 hours.
Can be baked at 350° for 3 hours.
Put in before Sunday School and will be ready after church.

title: a cowboy's supper
directions: Cook ground beef and onion until they are done.
Add corn and tomatoes and simmer about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Grease baking sheet.
Combine sugar, corn syrup and salt in 3-quart casserole.
Stir in peanuts.
Microwave at High (100%) until light brown, 8 to 10 minutes, stirring once or twice.
Stir in margarine, vanilla and soda.
Stir until light and foamy. Quickly spread on baking sheet.
Cool.
Break into pieces.

title: brownies
directions: Cream butter or margarine and sugar together until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and mix well.

title: fast fudge
directions: Heat on low until chocolate melts with milk.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread in pan.

title: chicken 'n dumplings
directions: Put a large hen into a large pan.
Cover with water, salt and cook until tender.

title: pineapple dream cake
directions: Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Bake in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool in pan 25 minutes.

title: latvian christmas cookies(gingerbread)
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and all the spices.
Heat to boiling point.
Remove from heat and add about 2 cups flour; let cool, then add the eggs.
Add the baking powder and baking soda to a cup of flour and add to mixture.
Blend well with wooden spoon.
Put in refrigerator to cool completely.
Knead in more flour as needed until mixture is fairly hard and no longer sticks.
Roll out with rolling pin as thin as possible and use cookie cutters to cut into shapes.
Bake at 450° until done.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Cream all together and shape into ball. Roll in chopped nuts or chopped parsley.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll in small balls (about the size of a grape).
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes until lightly browned.
When cool, roll in powdered sugar.

title: eggplant parmigiana
directions: Step 1:
In a large skillet, containing 2 tablespoons hot olive oil, saute onion, garlic and chuck, stirring occasionally until meat is no longer red (about 5 minutes).
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, oregano, basil, salt, pepper and sugar.
Bring to boil, stirring with wooden spoon.

title: tea cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg.
Add flour and flavoring and mix well.
Make into small balls and push hole in ball.
Put 1/2 tsp. jelly and half a pecan in each hole and press down a little.
Bake in an ungreased pan.

title: pape's dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve over salad.

title: hush puppies
directions: In a medium bowl, combine cornmeal, flour, baking powder and salt; mix well. Add the milk, egg and onion. Stir just until moistened. In a deep-fryer or electric skillet, heat oil to 365°. Drop batter by teaspoonfuls into oil. Fry for 2 to 2 1/2 minutes or until golden brown. Drain on paper towels. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until done.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine apples, celery and walnuts. Blend together mayonnaise, sugar, lemon juice and salt. Whip cream.
Fold into dressing mixture of mayonnaise. Gently stir dressing mixture into apples. Chill.
Garnish with frosted grapes.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix ingredients and beat for 3 minutes, then pour over base. Bake at 350 for 40 minutes.
Cool 1 hour before cutting.

title: youngberry pudding
directions: Put batter in pan and cover with two boxes of berries or canned cherries or any fruit.
If a bland fruit is used, add lemon juice to taste.
Mix sugar (1 cup) and boiling water and pour over fruit.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheesy chicken crescent supper
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine chicken and 2 tablespoons cheese.
Separate dough into 8 triangles.
Place 2 tablespoons chicken mixture on wide end of each triangle.
Roll up, starting at shortest side of triangle and rolling to opposite point.
In a medium saucepan, combine soup, milk and 1/4 cup cheese; heat until cheese melts.
Pour half of soup mixture into ungreased 8 or 9-inch square baking dish.
Arrange filled crescents over hot soup mixture.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes, or until golden brown. Sprinkle with remaining 2 tablespoons cheese.
Return to oven for 5 to 10 minutes, until cheese melts.
Serve with remaining sauce. Serves 4 to 5.

title: easy carrot cake
directions: Sift cake flour, soda, salt and cinnamon together.
Beat sugar, oil and eggs in mixer bowl until smooth.
Add flour mixture; beat well.
Stir in pecans and carrots.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool.
Spread frosting over cooled cake. Yield:
15 servings.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Grease a 13x9 baking dish. Brown hamburger, add taco seasoning. Mix cornbread according to directions. Add mexicorn or whole kernel corn. Pour 1/2 cornbread mixture into pan. Pour browned, seasoned hamburger on top. Pour 1 can cream style corn on top. Add shredded cheese, sprinkle evenly on top. Add remaining cornbread
mixture. Cover the top evenly. Bake at 425 degrees for 20 min. until well browned. Cool 10 min. This is good with Spanish rice.

title: raisin pie
directions: Cook raisins 5 minutes.
Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add to raisins.
Cook until thick, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake between 2 crusts for 30 to 35 minutes at 425°.

title: bean relish
directions: Rinse beans in a
and let stand for about 10 minutes (almost dry).
Combine with remaining ingredients and refrigerate for 3-4 hours.

title: corn flake candy
directions: Boil sugar and syrup long enough for the sugar to melt good. Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and stir until dissolved good, the add corn flakes and stir until mixed well through the cornflakes.
Put by spoonful on buttered plate and let cool.

title: maple butterscotch brownies
directions: In a bowl, combine brown sugar, butter, and maple flavoring. Beat in the eggs, one at a time. Combine flour and baking powder. Add to egg mixture. Stir in walnuts. Pour into greased 9 inch square baking pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until knife comes out clean. Cool.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Put instant pudding and milk in bowl and stir until thick. Add Cool Whip. Butter a 13 x 9-inch dish. Line with whole graham crackers.
Pour pudding on top.
Repeat with crackers and pudding. Have crackers on top.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Divide dressing into 3 portions.
Boil chicken, cool, and remove from bones; break in pieces.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine in 9 x 13 x 2-inch dish.
Sprinkle light coat of Pepperidge Farm dressing over margarine.
Add 1/2 of chicken pieces in a layer. Add can of chicken soup mixed well with 1 can chicken broth; pour over chicken.
Cover with Pepperidge Farm dressing.
Add other 1/2 of chicken.
Add can of cream of celery soup mixed with 1 can chicken broth and pour over chicken.
Cover with Pepperidge Farm dressing.
Put remaining margarine in patties on top dressing. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Mix all ingredients; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bake at 350° for 25 minutes, covered, and then for 15 minutes, uncovered. Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
Brown in a skillet in butter.
Place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Saute onion and celery in drippings until tender.
Add cranberry sauce and barbecue sauce.
Mix well.
Pour over chicken.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, basting every 15 minutes.

title: breakfast fizz
directions: Pour lemonade into blender.
Use lemonade can and add half and half and vodka.
Add other ingredients.

title: pepper steak
directions: Amount of steak, onion, and pepper depends on amount of servings you are making.
Stir fry steak in oil in dutch oven or large electric frying pan.
Remove.
Stir fry onion and pepper. Return steak to peppers and onions.
Mix cornstarch, water, and soy sauce in a cup.
Set aside.
Heat water and bouillon cubes in microwave about 4-5 minutes, until bouillon cubes are dissolved. Add to steak, peppers and onions.
Let simmer.
Just before serving, pour in cornstarch mixture and stir until it thickens. Serve over rice.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar in a bowl.
Heat butter, Coke and cocoa to boiling and pour over flour mixture.
Mix thoroughly. Add eggs, buttermilk, soda and vanilla.
Beat well and add marshmallows.
Batter will be thin with marshmallows floating on top.
Bake in a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Ice while hot.

title: chick n chips casserole
directions: Pour soup into casserole, add milk, chicken, peas and 1 cup potato chips.
Stir
well,	sprinkle
top
with
remaining potato chips.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: zucchini pineapple bread
directions: Beat together first four ingredients.
Add fruits; add rest of ingredients and stir gently until just blended.
Bake in 2 well-greased loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool ten minutes before removing.

title: souper strata salad
directions: In screw-top jar, combine tomato bisque soup, vinegar, oil, sugar, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.

Cover jar and shake well. In a large salad bowl, layer 1/2 lettuce, 1/2 chunk-style ham, 1/2 shredded Mozzarella, 1/2 sliced mushrooms and 1/2 of the croutons. Repeat layers using the remaining 1/2 of ingredients.
Drizzle some soup mixture atop salad and toss.
Put remaining soup mixture in serving bowl and put on table.
Makes 6 servings.

title: christmas spice fragrance
directions: Combine all in a 6-inch square of cheescloth.
Gather corners together to form a bundle.
Tie with string.
Place in a small kettle or pan with water.
Boil to send fragrance of Christmas spice through the house.

title: dale's famous liver and bacon dinner
directions: Cook bacon in skillet.
Remove bacon.
Dice peppers and onion. Fry mushrooms, diced onion and diced peppers in bacon grease. Remove all ingredients and save remaining grease.
Flour liver; season with salt and pepper and fry in bacon grease.
When done, turn to low heat.
Spread bacon, crumbled or whole, on top of liver.
Spread mushrooms, peppers and onion over liver and bacon. Sprinkle generously with grated Mozzarella cheese.
Cover with lid and let cheese melt, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sausage potato dinner
directions: Grease a 10-inch baking dish.
Line bottom with potatoes.
In saucepan, heat soup and water, stirring until smooth.
Stir in cheese; melt.
Add sausage over potatoes.
Pour soup and cheese mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: pesto torta
directions: Layer cream cheese or cream cheese and butter beaten together in mold lined with dap cheese cloth with mixture of basil, oil, nuts and Parmesan.
Unmold.
Serve with crackers.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs. Add flour to sugar.
Mix well into egg mixture. Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie crust. Cook at 300° about 45 minutes or until center of pie doesn't shake.

title: beer beef stew
directions: Roll beef in flour. Brown in oil in Dutch oven. Add onion, garlic and salt. Saute. Add beer, mushrooms, carrots and bay leaf. Cover and simmer slowly 2 to 2 1/2 hours. Add potatoes and peas last 1/2 hour.

title: mexican cheese snacks
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Stir all ingredients together well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: vegetable, pork and beef soup
directions: Cook bacon and hamburger in stew pot. Add water to cover vegetables and meat (green beans, diced potatoes, sliced carrots, whole kernel corn, onions, diced tomatoes).

These are canned, drained vegetables with exception of the tomatoes. Cook until flavors blend together. You want a lot of juice. Serve hot with hot sauce, if desired. Next day more vegetables can be added.

title: cucumber mold
directions: Mix cottage cheese, grated cucumbers, onion, salad dressing, season to taste, salt and red pepper.
Dissolve jello in hot water; cool.
Add to cottage cheese mixture.
This amount fills small mold.
Put layer of jello in cold; let thicken slightly, then lay slices of cucumber overlapping in jello mixture.
Put back in refrigerator until firm.
Pour cottage cheese mixture over cucumber slices; return to refrigerator until firm.

title: peanut butter chiffon pie
directions: Combine gelatin, sugar and salt.
Add
egg yolks and milk. Cook and stir over medium heat until
mixture
comes
to a boil. Remove and add peanut butter; stir until
smooth.
Chill
until thickens
and
is partially set.
Beat egg whites until foamy. Gradually beat in 1/4 cup sugar and beat until stiff
peaks form. Fold in peanut butter mixture; fold in whipped topping.
Put in crust;
chill until firm.

title: greek salad
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
Top with olive oil and balsamic vinegar.
Season to taste with garlic salt and pepper. Yummy!

title: yule logs
directions: Mix well the first 5 ingredients, then chill. Shape into small logs (if mix is too hard, lightly sprinkle with water). Put logs in freezer for 20 minutes. In top of double boiler, melt the chocolate chips, paraffin wax and chocolate squares. Use low heat. Dunk logs in chocolate and place on wax paper, then refrigerate. When hardened, place in cookie container and use layer of wax paper in between.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix 1 cup flour and Crisco with fingers to consistency of coarse cornmeal.
Add 2 tablespoons milk and mix well.
Knead on floured cloth until smooth.
Roll into thin crust.
Bake at 350° until brown about 10 minutes.

title: perfect pancake batter
directions: LESS STIRRING MAKES BETTER BATTER.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients. Cook until clear.
Remove from heat. Add food coloring and stir well.
Add jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Cool slightly and pour over berries that have been placed in cooked pie crust.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs and beat. Sift flour, soda and salt together. Add dry ingredients alternately with milk and mashed bananas. Add nuts. Bake in greased loaf pan 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Carefully blend together all ingredients (will throw
dust if stirred rapidly) and store in gallon jar.
Use 2 tablespoons mix per mug with very hot water to make hot cocoa.
Great for camping and retreats.

title: vanilla pudding with blueberries
directions: Combine milk, yogurt and pudding mix in medium size bowl. Stir.
Combine following package directions.
Pour into serving bowls.
Refrigerate.
Top with blueberries.

title: cinnamon rolls with cake mix
directions: Soften yeast in warm water in mixing bowl.
Add cake mix, 1 cup flour, eggs, oil and salt.
Beat on low speed to blend. Slowly add 5 1/4 cups flour to make a soft, but workable, dough. Knead for 10 minutes on a floured surface.
Place in a greased bowl to rise until double.
Turn out of bowl on floured surface and roll to 1/4-inch thickness.
Spread with melted butter. Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Roll up loosely and cut in 1-inch thick slices and place cut side down in greased baking pan. Let rise until double.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost if desired.

title: "old southern tea room's" famous frosty mint julep
directions: Put 2 sprigs of fresh mint in bottom of a tall, thin glass. Add powdered sugar and a few drops of water.
Use a wooden muddler and bruise the mint with the sugar and water thoroughly.
Pour in 1 jigger of bourbon whiskey.
Pack glass to the brim with finely crushed ice.
Add 1 more jigger whiskey.
Let trickle to bottom of glass.
Put sprig of fresh mint in top of glass.
Serve with 2 straws.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables by directions on package.
Mix vegetables, mushroom and cheese soup.
Put into 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with French fried onions and return to oven for 5 minutes.

title: creamy double decker fudge
directions: Line an 8-inch square pan with foil; set aside.
In a small microwave-safe bowl, place peanut butter chips and 2/3 cup condensed milk.
Microwave at High for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes; stir after 1 minute until chips are melted and mixture is smooth.
Stir in 1/2 teaspoon of vanilla.
Spread evenly into prepared pan.

title: rommegrot
directions: Cook milk, 1 cup flour and salt until thick, stirring constantly.
Cook sweet cream and 1 cup flour until thick, stirring constantly.
Take off butter as it comes on when cooking. Stir the 2 mixtures together.
Use the double boiler to prevent scorching.
Serve warm with sugar and cinnamon mixture.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into buttered casserole and add topping.

title: corn cake casserole
directions: Mix all contents into cake pan.
Bake for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in a glass pie dish, then spread chili on top and cover with cheese.
Top with onions and olives.
Melt in microwave until well melted and serve with nacho chips.

title: pound cake plain
directions: Cream sugar and butter until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix in flour and salt.
Mix well and add flavoring.
Pour into a well-greased and floured tube cake pan.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: no crust coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large mixing bowl.
Pour into a large pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, until brown.

title: strawberry angel food delight
directions: Tear angel food cake into pieces and place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. In medium size bowl, cream the cream cheese and sugar until light and fluffy. Fold in Cool Whip. Mash cake down with your hands and spread the cream cheese mixture over cake. In a bowl, combine strawberries and glaze until strawberries are coated. Spread over cream cheese layer. Chill.

title: fried noodles
directions: Cook Ramen noodles in 1 cup water with the seasoning powder. When noodles are al dente, drain, reserving broth.
Heat a wok and stir-fry the meat, cabbage and onion.
Do not overcook the vegetables.
Add the bean sprouts and stir-fry for 2 minutes before adding the noodles and serving.
Thicken the reserved broth with cornstarch and use a gravy if wet noodles are desired.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Stir dry ingredients together.
Blend in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in warm water; let stand 5 minutes.
Add buttermilk-yeast mixture to flour mixture.
Mix well.
Turn on pastry cloth or board.
Roll or pat to desired thickness.
Cut biscuits.
Dip in melted margarine and place on greased pans.
Bake at 450° for 12 minutes.

title: dressing for potato salad
directions: Cook and use either hot or cold for potato salad.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Grease 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan. Stir together corn syrup and margarine until blended. Add eggs; continue beating until light. Stir together flour, baking powder and salt. Add to syrup mixture alternately with banana. Stir in nuts. Turn into prepared pan. Bake in 375° oven 60 to 65 minutes or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.

title: mixed squash and tomatoes
directions: Saute squashes, onion and garlic in butter, covered, until just tender, about 7 minutes.
Stir in tomato; sprinkle with cheese and basil.
Re-cover and continue cooking a couple of minutes until cheese melts.
Serves 4.

title: chili sauce
directions: Mix in large pot.
Boil until thick.

title: crab puffs
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Blend well.
Spread about 2 tablespoons of cheese mixture on each muffin half.
Place on baking sheets.
Cover and place in freezer.
When you are ready to serve them, take out of freezer and cut into 8 pieces and broil 5 to 7 minutes or until crisp.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Butter an 8 x 8-inch casserole.
Mix sugar and cornstarch. Add to beaten eggs.
Mix in pineapple.
Dot with butter and cinnamon.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: european prune kolacky
directions: Sift flour and baking powder.
Cream butter, cream cheese, milk and sugar.
Add beaten egg yolk.
Add flour mixture.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown the first 4 ingredients all together.
Cook noodles.
Mix the sour cream and cream cheese together well, then add raw onions and noodles and mix.
In a large casserole, place 1/2 of the beef mixture, then all of the noodle mixture and 1/2 of the grated cheese, then add the rest of the beef mix and remaining cheese. Bake 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: spirited pecan pie bars
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 9-inch baking pan in oven while preheated to 350°.
Remove from oven; stir in graham cracker crumbs.
Press onto bottom of pan.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes or until deep golden brown.
Beat egg lightly in medium bowl; stir in sweetened condensed milk and maple flavoring.
Stir in pecans and coconut. Pour pecan filling over hot crust; spread evenly.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until center is set.
Cool completely in pan or on wire rack.
Cut into 2 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch bars.
Makes about 1 1/2 dozen bars.

title: low calorie salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients; shake well.
Keep in refrigerator. Good on salad greens, sliced tomatoes or cucumbers.
Has 60 calories per teaspoon.

title: boiled stuff
directions: Fill pot up with water; add salt.
Turn stove burner on high. Place pot of water on burner. When water starts to move about pan very
fast,
you
have completed the recipe.
It is called "Boiling
Water." Can be used with:
any frozen vegetable, raw spaghetti
or
macaroni,
raw
eggs;
just
use your imagination. Place
any
ingredient into "Boiling Water," but be sure to remove contents from pan before water is gone.
If water should disappear from pan, you have created a different recipe which
I cook
often.
It is called "Burnt Something." May also be used when birthing babies.

title: bistro burgundy stew
directions: Coat beef with flour; set aside.
Cook bacon over medium heat until just done; pour off excess fat.
Add beef and garlic; cook until browned.
Add carrots, wine and mustard; cover.
Simmer 30 minutes or until carrots are tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in mushrooms and scallions.
Cook 10 minutes more, stirring occasionally.
Makes 6 servings.

title: three bean salad
directions: Combine sugar, salad oil, salt, pepper and vinegar.
Pour over vegetables and refrigerate 12 to 24 hours before serving.

title: pineapple-date bread
directions: Combine sugar, egg, margarine and flavoring and beat until smooth.
Add dry ingredients alternating with pineapple and blend with a whisk.
Fold in dates.
Add juice to water and use 1/4 cup of liquid.
Blend well.
Pour into well-greased loaf pans.
Bake at 375° for 55 minutes.
This makes 2 (7 1/4 x 3 1/2-inch size) loaves.

title: hot dogs
directions: Put hamburger paties on a grill.
When there dun, heat hamburger buns.
Put everything you want on buns.
Put it together and you have your hamburger.

title: aunt beula's rolls
directions: In 1/4 cup water, dissolve 2 packages yeast (sprinkle little sugar on to activate). Beat in 1 egg and add to yeast and 3 1/2 to 4 cups flour. Mix and grease dough and bowl. Let raise. Shape into cloverleaf or other shape. Let raise. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: fluffy horseradish
directions: Whip cream to soft peaks, gradually adding sugar, dry mustard and salt.
Fold in horseradish.
Makes about 2 cups.
Best with beef.
Very good.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain grease.
Mix all ingredients together.
Fry bacon and crumble, adding to ingredients.
Pour bacon grease over beans for seasoning.
Simmer for 30 minutes and serve.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown beef and salt to taste.
Mix sauce and tomato juice and heat.
In skillet, warm 3 tablespoons oil, placing 2 to 3 tortillas at a time, and turn enough to get limp.
Place in casserole dish and add meat and other ingredients.
Fold over and pour remaining sauce over them; top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon mousse
directions: Pour milk into bowl.
Put in freezer.
Let chill until ice crystals form around edge.
Beat with mixer on high speed until fluffy.
Add sugar gradually while beating.
Then add lemon juice. Finish mixing, then pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan lined with a good layer of graham cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle a few crumbs on top for decoration.
Freeze overnight.
Keep in freezer like ice cream.

title: festive cookie dough
directions: In medium mixing bowl stir together flour and baking powder. Set aside.
In large mixing bowl beat butter or margarine and cream cheese with an electric mixer on medium speed.
Add sugar; beat until fluffy.
Add egg, vanilla and almond flavoring; beat well.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Add 1 1/2 cups mini chocolate chips.
Chill in refrigerator for a few hours.
Make into small balls or crescents.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Dip ends into melted chocolate and decorate with chopped nuts, coconut or sprinkles.

title: greek stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken breast.
Cut each breast to make a pocket.
Fill pockets with cheese mixture.
Tie securely or skewer shut.
Bake in a casserole dish at 325° for 35 minutes covered.
Serve with couscous or rice.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain. Mix with rest of ingredients and simmer for about 1 hour. Serve with tortilla chips or can be served over rice.

title: corn and green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans.
Thaw corn and mix.
Saute onions and green pepper in the 2 tablespoons margarine until tender.
Combine this with corn, beans, cheese, soup, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Stir well and spoon into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Combine cracker crumbs and 1 tablespoon melted margarine.
Stir well and sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Cover to bake until the last few minutes of cooking time.
In order to brown top, uncover.
This serves 6 to 8 people.

title: waldorf red cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Make a paste of food coloring and cocoa; add to creamed mixture.
Add buttermilk and salt, alternating with flour.
Add vanilla, soda and vinegar and add to batter.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into three 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift flour, then sift again with dry ingredients. Dissolve yeast in warm water. Mix shortening with flour mixture. Add yeast and buttermilk. Knead real good. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: marshmallow treats
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and cook, stirring constantly, until marshmallows melt and mixture is very syrupy.
Remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies.
Stir until coated.
Using buttered spatula or waxed paper, press mixture evenly and firmly in buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: cauliflower and cheese
directions: Cook cauliflower in boiling water about 20 minutes until tender.
Drain.
Place in buttered baking dish.
Cover with sauce made of milk and cheese, cooked until smooth in top of double boiler.
Add butter.
Pour over hot cauliflower.

title: california bundt cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in mixing bowl; stir until blended.
Add bananas, oil, vanilla, eggs and pineapple.
Stir until well blended.
Place in greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for about 1 hour.
Leave in pan until completely cool.

title: chicken breasts in cooking sherry
directions: Arrange chicken in shallow baking dish; do not overlap.
Cover with mushrooms.
Combine undiluted soup with sherry and sour cream which have been blended.
Pour over chicken, completely covering. Sprinkle with paprika and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: french salad dressing
directions: In blender, combine mustard and vinegar.
Add garlic and a little oil; blend thoroughly.
Add oregano; blend.
With blender running, add the oil slowly and only as much as it will absorb. Add the fresh parsley as you use it.
Do not refrigerate.

title: fettuccine with veggies and ham
directions: Cook fettuccine according to package directions, omitting salt; drain.
Place in a large bowl and keep warm.
Bring water to a boil.
Add veggies; cook, uncovered, until veggies are crisp-tender, about 3 minutes.
Drain; set aside and keep warm.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix beef, bread crumbs, onion, milk, egg and next four ingredients.
Gently shape into 1-inch balls.
Brown meatballs in 400° oven.
Heat chili sauce and jelly in skillet, stirring constantly, until jelly is melted.
Add meatballs and stir until thoroughly coated.
Simmer uncovered for 30 minutes.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Combine beans and chilies; spread on a large plate.
Combine sour cream and taco mix; spread over beans.
Mash avocados, salt and lemon juice; spread over cream mixture.
Cover and chill several hours.
Just before serving, garnish with cheese, tomatoes, onions and olives.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: philly ham dip
directions: Mix together until well blended.
Serve with chips and/or veggies.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix marshmallow cream, vanilla and cream cheese.
Chill.
Dip fresh strawberries into dip and enjoy.
May also use apple slices.

title: fried chicken
directions: Cut chicken into pieces.
Cut each breast half into halves. Mix flour, salt, paprika and pepper.
Coat chicken with flour mixture.
Heat oil (1/4-inch) in 12-inch skillet.
Cook chicken in oil over medium heat until light brown, 15 to 20 minutes.
Reduce heat.
Cover tightly and simmer, turning once or twice until thickest pieces are done, 30 to 40 minutes.
If skillet canned be covered tightly, add 1 to 2 tablespoons water.
Remove cover during last 5 minutes of cooking to crisp chicken.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes; cut into 1-inch slices. Combine oleo, sugar and water in electric skillet. Add sweet potatoes.
Cover and simmer at 250° for 1 hour, turning frequently.
Yields 4 servings.

title: penna. dutch potato filling
directions: Cook potatoes and mash them.
Dice bread.
In 1/2 butter, fry onions, celery and parsley.
When finished frying, add milk.
Add mashed potatoes, sugar, salt and pepper.
Add eggs.
Beat together all ingredients.
Mixture should be a bit runny; if not, add more milk.
Put in casserole (2 large and 1 small).
Store until ready to use.
When ready to use, brown in 350° oven for 30 to 60 minutes.
Before browning, crisscross top of casserole with fork and top with pats of butter.

title: bourbon street bars
directions: Beat together butter and sugar until creamy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in bourbon and melted chocolate.
In another bowl, combine all dry ingredients.
Stir the dry mixture into the butter mixture.
Combine evenly.
Pour into a buttered 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar and top with pecan halves.

title: old time jerky
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add to meat.
Marinate at least 12 hours. Bake 6 to 8 hours in oven at 150°.
(Can use smoker with alder wood or mesquite, 2 pans.)

title: veggie bars
directions: Unroll crescent rolls, spread and pat into a single piece on a large greased cookie sheet.
Bake 350° for 7-9 minutes until brown.
Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise and salad dressing mix and beat until smooth.
Spread on cooled crust.
Sprinkle on vegetables, then the shredded cheese.
Press down lightly.
Chill overnight and cut into squares.
tags: Hidden Valley salad dressing dry mix

title: arkadelphia pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops; peel and grate potatoes.
Layer potatoes, onions and cheese in a baking dish or Dutch oven.
Mix soup, made with milk; pour over all.
Arrange pork chops on top, cover and bake at 350° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: macaroni bake
directions: Combine ingredients in casserole.
Add 3 cups boiling water and Mrs. Dash seasoning to taste.
Stir well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour; stir in 1/2 hour.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Drain cherries on paper towels several hours or overnight. In a small mixing bowl, combine margarine and corn syrup.
Stir in powdered sugar.
Knead until mixture is smooth.
(Chill mixture if it is too soft to handle.)
Shape about 1/2 teaspoon of powdered sugar mixture around each cherry.
Place cherries on waxed paper-lined baking sheet; chill.

title: sour cream layer cake(from southern living)
directions: Combine sour cream and milk; set aside.
Cream butter. Gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream mixture, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix after each addition.
Add vanilla extract. Pour batter into two greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes; remove and cool completely on wire racks.
Frost as desired.
Yields one 2 layer cake.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix oil and sugar together.
Add remaining ingredients; pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: chicken with rice
directions: Boil chicken.
Bone and reserve broth.
Add all the ingredients to chicken and place in an 8 x 12-inch baking pan and cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream the eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and baking powder.
Then add to cream mixture.
Add zucchini and optional items.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, Worcestershire sauce,
crab, milk and onions in a bowl.
Place dip in a baking dish; sprinkle with toasted almonds.
Bake at 350° until hot.
Serve with crackers.

title: spaghetti bravissaimo
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add sauce, paste, onion soup mix, parsley, oregano and sweet basil.
