Boil spaghetti in 2 quarts water.
Drain and rinse.
Eat it up.

title: grostali
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, butter, vanilla, rum and lemon or orange.
Add 2 cups flour and baking powder and mix well, adding more flour until ingredients hold together.
Roll out to very thin layer.
Cut into 1-inch wide strips.
Knot lightly and fry in deep hot fat.
Drain on paper toweling.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar. Cool.

title: easy apple cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 8 in. square casserole dish.
Stir in milk, sugar, and flour.
Add cinnamon to taste, stir well.
In separate bowl mix cinnamon with applesauce or pie filling.
Pour in casserole dish with previous ingredients.
DO NOT STIR.
Bake at 350 degrees for approximately 30 min. or until done.

title: cranberry cloud
directions: Chop cranberries, coarsely, in food processor.
Combine cranberries, sugar and marshmallows in large bowl; stir gently. Cover and chill 1 1/2 hours at least.
Add apples, grapes and walnuts.
Stir gently.
Fold in whipped cream; cover and chill at least 1 hour.
Serve on lettuce leaves, if desired.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: apple chip cake
directions: Cream the sugars and oil. Add eggs and beat.
Mix in flour, salt, soda and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Stir in the apples and nuts. Sprinkle a mixture of the 1/2 cup sugar and some cinnamon on top. Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: gazpacho
directions: Blend first 6 ingredients in blender.
Add these to last 4 ingredients and chill.
Serve very cold.

title: celery salad
directions: Drain pineapple and heat juice to dissolve Jell-O.
Mash up cream cheese and place in Jell-O.
Add other ingredients except Cool Whip.
Fold it in last, then chill.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix soup, vegetables, chicken and milk.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Let cool 15 minutes before cutting.

title: squiggles
directions: Cook ground beef and onion; drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for about 20 minutes.
Add cooked spiral macaroni.
Serve with Parmesan cheese sprinkled on top.
Serves 6.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Mix all together and beat at medium speed for 2 minutes. Add 1/2 cup flaked coconut and 1/2 cup chopped walnuts. Bake at 350° in a greased and floured 9 X 13 pan for 30-35 minutes.

title: spinach salad
directions: Place into salad bowl in order.

title: orange delight
directions: Mix the first 2 ingredients.
Fold in remaining ingredients. Chill.
Garnish with mint or other sliced fruit.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream the Crisco, brown sugar, eggs, sugar and vanilla until fluffy. Stir in flour, soda, salt and baking powder.
Add rolled oats, chocolate chips and nuts. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes. Makes 9 dozen.

title: peach punch
directions: In large punch bowl, mix Hi-C peach drink and ginger ale. Add ice cream last or just before serving.
Add more ginger ale as needed.

title: wassail bowl
directions: Mix ingredients in a 30 cup percolator.
Simmer 10 minutes. Remove cinnamon and cloves.
Serve hot.
Serves 30 persons, one cup each.

title: "so good" casserole
directions: Prepare shells according to package; drain.
Brown meat and onion in skillet; add salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Simmer until cooked; drain.
In a 9 x 13-inch casserole pan, arrange alternating layers of shells, meat and corn.
Heat soup in skillet to get all the "meat brown" using enough water to rinse out soup can.
Pour over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: poor man's lobster
directions: In a deep cooking container, boil last three ingredients.
Add frozen haddock.
Let cook about 10 minutes.
Turn over.
When prong of fork goes through and fish flakes, it is done.
Serve with individual dishes of melted butter for dipping.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: country pie
directions: Combine ingredients and put into bottom and sides of pie plate.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy; add sugar and oil.
Beat again.
Sift salt, soda and flour.
Add to egg mixture.
Add vanilla and zucchini; beat well.
Pour into 2 greased bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: christmas applesauce cake
directions: Combine applesauce, soda and oleo.
Heat and let cool.
Mix sugar, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg and flour.
Combine with applesauce mixture, then add preserves and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes in well-greased and floured tube pan.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Saute beef and onion.
Drain.
Add soups, milk and enchilada sauce.
Cube cheese into squares and mix in.

title: cobbler
directions: Melt 1 stick of butter in a 2-quart baking dish.
Mix well all other ingredients except fruit.
Pour batter over melted butter. Add hot fruit and bake until golden brown.

title: ooey gooey cake
directions: Mix cake mix, egg and butter.
Pat into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese, 10x sugar, eggs and vanilla. Pour over top of first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cut into squares.
(Variations to this recipe:
Add 1/4 cup chocolate chips to the topping mixture.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar while hot.)

title: apple cake
directions: Use fresh apples. Taste and texture is better. This is an excellent coffeecake for Sunday breakfast.

title: chocolate chip kisses
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Gently add nuts and chocolate chips to the egg whites.
Drop the batter onto a waxed paper covered cookie sheet to form a teardrop. Bake for 20 to 30 minutes until the kisses are hard, but still white.
Makes 36.

title: pickle beans
directions: Put beans in pint jars with garlic, dill and pepper.
Mix vinegar, water and salt.
Bring to boil.
Pour over beans and seal.

title: sauerkraut and pork chops
directions: Brown chops in skillet.
Mix sauerkraut with meat juices in skillet.
Layer 1/2 sauerkraut and apples in casserole.
Arrange the pork chops over the top.
Layer remaining sauerkraut and apples.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: lemon chiffon pie
directions: Soften gelatin in water for 5 minutes.
Beat egg yolks; add 1/2 cup sugar, lemon juice and orange juice.
Cook over boiling water until custard consistency.
Add softened gelatin; stir thoroughly.
Cool.

title: corn bread sticks
directions: Beat egg, sugar and liquid shortening together.
Sift flour and corn meal with salt and baking powder.
Then gradually add to the egg mixture alternately with the buttermilk.
Pour into greased, hot iron corn stick pans and bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Makes 12 sticks.

title: night before french toast casserole
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Arrange the bread in the pan. Beat together the eggs, milk, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Pour over the bread evenly. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: louisiana punch
directions: Pour pineapple and canned juice into square pan or ice cube trays.
Freeze.
Chill remaining ingredients.
In a large bowl, combine frozen pineapple chunks, fruit juices and ginger ale.
Cut strawberries in half; add to punch, along with mint sprigs.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: oven fries
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Cut potatoes into 1/2-inch thick slices (cover with water if cut ahead of time).
Toss with oil and seasonings.
Spread out on baking sheet.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes, turning occasionally.
Yields 4 servings.

title: pone cornbread
directions: Pour boiling water over ingredients and mix well.
Form into pones about 3-inches long and 1 1/2-inches wide.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Put a little grease on top of each pone.
Bake until brown in oven about 450° for 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 8 pones.

title: fresh fruit salad
directions: Arrange fruit and greens in a salad bowl. To serve, add mayonnaise and toss well. Serves 6.

title: supper popover
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Cook and stir ground beef in a 10-inch skillet until brown; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, green pepper, 2 tablespoons flour, 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling. Cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Pour into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle cheese on top.

title: peanut butter crisscrosses
directions: Cream shortening, sugars and vanilla.
Add eggs, beat thoroughly.
Stir in peanut butter.
Sift dry ingredients and stir into creamed mixture.

title: daddy's spoon biscuits
directions: Sift
flour and salt together.	Cut shortening in flour with 2
knives.	Add
milk
and mix quickly with large spoon. Drop mixture from a large spoon into greased muffin pan or on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° about 12 minutes.

title: pumpkin rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Use 11 x 16 cookie sheet lined with waxed paper-spread batter over waxed paper.
Mix dry mixture and batter together.

Spread evenly in pan, bake 15 to 18 minutes. Use two sheets white paper towels placed on cloth towel-dump on towel peel off waxed paper, cut in half where paper towel ends-start from the center and roll up with paper towel-let cool. Unroll-rolls taking off paper spread on filling reroll and wrap in foil and freeze.
When ready to eat cut in 1/2 inch and refrigerate until time to serve.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Saute together the onions, celery, green pepper and mushrooms. Brown meat; add sauteed vegetables, tomato sauce and tomatoes. Season with salt, fresh ground pepper, garlic powder and chili powder to taste.
Cook slowly for 3 hours.
Add water if needed. Freezes well.

title: ms. jacqui's chicken
directions: Place potatoes in a small mixing bowl; sprinkle with seasoned salt and pepper.
Pour oil over top and coat well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Drain half of the juice off of peas and pour over potatoes.
Coat chicken with salt and pepper as desired, then roll in bread crumbs.
Place over top of peas.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for an hour.
May want to cover for half of the cooking time.

title: ham and cheese fondue casserole
directions: In a large bowl, mix bread, ham and cheese cubes.
Place 1/3 of mixture in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix flour and mustard in a cup.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon over bread mixture.
Drizzle with 1 tablespoon melted butter.
Repeat with remaining bread mixture, flour mixture and butter to make 2 more layers.
Beat eggs and milk until foamy.
Pour over layers in baking dish.
Cover.
Chill 4 hours or overnight.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 350° until golden and puffed.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Beat cream cheese, Cheddar cheese, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper on medium speed, scraping bowl constantly until fluffy.
Press mixture in small, deep bowl.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Loosen edge of cheese ball with spatula; unmold on serving plate.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: impossible pumpkin pie #1
directions: Mix the ingredients in a blender and pour into a pie pan sprayed with nonstick spray. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: soyo chicken
directions: Brown chicken in 2 tablespoons oil.
Add sugar, soy sauce and water.
Let cook on low 1 1/2 hours or until soy sauce has soaked into chicken.
Serve with yellow rice.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown hamburger, bacon and onion.
Cook until tender and drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: utah's best oatmeal chip cookies
directions: Cream the brown sugar, sugar and butter. Add the eggs.
Mix in the salt, baking powder, baking soda, vanilla, flour and oatmeal. Add the Hershey bar, nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and sprinkle salt on it.
Let sit for 1 hour. Grate carrot, pepper and onion.
Boil vinegar, water, sugar and seeds for one minute.
Let cool; mix onion, carrots and pepper with cabbage.
Pour cool liquid over cabbage mixture.
Mix it and freeze.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels and butter in top of double boiler. Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar; cool 5 minutes.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add eggs and vanilla to sugar, butter and butterscotch morsels.
Blend in dry ingredients and walnuts.
Turn into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: butter flavor cake
directions: Mix all but last 3 ingredients for 8 minutes.
Pour 1/2 batter in pan.
In separate bowl mix last three ingredients.
Mix and sprinkle half of mixture on batter.
Add the rest of the batter and sprinkle the rest of the dry mixture on batter.
Bake for 45 minutes at 300°.

title: shanghai casserole
directions: Brown
meat
in hot oil.
Add onion, garlic and celery; cook until
tender.
Stir in soup, thawed vegetable, rice and seasoning.	Turn
into
greased
2 1/2 quart casserole.
Cover and bake in moderate oven at 350° for 25 minutes.
Uncover and sprinkle with chow mein noodles;
return
to
oven for about 5 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: easy spiced peaches
directions: Add the sugar, vinegar, cinnamon, cloves and the juice from the peaches.
Bring to a boil; simmer for 20 minutes.
Pour over peaches.
Cool.
Chill before serving.
Will last for weeks in the refrigerator.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add flavoring.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Stir evenly.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan for 1 1/2 hours at 350° or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: shari's fudge pie
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in microwave.
Mix rest of ingredients with chocolate and butter.
Place batter in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Check after 30 minutes. Makes 1 pie.

title: impossible pie
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Pour into greased and floured 9 1/2-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat together sugar and eggs.
Add oil and vanilla.
Mix well. Sift flour.
Add with spices and mix.
Stir in apples and nuts. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with icing, ice cream or whipped cream.

title: cheese and olive dreams
directions: Place on 6 muffins cut in half, then cut into quarters (48 pieces).
Bake in moderate oven until cheese melts at 350°.

title: short'nin bread
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Combine dry ingredients using pastry blender
or
two knives.
Cut shortening into dry mix. Looks like
coarse meal.
In another bowl beat egg with milk. Pour
into flour mix and stir until well mixed.
Drop 1/3 cup of
dough into mounds on greased baking sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 6 to 8 cakes.

title: taco dip
directions: Cream together with mixer the cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning.
Place in a glass 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with remaining ingredients.
You can vary amounts according to taste. Chill. Serve with chips of choice.
We like Ranch, taco, Doritos or Tostitos chips.
Makes a 13 x 9-inch pan, well over half full. Can easily be doubled.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Mix all this together and shape into a ball; let chill.
Serve with crackers and cocktail sauce.

title: fruit salad
directions: Prepare topping mix.
Fold into cottage cheese.
Sprinkle gelatin over mixture.
Blend.
Fold in fruit cocktail, marshmallows and pecans.
Refrigerate 1 hour before serving. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Let cream cheese soften.
Mix mayonnaise and sugar.
Whip cream.
Add cream, fruit and nuts and freeze.

title: caramel filling
directions: Put 1/2 cup sugar in a dry skillet.
Heat until golden brown. Add water and cook until sugar is melted and forms a thin syrup. Combine with remaining ingredients in a large saucepan.
Boil rapidly to the soft ball stage. Remove from heat.
Place saucepan in a pan of cold water and beat until thick and creamy. Add vanilla. Will frost one 3 layer cake.

title: vegetable strudel
directions: Filling:
Combine the first 5 ingredients; set aside.

title: sausage-squash parmesan
directions: Cook sausage and garlic until meat is brown.
Drain fat.
Set aside.
Cover and cook squash in a little water until tender. Drain and mash.
Combine mashed squash, cheese, milk, parsley, salt, oregano, chili powder and crumbs with the meat.
Fold in eggs.
Place in baking dish and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken breasts in sour cream
directions: This entree is so easy to prepare and makes an impressive dinner to serve guests.
It requires literally no attention once you pop it in the oven and tastes like you worked for hours!

title: hearty bacon potato chowder
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, cook bacon over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Add potatoes and onions.
Continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until potatoes are tender (15 to 20 minutes).
Add remaining ingredients.
Continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until heated through (10 to 12 minutes).
Great for a cold winter night!

title: egg rolls
directions: Saute ingredients together until vegetables are crisp and tender. Stir in meat, saute for 3 to 5 minutes more. Cool and fill wrappers. Deep-fry or pan-fry rolls until crisp and golden. Drain and serve. Rolls may be frozen for future use. They must be defrosted before reheated, either by frying or baking.

title: granola
directions: Mix all ingredients, except oil and honey, in a large bowl. In a small bowl, mix the oil and honey.
Mix dry and moist ingredients together.
Spread in 2 large cookie sheets.
Bake at 250° for about 1 hour; stir once to prevent burning.
Cool.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.
Freezes well.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Combine tomato soup, oil, sugar, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, dry mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour over carrots, onions and peppers.
Let stand for 12 hours.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix shortening, sugars, egg, water and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef. Add onions and cook until clear. Drain. Add next 8 ingredients.
Cover and simmer 1 hour. Cook lasagna noodles according to directions on box. Drain.
Alternate layers of meat, noodles, Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 30 minutes.

title: horseradish cream dip
directions: Mix together.
Let sit 1 hour before serving.

title: cream cheese-pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Combine pineapple, cream cheese and sugar in pan and cook over low heat (stir often) until well mixed.
Add lemon juice and gelatin mix.
Let cool.
Fold in Cool Whip, cherries and pecans.
Chill until firm.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer as follows:
(first layer) shredded lettuce; (second layer) chopped pepper, onion, celery and grated carrot and (third layer) frozen green peas.
Put in a large clear bowl; top with mayonnaise, then sprinkle the sugar.
Finally layer the bacon and cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: rib lifters
directions: Brush meat with Kitchen Bouquet.
Brown well in hot oil. Remove meat from pan.
In same pan, saute garlic, onion and celery for 2 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Return meat to pan.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until meat is fork-tender.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Mix fast and pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
This hardens fast.

title: tarragon tuna salad
directions: Drain and flake tuna.
Add celery and relish.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix well.
Add to tuna.
Mix thoroughly. Serve on crisp lettuce.
Garnish with sliced hard cooked eggs, tomato wedges, or thin slices of avocado.
May also be used as a filling for sandwiches.

title: lemon bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Grate lemon rind over bread cubes in large mixing bowl.
Bring milk and sugar to a boil; add butter and pour over bread cubes; cool.
Add beaten egg yolks and lemon juice to the bread mixture.
Beat egg whites and salt until whites form stiff peaks, then fold into bread mixture.
Egg whites may be omitted if so desired.
Pour into prepared dish and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Place baking dish in a pan of hot water and bake at 350°
for 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients. Put in 9 x 13 casserole. Top with buttered bread crumbs and sliced almonds. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: wiggle
directions: Mix ground beef, chili powder and salt; brown in skillet. Add onion, celery and green pepper.
Saute until onions are transparent.
In a large roasting pan, spread half of the meat mixture and top with a sprinkling of flour.
Top with peas and sprinkle with flour.
Add tomatoes and another layer of flour. Next, spread noodles over mixture and top with grated cheese. Sprinkle bread crumbs over cheese.
Bake 2 hours at 350°.

title: mexican salsa
directions: Chop
peppers
in
food processor.
(Avoid contact with skin or eyes.)
Wash
tomatoes and dip in boiling water for 30 to 60 seconds
or
until skins split.
Dip in cold water, slip off skins and remove cores.
Coarsely chop tomatoes.

title: english pound cake
directions: Add eggs to melted butter, sugar and flour.
Mix well.
Bake 1 hour and 15 to 20 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: pumpkin layer cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended. Add eggs; mix until blended. Stir pumpkin and spices into 1 cup of the batter; pour remaining plain batter into crust. Top with pumpkin batter. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until center is almost set. Cool. Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight. Makes 8 servings.

title: baked green beans
directions: Fry bacon to crisp; drain off grease.
Place on paper towel. Cook onion and bell pepper in pan where bacon was cooked.
Combine beans with bacon and about one tablespoon bacon drippings, catsup, sugar, onion, pepper, relish and mustard.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Do not cover pan.

title: golden cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease 8 or 9-inch pan.
Combine all ingredients in order listed; stir until smooth.
Pour into pan. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 9.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together first 6 ingredients. Combine pumpkin, sugar, milk and eggs in mixing bowl.
Add dry ingredients and butter; mix until well blended.
Stir in nuts. Spread in well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: pumpkin pudding
directions: Whisk all ingredients in a 3-quart microwave-safe casserole until smooth.
Cover with lid or vented plastic wrap and microwave on High for 10 minutes, stirring after 5 minutes.
Reduce power to Medium-high and microwave 10 minutes more, stirring after 5 minutes.
Let stand covered for 20 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: raspberry chicken salad
directions: Toss all ingredients in bowl. Serves 1.

title: linguine a'la anna
directions: Cook linguine as directed and drain.
Melt margarine in saucepan over low heat.
Stir in flour and salt, adding evaporated milk.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Add liquid from mushrooms, water and bouillon cube.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until bubbly and slightly thickened. Add 2 cups sauce and mushrooms to linguine; toss well.
Spoon linguine mixture into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, pressing up the sides to leave a slight hollow in center of dish.
Toss ham in remaining sauce; spread it in center of linguine.
Sprinkle with Romano cheese.
Saute red and green peppers in vegetable oil until soft; cool.
Bake linguine in preheated 400° oven.
Before serving, sprinkle croutons around edge.
Reheat peppers and mount them in center.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cheesecake
directions: Add boiling water to Jell-O and put in freezer; almost let it jell.
While this is setting up, cream sugar and cream cheese together.
Add vanilla and lemon juice.
Mix all real well.
Set this aside.

title: monkey bread
directions: For best results, use mixer.
Cream shortening, sugar and salt. Add boiling water.
Cool until lukewarm.
Add eggs, yeast and flour.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Punch down and knead slightly.
Roll to 1/4 to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut in various shapes.
Dip in melted butter and place in Bundt cake pan.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
(May be refrigerated after punching down.
Can be frozen after it is placed in pan.)

title: salted roasted pecans
directions: Melt oleo and mix in spices.
Use large broiler pan and put one layer of nuts into pan.
Pour liquid over nuts.
Bake at 200° for 2 hours or longer if needed.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Boil cabbage until about done.
Put 1/2 cabbage in bottom of casserole.
Cover with a layer of cheese and rest of cabbage.
Mix milk with cream of celery soup.
Pour on top of cabbage.
Add more cheese.
Melt margarine and mix with crushed crackers.
Put on top of cabbage mix and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: orange sparkle
directions: Slice bananas; cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix pineapple and marshmallows into Jell-O that has been dissolved in boiling water and to which cold water has been added; pour over bananas. (Use enough marshmallows to cover bottom of pan.)
Let set to gel.

title: better than sex cake #2
directions: Combine chocolate chips and walnuts or pecans.
Remove a spoonful of cake mix and toss it with chips and nuts.
In a mixing bowl, combine all ingredients, except the chips, nuts and confectioners sugar.
Mix well.
Fold in chips and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until cake tests done.
Remove from pan and cool on wire rack.
Dust with confectioners sugar to serve.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine the first four ingredients and melt until sugar is thoroughly dissolved.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter. Dissolve and add oats.
Spoon out on wax paper (like drop biscuits) and let cool.

title: sausage dressing
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until crusty.

title: peach frost
directions: Place peaches, corn syrup and ginger root in blender container.
Cover.
Blend on medium speed for 30 seconds or just until smooth.
Add sherbet and ginger ale.
Cover.
Blend on medium speed for 15 seconds or just until smooth.
Pour into two large glasses.
Top each with ice cream.
Serves 2.

title: salmon ball
directions: Mix well and chill.
Roll in chopped nuts and/or parsley.

title: dill dip
directions: Very good with veggies.

title: easy egg salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Spread between bread slices.

title: turkey mushroom chowder
directions: Saute mushrooms, onion, carrot and celery in butter in saucepan.
Stir in flour, bouillon cubes, tarragon, pepper, water and turkey.
Cover and cook 10 minutes.
Stir in evaporated milk. Heat to serving temperature.
Makes about 5 cups.

title: pepperoni spread(appetizer)
directions: Grind pepperoni stick with 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese.
Add enough mayonnaise to hold mixture together.
Stir ingredients together well.
Spread on Ritz crackers.
Garnish with sliced olive rings or pimento.
Yield:
2 dozen.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cornmeal thoroughly.
Cream butter and gradually add sugar mixture.
Add beaten eggs to which milk and vanilla have been added.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° (preheated) for 15 minutes, then lower to 350° and continue baking until firm, 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool thoroughly at room temperature.

title: multi-grains waffles
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender.
Blend 1/2 the ingredients at a time as they will not all fit in the blender at the same time.
Add more water if batter is too thick.
Bake in hot waffle iron 8 to 10 minutes to desired crispness.

title: marinade for steak(flank steak suggested)
directions: Let steak marinate for 3 hours at rom temperature, turning occasionally.
Grill or broil, using marinade as a basting sauce.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except apples and nuts.
Stir in nuts and apples.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 75 minutes. Variation:
Add 1/2 cup coconut.

title: lentil soup
directions: In a large pot, rinse the red lentils clean; add water and bring to rapid boil, then simmer gently. When the lentils become tender, add the carrots and leeks; add more water if needed and stock cubes to taste. Continue to simmer until the carrots and leeks are cooked; add seasonings to taste. Add more or less water, depending upon consistency desired.

title: lemon cheese bars
directions: Mix together cake mix, 1 egg and oil until crumbly, reserving 1 cup.
Lightly pat remaining mixture in bottom of ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Beat together cream cheese, sugar, lemon juice and remaining 1 egg until light and smooth; spread over baked layer.
Sprinkle with remaining 1 cup crumb mixture.
Bake 15 minutes longer; let cool.
Cut into bars.

title: cinnamon pecan rolls
directions: Mix ingredients together, placing 1/4 teaspoon on 1/2 of each biscuit.
Fold over and pinch.
Place pinched side down in 9 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Spread excess mixture over top of biscuits. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Let cool for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Line pan with one crust and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients; salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into lined pie pan. Top with remaining crust.
Cut slits into top to vent.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes, until golden brown.
Makes 6 servings. (Tuna can be substituted for chicken; use 12 ounce can.)

title: fried haddock
directions: Heat 1/4-inch of fat until very hot.
Cut haddock in serving pieces. Dip in flour, then in egg and water mixture. Roll in cornflakes.
Put fish in hot oil. Fry 5 minutes, turning once. Drain on paper towel.
Makes 3 or 4 servings.

title: little bit of heaven
directions: Cream together, serve with strawberries.

title: western hash
directions: Brown ground beef; add tomatoes, bell pepper, onion, rice, salt, basil and pepper.
Cover and simmer for 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Top with slices of Velveeta cheese.
Heat until melted.

title: rhubarb dumplings
directions: Sift together 2 cups flour, 1 teaspoon salt and baking powder. Into this work lard, then add milk and mix well.
Roll dough to 1/4-inch.
Spread thick with soft butter, sugar and rhubarb. Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Roll as you would cinnamon rolls and cut into 1 1/2 to 2-inch slices.
Place in pan; pour sweet sauce over and around them.
Bake in moderate oven.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Stir together the first 2 ingredients.
Add the last 3 ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: ginger cookies
directions: In a large bowl, cream the shortening and sugar.
Add the molasses, salt and egg. Blend well.

title: 1 hour rolls
directions: Scald milk and salt, oil and sugar.
Let cool.
Pour over yeast.
Add flour and mix well.
Knead a few times and roll out on flour surface.
Cut out rolls, brush tops with butter.
Let rise 1 hour or longer.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: souse meat
directions: Clean the hog's head by removing snout, eyes, ears, brains and all skin.
Trim off fat.
Cut head in four pieces and soak in salt water (1/2 cup salt to 1 gallon cold water) for 3 hours to draw out blood.
Drain off salt water and wash well in cold water. (Heart, tongue and other meat trimmings may be cooked with head meat.)

title: french toast
directions: Mix well with fork.
Dip bread slices into mixture, both sides. Cook in 2 tablespoons of shortening or oil. Just enough to cover bottom of skillet.
Turn brown, flip to the other side until golden.
Serves 3.

title: cheesy vegetables
directions: Cook broccoli and cauliflower by package directions and drain off water.
Put in buttered baking dish.
Mix soup and milk and pour over vegetables.
Bake for 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over top and bake 10 more minutes.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Sprinkle apples with lemon juice.
Add celery, nuts and raisins.
Fold mayonnaise into apple mixture; chill.
Serve on a lettuce leaf.
Sprinkle with paprika before serving.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Combine eggs, sugar substitute, onion and mustard in container of an electric blender; cover and process until mixture is smooth. With blender running, add Italian dressing in a slow steady stream, processing until blended.
Stir in poppy seed and sesame seed.
Cover and refrigerate until thoroughly chilled.

title: okra pilau
directions: Slice pork, cut
up okra, onion and tomatoes, should be steamed for half
an
hour.
Cook rice in boiling water.
When rice is done, add
to
mixture
of pork, okra, onion and tomatoes. Add seasonings, cook until dry.

title: delicious chicken cutlets
directions: Place chicken breasts on a cutting board.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Pound breasts with a rolling pin until they are about 1/4 inch thick.
Mix eggs and milk in a bowl.
Dip breasts in egg mixture, then coat with bread crumbs.
Cook breasts in frying pan, using cooking oil for 10 to 15 minutes, turning them over halfway through cooking time.

title: small pizzas
directions: Brown and drain meat, then add rest of ingredients.
Put 1 teaspoon on each slice of bread (use Party rye bread).
Cook 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken au gratin
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Spoon into shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: crunchy tossed salad
directions: In a jar with tight-fitting lid, combine oil, sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper. Shake well. Chill for 1 hour. Just before serving, combine the lettuce, bacon, almonds, sesame seeds and onions in a large bowl. Add dressing and toss. Top with chow mein noodles. Yield: 12 servings.

title: coleslaw for freezing
directions: Mix salt with cabbage.
Let stand one hour.
Drain excess moisture.
Add carrot and pepper.

title: chicken taco casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add chilies, tomato juice, Cheddar cheese soup, chili powder and garlic powder.
Add chopped chicken. Break tortillas into about 6 pieces each.
Put a layer of tortillas, layer of chicken mixture and a layer of grated cheese. Repeat until all is used.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes in a 2-quart casserole, covered; then uncover and add more grated cheese and cook until cheese is melted.
Serves about 8.

title: reuben dip
directions: Heat all ingredients in a small saucepan over low heat until hot.
Thin with milk, if necessary.
Serve with chunks of rye bread.
This recipe can be doubled and poured into hollowed out pumpernickel bread loaf and served for crowd (use a little more milk for dipping consistency).
The best rye is dark Cincinnati Rye by Klosterman's.

title: cream cheese-pineapple ball
directions: Mix together all ingredients except nuts.
Set in refrigerator until it hardens.
Form into a ball and roll in chopped nuts to cover.
Makes 2 balls.
Can be frozen.

title: apricot balls
directions: Mix well; roll into small balls and roll in powdered sugar.

title: c-mama's almond brittle
directions: Note:
Place buttered waxed paper on countertop.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into shell.
Bake at 350° until set.

title: banana cream supreme
directions: Coarsely chop graham crackers with a food chopper.
Combine graham crackers, butter and sugar.
Press into the bottom and up sides of a 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: no-fail quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a 9 X 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 50-55 minutes.

title: box cake cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put box cake mix in a large bowl and add eggs and oil.
Mix well until the batter shows no lumps. Using teaspoon, drop batter about 2 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Be sure to let them cool before serving with a cold glass of milk.
To make these cookies extra special, you can add some raisins, nuts, or chocolate chips. Simply delicious!

title: heavenly bits
directions: Cream butter until soft.
Add sugar; blend until creamy.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for approximately 40 minutes.
While hot, roll cookies in confectioners sugar.

title: grillades
directions: Fry steak until brown.
Set aside.
In the same skillet saute onions; add the flour and brown slightly.
Add tomato sauce, water and other seasonings.
Lower heat and add meat.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes.
Serve with rice.
Grits and Grillades is a traditional brunch favorite in New Orleans.

title: cajun casserole
directions: Add all items in baking dish.
Cook, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: black bean chili marsala
directions: Cook onion and garlic in oil in a Dutch oven over medium-high heat, stirring constantly, until tender.
Add chopped roast and next 8 ingredients.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat, simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Add beans, and cook until thoroughly heated.
Serve chili over rice.
Yield: 12 cups.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Chill at least 4 hours. Serve with any kind of fresh fruit.

title: caramel chocolate squares brownies
directions: Mix caramels and Pet milk.
Cook over low heat and stir until melted.
Set aside.

title: cucumber sauce
directions: Brown 1 pound of ground beef, drain well.
Add one drained (15 oz.) can kidney beans, 1/4 tsp salt and a splash of water.
Simmer 10 minutes or until dry.
Chill the meat and bean mixture and add to the cold salad.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: fresh apple bread
directions: In a large bowl, mix oil, sugar, apples, and eggs.
In small bowl, mix flour, salt, and baking soda.
Add flour mixture to apple mixture, and stir well.
Add pecans and vanilla.
Mix well. Bake at 350° for recommended time for your size pan.
Cool and remove from pan. Make glaze while bread is baking, so the glaze can cool.
Makes 4 small loaves (bake for 45 minutes) or 2 large loaves (bake for 45 to 60 minutes).
May also bake in bundt pan for 1 hour.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Add salt and soda to buttermilk.
Add sifted flour and buttermilk mixture alternately to sugar and egg mixture.
Pour into tube pan and bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.
(Tube pan must be greased and floured before preparation.)

title: bailey's irish cream
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Can be stored in refrigerator.
Great on ice cream!

title: spearmint iced tea
directions: Put tea bags in basket of coffeemaker.
Pour water in coffeemaker.
Process as for making coffee.
Pour into tea pitcher.
Add water to make 1/2 gallon.
Stir in sugar.

title: tiramisu
directions: Mix together the coffee and rum substitute.
Grate around 1/4 of the chocolate and cut the rest into small pieces.
Beat the egg yolks with the sugar until the mixture is very pale and forms a ribbon.
Fold in the mascarpone, one tablespoon at a time.
Whisk the egg whites until stiff, then fold them into the mascarpone and egg yolk mixture.
Put a layer of ladyfingers on an oval dish.
Dip a pastry brush into the coffee mixture and soak the ladyfingers with it.
Spread about 4 tablespoons of the mascarpone cheese over the ladyfingers and scatter the pieces of chocolate.
Cover with a layer of ladyfingers, soak with coffee and so on, layering by using all of the ingredients.
End with a layer of mascarpone cheese. Refrigerate for 6 hours.
Sprinkle grated chocolate and coffee beans for garnish.

title: apple torte a la mode(crusty on top, cake-like on the bottom.)
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream together butter and sugar.

Add egg and beat until light and fluffy. Sift together flour, cinnamon, baking powder, soda and salt into mixing bowl and beat. With a rubber spatula or wooden spoon, gently stir apples into batter. Turn into a buttered 9-inch pie pan and spread. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Cut into wedges while warm and serve with ice cream or whipped cream topping.
Makes 6 servings.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Put 2 cups blueberries in unbaked pie crust.
Bake in oven at 400° for 10 minutes.
Turn oven down to 350°.

title: spiced braised beef and onion
directions: Heat olive oil in heavy skillet over moderate heat until smoking.
Pat beef cubes completely dry with paper towels before browning quickly in hot oil.
Brown 3 or 4 batches, turning frequently with slotted spoon and regulating heat so meat browns a deep color without burning.
Transfer beef to a heavy 6-quart casserole.
Add water, tomato paste, vinegar, cumin, cinnamon, salt and pepper to pan drippings in original skillet; bring to a boil.
Meanwhile, scrape brown particles clinging to the bottom and sides of pan.
Pour scrapings over meat.
Bring meat and liquid to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover casserole and simmer 1 1/4 hours.
Peel onions and add to casserole at end of 1 1/4 hours. Cover and cook 30 minutes longer until tender.
Stir in cheese; simmer, uncovered, for 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve directly from casserole.

title: cranberry pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter together.
Sift together flour and baking powder.
Add milk alternately with flour.
Add cranberries. Bake in 9-inch greased pie tin 35 minutes at 350°.
Serve with warm Butter Sauce.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: While pasta is cooking, melt butter in saucepan.
Add freshly cooked pasta; toss gently until pasta is well coated.
Add a mixture of heavy cream and egg yolk.
Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.
Blend well.
Serve immediately.

title: fresh peach party ice cream
directions: Mix 2 to 3 tablespoons molasses into 1 cup white sugar.

title: shrimp toasts
directions: Toast slices of white bread.
Butter it lightly and cut off crusts.
Cut each slice into 4 squares.
Mix together with Mixmaster (electric) the shrimp (drained), shredded Cheddar cheese (1/2 to 1 cup), mayonnaise and dash of lemon juice.
Mix until smooth mixture.
Spread mixture on toast square and mound slightly.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: cranberry almond pancakes(with orange ginger syrup)
directions: Combine the almonds, cranberries, flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Add the egg yolks and milk.
Mix until well blended. Fold in the stiffly-beaten egg whites.
Heat an electric skillet to 375 degrees (or you can use a griddle). Lightly brush the pan with oil. Use 1/3 to 1/2 cup of the batter for each pancake.
Cook until bubbles form on top of the pancakes. Flip the pancakes and continue cooking until other side is lightly browned.
Makes 10 to 12 pancakes. Serve with Orange Ginger Syrup.

title: favorite pancakes
directions: Preheat lightly greased griddle.
In mixing bowl stir together flour and sugar.
Combine egg, milk and oil; add all at once to flour mixture, stirring just until blended and still slightly lumpy.
Pour about 1/4 cup batter onto hot griddle for each standard-size pancake or about 1 tablespoon batter for each dollar-size pancake.
Cook until golden brown, turning once.

title: sour cream
directions: Process lemon juice and cottage cheese in blender until smooth.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend sugar, and cream cheese. Add peanut butter; blend until smooth. Fold in half of whipped topping and top with the remaining whipped topping.

title: barbecue spareribs
directions: Boil spareribs for 1 hour.
Mix remaining ingredients and marinate ribs overnight.
Broil or grill for 20 minutes.
Pour some of the sauce over cooked ribs before serving.

title: swedish rusks
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Beat egg into mixture.
Add buttermilk or sour milk and pinch of salt with soda.
Add flour alternately with nuts.
Bake in slow oven.
Cool about 1 hour. Cut in 3/4 x 4-inch slices and dry thoroughly in slow oven.

title: violet's goulash
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Put in layers in casserole.
Start with cabbage and end with cabbage.
Pour soup over the cabbage and meat.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°, covered.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add garlic salt, tomato sauce, canned tomatoes, salt, pepper, oregano and chili powder and simmer 20 minutes.
Cook noodles completely.
A tablespoon of oil will keep them from sticking together.
Put in casserole dish in layers, noodles, cheese and meat sauce.
End with layer of Mozzarella on top.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate sheath cake
directions: Mix the flour and sugar.
Bring to a boil the water, Crisco, margarine and cocoa.
Pour over dry ingredients.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour into sheath cake pan. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: toasted garlic dilly parmesan rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Cut rolls in half; brush with butter and sprinkle with garlic powder, dillweed and parmesan cheese. Bake approximately 10-12 minutes until golden brown in 425° oven. Good with soup, pasta and steaks.
Makes 12 rolls (6 servings).

title: fiesta flan
directions: Prepare instant pudding as directed, except substitute chilled whipping cream for milk.
Pour in 6 dessert dishes.
Top each with 1 tablespoon caramel ice cream topping.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour mixture in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into balls.
Roll into sugar. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 375°. Top each cookie immediately with chocolate kiss.
Press down firmly until cookie cracks around edges.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour hot water on oatmeal.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add oatmeal, all ingredients; beat well.
Bake in pan for 40 minutes at 300°.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and softened cream cheese. Add Cool Whip and confectioners sugar. Stir together and pour into pie crust. Chill for 2 to 3 hours. Best if made the night before. Stick toothpicks in top and cover with plastic wrap to carry.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix in bowl the eggs, creamed corn, kernel corn and muffin mix. Saute butter, onion and green pepper. Put batter mix in greased 13 x 9 pan. Sprinkle saute mix on top. Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese and Cheddar cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: grandpa's cheese cake
directions: Blend cheese, sugar and egg yolks.
Fold in beaten egg whites. Pour into graham cracker crust.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool 10 minutes.

title: fruit tea punch
directions: Mix all together and serve over ice.

title: snicker cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cake according to package directions.
Pour half of cake batter into a 13 x 9-inch pan, which has been greased on the bottom.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cheeses soften and then blend with all ingredients except nuts.
Form into a ball and roll in the nuts.
Chill overnight. Remove 1/2 hour before serving.

title: chocolate oatmeal cake
directions: Place oatmeal in large mixing bowl. Pour in boiling water and let set at room temperature for 10 minutes. Add brown sugar, granulated sugar and margarine. Stir until margarine is melted. Add eggs. Mix well. In separate bowl, mix together dry ingredients. Add to sugar mixture and stir well. Pour in 1/2 package of chocolate chips. Mix well. Pour mixture into well-greased and floured 9 x 13 baking dish. Sprinkle nuts and remaining chips on top. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: crunchy jumble cookies
directions: Sift together first 3 ingredients; set aside.
Measure margarine and sugar into large mixing bowl.
Beat well until blended and smooth.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients; mix well until combined.
Stir in Rice Krispies cereal and semi-sweet chocolate morsels.
Drop by level measuring tablespoon onto lightly greased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove immediately from baking sheets.

title: southern style oven barbecued chicken
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Place chicken in baking dish.
For barbecue sauce, heat crisco shortening or crisco oil in medium skillet on medium heat.
Add onion and garlic.
Stir fry until soft but not browned.
Remove from heat.
Cool slightly. Stir in ketchup, lemon juice, honey, worcestershire sauce, dry mustard, hot pepper sauce, salt and liquid smoke, if used.
Stir until well blended.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink in center.
6 servings.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: In large container, combine ingredients.
Mix well.
Store in airtight container.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add tomatoes and pinto beans and simmer.
Mix cornbread mix with egg and milk.
Pour meat mixture in baking dish, then pour cornbread mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Refrigerate until ready to use. Serve on crackers or small breads.

title: sesame shrimp and asparagus
directions: Cut asparagus into 2-inch pieces.
Toast sesame seed.
In 12-inch skillet, heat oil over medium heat.
Cook asparagus, onions and shrimp until shrimp are pink and vegetables are tender-crisp.
Stir frequently, about 5 to 8 minutes.
Stir in sesame seed, soy sauce and salt until just mixed.
Serve with steamed rice.
Serves 4.

title: fried fresh peach pies
directions: Combine cornstarch and water in measuring cup and stir until dissolved.
Place sugar and salt in medium saucepan; add water and cornstarch mixture.
Stir over low heat until thick and clear. Add flavoring and peaches and set aside while preparing the pastry.

title: macaroni salad for two
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring lightly.
Cover and chill several hours before serving. May be doubled as needed.

title: green tomato mincemeat
directions: Combine drained tomato pulp and water (same amount as tomato pulp).
Bring to a boil, drain and add.

title: creamy fruit salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot fruit cocktail syrup.
Cool slightly. Fold in remaining ingredients.
Add milk last.
Mix well.
Chill until firm.

title: rice casserole
directions: Bake 1 hour at 350° in greased dish.

title: caramel topping
directions: Mix butter, corn syrup and sugar together; stir and simmer 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add cream.
Return to heat; cook until sugar dissolves, then add vanilla.

title: ham olive log
directions: Mix together and chill. Roll into two rolls.
Roll in 2 tablespoons chopped chives.

title: india relish
directions: Combine tomatoes, celery, onions and salt; let stand 2 hours. Add vinegar, brown sugar, mustard seed, red peppers, cinnamon, allspice and cloves to tomato mixture.
Cook until mixture is thickened.
Carefully fill hot jars, one at a time, leaving 1/4-inch head space.
Wipe jar rim clean, place lid on, and screw band down evenly and firmly.
Place jars in canner; process pint and 1/2-pint jars 15 minutes in boiling water.

title: perfect pie crust
directions: Combine Crisco, flour, sugar and salt.
Stir around or cut into with pastry cutter until crumbly.
Add egg, water and vinegar all at once.
Mix well.
Turn dough out onto floured board. Sprinkle flour on top of dough and pat down. Roll out to desired size.

title: orange julius
directions: Mix in blender.
(Lemon juice is also good.)

title: frozen confetti cheesecake
directions: Combine cookies, walnuts and butter in a bowl.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch dish. Chill. Beat cream cheese, sugar, egg yolks and juice concentrate with mixer in a large bowl until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip. Stir in candies.
Spoon over crust and freeze until firm. Thaw for 15 minutes.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Measure flour, granulated sugar and 2 tablespoons cocoa into a bowl.
Blend in milk and Butter Buds; stir in Grape-Nuts.
Pour into a square pan sprayed with a nonfat cooking spray.
Stir together brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa; sprinkle over batter.
Pour hot water over batter.
Bake 45 minutes.
While hot, cut into squares; invert onto a dessert plate and spoon sauce over each serving.
If desired, top with Dream Whip.
This is a sure-to-please-everyone dessert.
Cake and sauce bake in the same pan.

title: easy chicken fajitas
directions: Marinate chicken breasts overnight in Italian dressing.
Saute peppers and onions in oil until tender.
Remove breasts from dressing.
Place carefully over medium fire in grill.
Cook until done.
Remove from grill and slice into thin strips.

title: burnt creme
directions: Heat cream over low heat until bubbles form around edge of pan.
Beat egg yolks and sugar together until thick.
Gradually beat cream into egg yolks.
Stir in vanilla and pour into 6 (6-ounce) custard cups.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix all ingredients together. Sprinkle sharp cheese on top.
Bake for 30 minutes in an 8 inch by 8 inch or a 9 inch by 9 inch greased baking dish.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Crush crackers.
Pour some of the liquid from asparagus on crackers (will be mushy).
Drain remainder of asparagus.
Add mushroom soup, cheese and almonds.
Mix well. Spread a layer of cracker mixture in Pyrex baking dish; layer the cut asparagus.
Add remainder of cracker mixture.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top.
Put in a 350° oven and heat until bubbly.
Serves 6. So-oo-oo easy, so-oo-oo good!

title: oven swiss steak
directions: Place foil in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan allowing enough to cover and seal tightly.
Cut steak into serving size pieces and arrange in foil.
Add remaining ingredients in order listed.
Mix tomato juice and cornstarch together and pour over top.
Seal foil tightly.
Bake 2 hours at 365°.
Serves 6.

title: banana pudding
directions: Put layer of vanilla wafer crumbs in casserole dish. Top with a layer of bananas. Continue until close to top of dish. In one bowl, beat 2 egg whites until stiff and a pinch of cream of tartar.
Don't stop beating while mixing in cream of tartar.
Add 1/4 cup sugar while beating.
In second pot, mix 2 egg yolks, 3/4 cup sugar and milk. Cook to a slow
boil.
Pour over mixture in bowl.
Pour egg whites and sugar over this.
Bake until lightly brown.

title: herb rolls
directions: Cut rolls in perforation.
Spread oleo and sprinkle with seasoning.
Make 4 stacks.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 11 to 13 minutes.
Yields 8 rolls.

title: sunday chicken casserole
directions: Heat first 3 ingredients to boiling; add the rice.
Pour mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place chicken pieces over top. Sprinkle soup mix over all with Cheddar cheese soup.
Bake at least 2 1/2 hours in 325° oven.
Cover pan with foil.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Heat margarine over low heat until melted.
Blend in flour, onions, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in broth and milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in chicken and frozen vegetables.
Pour into pot pie crust and bake.

title: rice and corn casserole
directions: Prepare rice according to directions. Mix in margarine, Mexicorn, and soup. Pour into casserole dish. Bake covered at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: drizzle cake
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch ungreased cake pan (glass is best).
Drizzle ingredients in the order given.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar, lard (I use Crisco) and eggs together.
Add sour milk and vanilla.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Chill at least 3 hours or longer.
Roll out.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes.

title: the golden spoon's apple crisp
directions: After peeling and slicing apples, sprinkle with the lemon juice to keep them from browning.
(Once sprinkled, they will keep in the refrigerator for a week.)
In a food processor, pulse together sugar, flour, cinnamon, butter and salt.
Spread apples in a baking dish (or individual dishes), and sprinkle topping on it.
Bake at 350° until the apples are fragrant and easily pierced with a fork. Serve warm, topped with whipped cream or ice cream.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: poke cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box; cook in 9 x 13-inch pan.
When cake is done, poke holes with fork in 1/2-inch intervals all over cake.
Mix jello with hot water.
Add cold water.
Spoon over cake. Chill a few hours.
When ready to serve, top with Cool Whip.

title: toll house oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift the flour once before measuring, then sift with salt. Cream the shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Dissolve baking soda in hot water and add to creamed mixture alternately with sifted dry ingredients.
Add nuts, chocolate and oats; mix thoroughly.
Then add vanilla; blend.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 60 to 70 cookies.

title: wonder salad
directions: Drain the pineapple, fruit cocktail and oranges.
Cook butter, vinegar, sugar and eggs carefully over low heat.
Add cream cheese. Mix marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Add fruit.
Garnish with pecans.

title: favorite stuffed peppers
directions: Cut tops off green peppers and remove seeds and membrane. Mix beef with rice, onion, salt, pepper and garlic. Fill peppers with meat mixture. Arrange snugly in 3-quart casserole, with one pepper in the center of the dish. Mix together soup and water. Pour over and around peppers. For the microwave, cover with plastic wrap, leaving a vent. Cook 28 minutes on high. For the oven, cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix eggs, oil and sugar.
Sift together flour, soda and salt. Add to egg mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Fold in cereal. Bake at 400° 15-20 minutes.
Use only amount desired, refrigerate the rest of mixture, will keep for 6-8 weeks.

title: pie crust
directions: Work together flour, Crisco and salt until creamy. Work all together to make in ball. Set in icebox for 15 minutes. Enough for 2 crusts. Roll between wax paper.

title: bread quick rolls
directions: Combine oil, sugar, yeast and warm water in large bowl.
Mix well.
Add 4 cups flour, eggs and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in enough flour to make stiff dough.
Let rise until doubled in bulk. Shape into rolls.
Place in greased baking pan.
Let rise in warm place until doubled in bulk.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield: 2 to 2 1/2 dozen.

title: zucchini squash bread
directions: Mix well first 8 ingredients and fold in flour.
Last add oil and nuts.
Put in a greased pan (9 x 13-inch) or Bundt pan; bake 50 to 55 minutes at 350°.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Combine salad oil and sugar.
Mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add sifted ingredients and mix.
Add carrots, nuts and raisins.
Pour into two 8 x 8 x 2-inch or one 13 x 9-inch well-greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: bakery style cheesecake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, sugar and melted butter in a bowl.
Mix with fork.
Press evenly in a spring form pan.
Place in oven.
Bake 375° for 15 minutes.
Remove and cool.
Pour filling (recipe to follow) into crust.
Place a roasting pan filled with hot water on the bottom rack of the oven.
Bake at 300° for 1-1/2 hours.
Spread topping (recipe to follow) over cheesecake and bake for 7 minutes.
Cool completely and refrigerate.
Cover the top with strawberries or other fruit.

title: brazilian casserole
directions: Combine ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pinwheels
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients. Spread on tortillas. Sprinkle on remaining ingredients; roll up and wrap tightly. Chill 2 hours, then cut rolls into 1 inch slices.

title: baked pasta casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare pasta as package directs.
In large bowl, combine pasta, sausage, pasta sauce and 2 cups cheese. Mix well.

title: mother-in-law's beef stroganoff
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Season steak; cut in strips.
Roll in flour; brown in butter.
Add consomme and garlic; simmer until tender.
Add mushroom soup, mushrooms and sour cream.
Mix well; add noodles.
Put in 3-quart casserole; top with grated cheese and potato chips.
Heat through in 350° oven until browned on top. Makes 10 servings.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: fresh apple muffins
directions: Sift the first 5 ingredients into a mixing bowl.
Stir together oil, eggs, milk and apples until apples are finely chopped.
Pour over dry ingredients.
Stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fill greased muffin pans 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Cream butter.
Beat in 3/4 cup grated cheese and whipping cream.
Cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain pasta and toss with sauce.
Sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese.

title: turtles
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and spoon onto buttered cookie sheet. Refrigerate to set. Dip in melted almond bark and refrigerate.

title: homemade brunswick stew
directions: Boil chicken; drain.
Combine chicken, ground beef and sausage along with chopped onions and 2 cups of broth.
Let simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Add 2 more cups of broth, ketchup, Worcestershire sauce and tomatoes; let simmer for about 20 minutes.
Then add cream-style corn.
Let simmer for another 5 minutes.

title: green rice casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in margarine or butter.
Combine broccoli and cooked rice.
Add to sauteed mixture.
Mix cream of mushroom soup, milk, Cheez Whiz, salt and pepper.
Add to rice mixture.
Season to taste.
Pour into buttered baking dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Microwave for 20 minutes on High.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Mix flour, salt, pepper, paprika, cayenne and onions together. Dip chicken pieces in buttermilk and then into flour mixture. Melt butter in shallow baking pan in a 400° oven.
Place chicken pieces in pan, turning to coat in butter (skin side down in single layer). Bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Turn chicken and bake 30 minutes longer or until tender.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine and shortening.
Add sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Add egg yolks and beat.
Add flour, alternating with buttermilk.
Add vanilla, coconut and nuts.
Fold in egg whites. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes in two greased 8-inch cake pans.
Ice with Italian cream cake icing.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Stir in zucchini. Sift dry ingredients together; add to egg mixture.
Add nuts. Bake in two greased loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.

title: meat balls
directions: Combine hamburger, bread crumbs, eggs and onion soup mix. Make into meatballs.
Mix together sauerkraut, cranberry sauce, brown sugar, chili sauce, and chili sauce bottle of water. Pour over meatballs.
Bake, uncovered at 350 degrees for 2 hours.

title: homemade apple pie filling
directions: In a large saucepan, blend sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Stir in water.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly. Add lemon juice.

title: "blondies"
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan over low heat.
Stir in sugar until smooth.
Remove from heat and cool.
Butter a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Combine flour, powder and salt; set aside.
Beat eggs one at a time into sugar mixture.
Beat in vanilla.
Gradually stir in flour mixture.
Pour into prepared pan and sprinkle pecans over top.
Bake at 325° until blondies come away from sides of pan, 45 to 60 minutes.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and salad dressing with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended.
Stir in broccoli and 1 1/2 c. cheddar cheese.
Spoon into 9 in. pie plate.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.
Top with remaining 1/2 c. cheddar cheese. Bake 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Garnish with blanched broccoli flowerets and red pepper strips.
Serve with bread, crackers, or assorted cut-up vegetables.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix together and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: barbecued pork ribs
directions: Boil pork ribs	until
tender.	Take out of pan and rub good with brown sugar.
Place on outdoor grill.	Brown on both sides. Brush
ribs
with your favorite barbecue sauce and put back on grill and brown.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix water, Karo syrup and sugar in 3-quart pot and heat over high fire; stir once.
Grease 12 pans.
After coming to a high boil, the white foam goes down.
Pour peanuts in and mix.
Stir occasionally, about 3 times.
When starting to turn brown, remove from heat and stir in butter, baking soda and salt (over the pans). Keep stirring and slopping in pans fast.

title: poor man's pie
directions: Prepare pastry for one-crust pie and place in pie plate. Measure apples after chopping.
Sift flour and sugar together. Mix with chopped apples and spread evenly in pastry.
Combine beaten egg and milk.
Pour over apples to fill pie.
A little additional milk may be needed to fill plate.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes or until custard sets.
Serve warm or cold.

title: caramel apple salad
directions: Mix and chill overnight the drained pineapple and marshmallows.
Cook pineapple juice from drained pineapple until thick.
Add sugar, egg, flour and vinegar.
Chill.
When ready, add chopped peanuts, Cool Whip and diced apples.
M-M Good.

title: favorite doughnuts
directions: Mix all ingredients together and roll and cut into 1/4 inch thick.
Fry in hot oil until brown.

title: stuffed quahogs
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Steam quahogs.
Put bread pieces in a bowl and soak in clam broth from quahogs until soggy.
Fry onions and chourico; simmer 20 minutes.
Add mixture to bread in a large bowl and mix well.
Add spices.
Mix and put into a 9 x 13-inch roasting pan.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Stuff shells (open) and sprinkle with parsley.
Bake for another 30 minutes.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Mix flour, soda and salt.
Cream shortening and butter. Gradually add sugar and cream well.
Add egg yolk and vanilla and beat until light and fluffy.
Add flour mixture, alternating with sour cream (or buttermilk), stirring until batter is smooth after each addition.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls 3 inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Flatten with granulated sugar, if desired.

title: dirt delight
directions: Put 1/2 of crumbled Oreo cookies in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix ice cream and Cool Whip and pour on top of crumbs.
Take the other half of cookies and press on top of mixture.
Freeze 12 hours and cut into squares.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots. Drain and cool.
Mix other ingredients.
Pour over carrots.
Cover and marinate. Store in refrigerator 24 hours before serving.

title: spinach au gratin
directions: Place spinach in an ovenproof dish, spreading it in a thin layer.
Season with paprika, salt and cayenne.
Cover with grated cheese.
Pour cream over top.
Broil until cheese is melted.

title: fried noodles with cottage cheese
directions: Cook noodles in boiling, salted water following package directions; drain well.
Combine noodles, cottage cheese, salt and sugar.
Mix eggs into mixture.
Melt butter in heavy skillet.
Add noodle mixture, a small amount at a time and fry until brown. Remove and serve.

title: hot layered nacho dip
directions: Combine beans and seasoning mix.
Spread bean mixture in 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Layer remaining ingredients in order listed. Serve with corn chips.
Yield: 8 cups.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Combine sugar, salt, nutmeg and flour.
Toss with rhubarb. Turn into pastry-lined pan.
Stir milk into eggs and pour over rhubarb.
Top with a lattice crust.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake an additional 25 minutes.

title: coffee bars
directions: Mix, grease and flour pan.
Mix together all ingredients.
Top with 1/2 cup nuts and 1/2 cup chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in 17 x 12 x 1-inch high dish.

title: peaches and cream
directions: Beat flour, vanilla pudding and pie mix, egg, butter, milk, peaches and peach juice for 2 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into greased Pyrex dish.
Place peach slices on top of batter.

title: ground beef pie
directions: Brown ground beef, onion, salt and pepper.
Place in bottom of greased, heavy pie pan.
Stoneware or Pyrex is okay. Add cheese.

title: cinnamon whirls
directions: Set oven at 425°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Prepare biscuit mix as directed on package.
Roll out on a lightly floured board in a rectangle, about 8 x 16-inches.
Brush with melted butter or margarine.

title: rolled sugar cookies
directions: In large bowl, combine 1 cup sugar, margarine, milk, vanilla and egg; blend well.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt; mix well. Cover with plastic wrap; refrigerate 1 hour for easier handling. Heat oven to 400°.
On lightly floured surface, roll dough, 1/3 at a time, to 1/8-inch thickness.
Place 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheets; sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 400° for 5 to 9 minutes or until edges are light brown.
Immediately remove from cookie sheets.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: favorite muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients; batter should be lumpy.
Grease muffin tins.
Fill 2/3 full.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: orange drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add baking powder, vanilla, mashed carrots and flour.
Drop by spoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until lightly golden.
Cool and frost with powdered sugar icing made with orange juice instead of milk and top with almonds.

title: rhubarb coffee cake
directions: In mixing bowl cream shortening, sugar and egg.
Combine flour, soda and salt; sift.
Add alternately with sour cream to the creamed mixture.
Fold in rhubarb and spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: barbecue hamburger
directions: Brown hamburger and chopped onion in margarine.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: ranch potato salad
directions: Peel, cube and cook potatoes; let cool.
Place in salad bowl and add celery and onion.
Prepare Ranch dressing mix with mayonnaise and water.
Add to potatoes and toss to coat.
Chill. Serves 4 to 6.

title: tipsy sweet potatoes
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
In saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch. Gradually add water to make a smooth paste. Add butter, bourbon, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sauce is thickened and smooth. Arrange potatoes in pan. Cover with sauce.
Bake in oven for 20 minutes. Serve at once.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Mix together and put in 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool.

title: layered vegetable salad
directions: Place 3 cups of lettuce in bottom of large bowl.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and sugar.
Layer eggs atop lettuce in bowl. Sprinkle with more salt.
Layer in order:
peas, remaining lettuce, bacon and cheese.
Spread mayonnaise over top, sealing to edge of bowl.
Cover and chill for 24 hours.
Garnish with green onions and paprika.
Toss before serving.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: wicked chicken
directions: Spread 2/3 cup dry stuffing in casserole which has been buttered.
Spread partially cooked beans, mushrooms and chicken on top.
Mix soup with milk and pour over all.
Mix 1 1/2 cups dry stuffing mix with 1/4 cup hot water and 2 tablespoons melted butter to moisten.
Spread on top.
Bake, covered, 30 minutes at 400°.

title: chez basic favorite indian curry base
directions: *Or use 2 cups grated domestic Swiss cheese.

title: rhubarb custard
directions: Beat yolks.
Add flour and melted butter.
Beat.
Add sugar and beat.
Stir in milk; mix well.
Stir in beaten egg whites. Arrange rhubarb in bottom of 9-inch unbaked pie crust.
Pour mixture over rhubarb.
Bake at 425°
for 10 minutes.
Reduce to 350° and bake 20 to 25 minutes longer.
Blueberries or cherries may be substituted for the rhubarb.

title: oven barbecue spareribs or country ribs
directions: Cut ribs in serving pieces; brown slowly in skillet. Put in baking dish. Discard fat from skillet; add onions and cook until brown. Add remaining ingredients and pour sauce over ribs. Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, stir together the sugar and syrup. Microwave at High 4 minutes.
Stir in peanuts.
Microwave at High for 3 to 5 minutes, until light brown.
Add butter and vanilla to syrup, blending well.
Microwave on High 1 to 2 minutes more.
Add baking soda; gently stir until light and foamy.
Pour onto buttered cookie sheet.
Let cool, then break into small pieces. Store in airtight container.

title: homemade mustard
directions: Soak mustard and vinegar together.
Add eggs and sugar.
Cook over medium-low heat, stirring constantly with wire whisk.
Cook until boiling and thick (around 15 minutes).
Pour into small jars and refrigerate.
Serve hot or cold.

title: one hour rolls
directions: Combine buttermilk, sugar, oil and salt.
Sift flour and soda into large bowl.
Dissolve yeast in warm water and milk.
Add to flour mixture; mix well.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Roll out and cut into desired shape.
Melt additional butter in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place rolls in pan, turning to butter top of each. Let stand 30 minutes to rise.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cold string bean salad
directions: Drain string beans.
Add bottle of Italian dressing with diced onions.
Chill for at least 1/2 hour, then drain remaining oil. You may garnish with carrot shreds.
Makes pretty summer cold vegetable.

title: bingo nuts and bolts
directions: In large bowl, combine cereals, pretzels, peanuts and M&M's. In saucepan over low heat, combine white chocolate chips and oil; cook, stirring constantly, until melted and smooth. Pour over cereal mixture, tossing to coat. Spread on waxed paper and allow to cool. Break into chunky pieces for serving. Makes 20 cups.

title: orange chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sprinkle chicken with pepper.
Coat with flour.
In a large skillet, heat oil over medium heat.
Add chicken.
Cook over medium heat until brown.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, arrange chicken.
In the skillet, saute onion in the pan drippings until tender.
Spoon onion over chicken.
Spread orange juice over chicken.
Bake for 1 hour.
Serve with rice. Makes 4 servings.

title: broccoli fromage
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Melt margarine; blend in flour and salt, then add milk and cheeses.
Heat just until hot and mixed. Put broccoli in casserole; top with hot sauce, then sprinkle cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: oriental salad
directions: Cook Ramen noodles according to package directions omitting seasoning packet.
Cool in cold water and drain well.
Combine vegetables, noodles and sesame seed in a large bowl.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: taco salad
directions: Tear head of lettuce in large bowl.
Add hot, cooked and drained ground beef, black olives, dressing, onion and cheese. Crush 1/2 bag of chips and add to mixture.
Serve warm along with remainder of chips.

title: herbal green salad dressing(low-fat salad dressing)
directions: Place garlic, chives, seasonings, vinegar and 1 tablespoon olive oil in blender or mixing bowl.
Cover and blend (or mix) at low speed.
Add remaining oil in slow stream, then blend in yogurt and buttermilk thoroughly.
Store in tightly covered jar in refrigerator.
Will keep about a week.
Makes 7 cups.

title: welsh cookies
directions: Cream butter and Crisco.
Add sugar and mix.
Beat eggs and milk together; add to creamed mixture.
Mix dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Stir in currants.
Mixture will be like pie crust.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mash cooked squash. (Drain squash well after cooking until tender.)
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a greased 1-quart casserole and bake at 375° about 40 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: cinnamon muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spoon into greased muffin pans.
Bake at 400° until done (approximately 15 to 20 minutes).

title: corn vegetable medley
directions: Thaw and cook vegetables.
Add rest of ingredients.
Heat and serve.

title: spinach orange salad
directions: Dressing: Combine oil, 2 tablespoons sugar, vinegar, parsley, salt, pepper and Tabasco sauce. Shake well and refrigerate.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in the order given.
Chill thoroughly.
Serve on crisp lettuce leaves.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Mix in other ingredients.
Make into marble sized balls (approximately 70).
Bake for 20 minutes at 350 degrees.
Can be frozen and thawed about 1 hour before serving.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix butter, powdered sugar and flour.
Press in a pizza pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove.
Mix milk, cream cheese and lemon juice.
Pour over crust.
Slice 1 quart strawberries and spread over top.
Spoon glaze over berries.
Top with Cool Whip and chill.

title: banana split pie
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine and mix with graham crackers.
Line bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix eggs, sugar, 2 softened sticks of margarine and vanilla (do not melt margarine).
Beat 5 minutes. Spread over crust.
Slice bananas and put over top.
Drain pineapple and put on top.
Then spread top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours, better overnight.

title: christmas salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add candy to boiling water and dissolve.
Add enough water to make 1 cup.
Add gelatin and other ingredients to the jello and candy mixture.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix margarine, eggs and sour cream together.
Add both cans of corn and cornbread mix.
Bake at 350° in covered 2-quart casserole for 1 hour.
Remove cover and bake for another 30 minutes.

title: marilyn's pork chops
directions: Coat pork chops in mustard and flour and brown.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan; add drippings.
Pour soup over them.
Cover with foil and bake 3 hours at 325°.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine baking soda, boiling water, molasses and flour.
Add beaten egg.
Let stand for 15 minutes. Make crumb mixture with shortening and sugars.
Put half of crumb mixture in unbaked pie shell.
Pour in liquid mixture.
Top with rest of crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: strawberry loaf pound cake
directions: Cut pound cake into slices.
Make a layer in the bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
In large mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in pudding powder, alternately with milk until smooth.
Mix glaze and strawberries in another bowl.
Spoon over cream mixture.
Spread whipped topping over strawberry layer. Garnish with strawberries if desired.
Chill several hours.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water and stir until dissolved.
Add blueberry pie filling and pineapple.
Chill until partially set, then put in an 8-inch square pan and let set.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix well.
Line large pan/dish with wafers.
Alternate with bananas, pudding, wafers.
Top with chopped pecans.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies(heart healthy)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat together Crisco, sugars, egg, water and vanilla until creamy.
Combine flour and soda; add to creamed mixture.
Add raisins and oats; mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
