Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Sift flour with baking powder and salt and set aside.
In a large bowl, with wooden spoon or electric mixer at medium speed, beat butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla until fluffy.
Gradually stir in flour mixture until well blended.
Form into balls.
Wrap in wax paper.
Refrigerate 1 hour or several.

title: tropical chiffon pie
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Slightly beat egg yolks in top of double boiler; stir in bananas, lemon juice and rind, sugar and salt.
Cook over boiling water, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened.
Remove from heat.
Stir softened gelatin into banana mixture until dissolved.
Chill until mixture is slightly thickened.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry.
Beat cream until stiff.
Fold egg whites, cream and coconut into banana mixture.
Pile into 9-inch pie shell.
Chill until firm.
Garnish with additional whipped cream, shaved chocolate and banana slices, if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: spiced oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening with sugar.
Beat eggs and mix with milk. Mix flour well with soda, salt and spices and then with the rolled oats and raisins.
Add liquid and dry ingredients alternately to the creamed shortening and sugar.
Drop on greased pans and bake about 15 minutes in a 375° oven.
Makes 4 dozen large cookies.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: *You can substitute 9 packages Equal sweetener instead of sugar.

title: lo-cal nut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Good source of protein and fruit.
Yields 4 servings.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Prepare cake and pudding according to package directions. Break cake into small pieces.
Lay part of cake in bottom of punch bowl.
Pour half of pudding over cake, then put another layer of cake.
Add rest of pudding, pineapple and pie filling.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts.

title: chicken and ham salad
directions: In large bowl, combine mayonnaise, sour cream, mustard and lemon juice.
Mix in chicken, ham and celery.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: peanut butter and jelly muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in peanut butter until it resembles coarse crumbs.
Add milk and eggs all at once, stirring just until flour is moistened. Place 1 or 2 tablespoons of batter in muffin cups; add 1 teaspoon preserves and top with 1 or 2 more tablespoons batter.
Bake 15 to 17 minutes; makes 15 to 18 muffins for extra good eating!

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine squash, pimiento, onion and cream of chicken soup. Melt butter; add 2/3 cornbread stuffing.
Cover bottom of casserole dish with cornbread stuffing mix and butter; add rest to squash.
Pour into casserole dish and top with dry stuffing. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: italian beef
directions: This recipe is perfect for sandwiches for a party.
It can be kept warm in crock-pot.
Also, good for serving at meal time.

title: cheese krispies
directions: Grate the cheese. Mix all ingredients together. Roll into small balls (marble to ping-pong ball size), flatten slightly with a fork. Bake at 375° for 12-15 minutes. Yields 5-6 dozen.

title: breakfast quiche
directions: Cook sausage; drain.
Remove crust from bread, butter and cut into cubes.
Put buttered bread into bottom of 11 x 14-inch Pyrex dish.
Spread crumbled sausage over bread, then put layer of cheese.
Beat eggs and milk.
Add salt and mustard and pour over mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: mary jane's oyster crackers
directions: Add spices to heated oil.
Pour oyster crackers into Tupperware container (shallow).
Pour oil mixture over crackers. Stir and shake well.
Leave overnight.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter with green peppers.
Mix together all other ingredients and put in casserole.
Preheat oven to 350°. Bake for 40 minutes to 45 minutes.
Put French fried onion rings on top before putting in oven.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Layer bottom and side of large glass bowl with cookies.
Pour 1/2 blueberry filling on top of the cookies.
On top of this, put cut up bananas and pineapple.
Cover with pudding, then Cool Whip. Put the other 1/2 blueberry filling on top.
Chill.

title: scotch shortbread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Gradually add flour until very thick. Pat smooth in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Make holes with fork as for one crust pie.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Hollow out (from the top) the loaf of rye bread.
Fill the loaf with the dip; tear the bread from the loaf into bite-size pieces for dipping.
Or, cut entire loaf into pieces and serve the dip in bowl.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray a 2-quart baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Prepare mashed potatoes according to package directions using water, skim milk and diet margarine and omitting salt.
Set aside.
In 12-inch skillet, over medium heat, heat 1 1/2 teaspoons oil.
Add the mushrooms, onion and garlic.
Cook about 5 minutes, stirring frequently, until vegetables are softened. Transfer vegetables to baking dish and wipe out skillet.
In skillet over medium heat, heat 1 1/2 teaspoons oil.
Add turkey; cook until turkey has lost its raw look, stirring to break up meat. Add turkey to baking dish along with tomato soup, peas, chicken broth and pepper.
Toss thoroughly to mix.
Spoon potatoes over top in even layer.
Bake 30 minutes until lightly browned.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream together sugar and butter; add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition. Sift flour and soda together and mix with the sugar mixture, alternating with the sour cream. Pour into a greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Tear into bite size pieces.

title: banana cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour two 9-inch layer cake pans.
Cream butter and sugar together until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add 1 cup of mashed bananas, mixing thoroughly.

title: margaret's peanut brittle
directions: Mix soda and salt together; set aside.
Combine sugar, water and syrup; bring to a boil.
Stir in peanuts gradually so as not to lose the boil.
Keep a rolling boil until peanuts pop and turn brown (309° on a candy thermometer).
Add soda and salt; stir well. Pour onto a well-greased cookie sheet.
Put cookie sheet on trivet so air can get under it.
When cold, break into pieces.

title: ham ball
directions: Beat together cream cheese, Miracle Whip, mustard and onion flakes until fluffy, then chop ham into small pieces, reserving 4 to 5 slices.
Add chopped ham to cheese mixture, then make a ball and lay it on top of the sliced ham.
Wrap the ham around the ball and chill.
Serve with gourmet crackers.

title: low-fat turkey casserole
directions: Spray skillet with nonstick spray.
Cook turkey and onions in skillet.
Peel and slice potatoes; put in pan and parboil.
Drain. Take a casserole dish and put potatoes in bottom.
Then put turkey and onions on top of potatoes.
Mix soups together and pour over top of casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cheesy fruit-n-nut spread
directions: Gradually add honey and brandy to cream cheese, mixing until well blended.
Stir in apples and pecans.
Cover; chill.
Serve with apples, pear slices and assorted crackers.

title: fruit fools peach
directions: Peel, halve and pit peaches.
Reserve 1 peach half for garnish.
Cut remaining peaches into chunks.
In blender at medium speed, blend peach chunks and sugar until smooth.
In small bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat heavy or whipping cream and almond extract until stiff peaks form.
With rubber spatula or wire whisk, fold peach puree into whipped mixture.

title: country fried steak
directions: Dredge steaks in flour with salt and pepper.
Brown steaks quickly on both sides in oil.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle on onion soup mix.	Stir together celery soup and water.
Pour over meat.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until meat is tender.	Good served over rice.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Mix with fork, drop by teaspoons on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: rice krispies squares
directions: Melt margarine over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until melted.
Remove from heat.
Add cereal; stir until well coated. Press mixture into a buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Peel, finely chop and drain tomato.
Combine all ingredients; cover tightly and chill.
Serve with crisp tortilla corn chips or raw carrot and celery sticks.
Yields approximately 2 cups.

title: mexicorn casserole
directions: Mix and bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: almond cheese spread
directions: Mix all ingredients well, shape, sprinkle with toasted almonds and serve with crackers.

title: debbie's chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken 30 minutes.
Cool, then remove bones.
Cut into bite size cubes.
Mix soup, chicken and sour cream in a casserole dish.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Melt 1/2 stick butter and mix with cracker crumbs.
Top chicken with crumbs.
Bake for 15 minutes more.

title: pickled beets
directions: Drain juice from three of the cans of beets, but save the juice from the fourth.
Combine the ingredients in a large saucepan. Heat to boiling.
Turn off and add beets.
Place in half-gallon jar and refrigerate for 6 to 8 hours.
Will keep up to 4 weeks.

title: company salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; cool.
When beginning to set, add pineapple, marshmallows and bananas.
Chill in large glass bowl until firm.
Heat pineapple juice in top of double boiler. Combine sugar, flour and egg.
Mix with pineapple juice and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Cool and fold in whipped cream. Spread over gelatin.
Top with grated cheese.
Chill until firm or overnight.

title: working woman's pork chops
directions: Layer pork chops in crock-pot with barbecue sauce. Add 1 cup of Coke. Cook on medium all day.

title: scalloped potatoes and ham
directions: Combine soup, milk and pepper in 1 1/2 quart casserole; arrange in alternate layers of potatoes, meat, onions and sauce. Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Uncover; sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Bake 15 minutes more, until potatoes are tender.

title: white cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and add flour to make a soft dough. Divide dough and place on floured base.
Knead flour into dough to make it ready for rolling. Roll to about 1/8-inch thick. Cut with cookie cutters and bake at 300° until lightly browned on bottom. Stores well.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Stir sour cream or Imo well.
Gradually add orange juice concentrate until desired thickness and taste.
Serve over any combination fresh fruit salad.

title: meringue mint cookies
directions: Combine egg whites, salt and cream of tartar and beat until stiff.
Stir in sugar, chips and coloring.
Drop by teaspoons on foil covered cookie sheet.
Preheat oven to 375° for 15 minutes. Turn off oven and put cookies in immediately.
Leave in oven overnight.
(Do not open door to look).

title: vegetable lasagne
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water for 8 to 10 minutes; drain. Steam spinach, covered.
Reduce heat when steam forms.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes.
Saute mushrooms, carrot and onion in hot oil until tender.
Stir in tomato sauce, tomato paste and oregano.

title: frozen peanut butter mousse squares
directions: In a bowl mix
crumbs,	sugar
and butter.
Reserve 1/2 cup of the crumbs	for the top.
Press remaining crumbs firmly and evenly into a nine-inch
square pan.
In a bowl mix peanut butter and apricot
preserves	until
well blended.
Gradually stir in milk. Fold in whipped topping.
Spread mixture evenly into crumb lined pan.
Sprinkle top with crumbs.
Freeze until hard.
Keep covered if	stored	for
any
length of time.
Cut into squares to	serve. Serve
topped with additional whipped topping
and
a
drizzle of fudge sauce.
Makes one nine-inch pan.

title: butterscotch balls
directions: Mix well the first 6 ingredients. Melt the margarine in shallow pan on low heat. Mix and roll balls. Melt the wax with the butterscotch chips. Dip balls and lay on wax paper.

title: hurry up steak and go
directions: Cut meat into serving size pieces.
Coat with mixture of flour, 1 1/2 teaspoons salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Brown steak in shortening at 325°.
Add water, onion and potatoes.
Season with 1 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper.
Cover; reduce temperature to 215° and cook for 45 minutes or until tender.

title: garden goulash
directions: Mash tomatoes. Add chopped pepper and onion. Dice and add squash, zucchini, seasoning, salt and pepper to taste. Simmer until tender. Add paste. Bring to boil, adding noodles. Cook for 1 minute, then simmer until noodles are tender.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix in boiler the oleo, sugar, flour and cocoa.
Beat egg yolks in milk; add to oleo mixture.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes on medium heat.
This will lump up if you don't stir well.
Add vanilla; mix well.
Pour into pie crust.

title: clothespin cookies
directions: Add sugar to flour.
Cut in 1/4 of Crisco.
Add egg mixture. Beat until smooth.
Refrigerate in bowl for 1 hour.
Every hour roll out dough and spread with 1/4 of the remaining Crisco until gone.
Refrigerate overnight.
Take a small amount to work with and keep the rest in the refrigerator.
Roll about 1/4-inch thick. Cut into 6-inch strips 1-inch wide.
Wind loosely on clothespin overlapping dough.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes until slightly browned.
Cool 2 minutes, then remove from pin.
Be sure to grease clothespins.

title: mama's irish stew
directions: Roll beef chunks in flour and coat well. Melt fat in a large saucepan.
Brown beef slowly and thoroughly.
Add 4 cups water. Cover tightly and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
At the end of 1 hour, if beef cubes are not completely covered, add 1 cup of water.
Add carrots, potatoes and onion to saucepan.
Cover tightly and simmer for 30 minutes until vegetables are tender.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and cocoa in a medium size saucepan.
Add sufficient water to form paste.
Beat in egg yolks well.
Heat remaining water and add with butter and salt.
Cook until thick. Remove from heat and add vanilla. Cool and pour into prepared pie shell (cooked).
Prepare meringue with egg whites.
Place on pie and brown.
Pie should cool before it is cut.

title: banana holiday bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and beat.
Stir in candied fruit, raisins and nuts.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with bananas.
Turn into 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool before slicing.

title: chicken breasts in sour cream
directions: Remove skin from chicken. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Melt 4 teaspoons butter in skillet.
Add chicken; saute until golden brown.
Pour wine over chicken. Cover and steam until tender, 20 to 25 minutes. Remove chicken to serving platter and place in warm oven.
Add the remaining 2 teaspoons butter. Add onion to skillet; saute until soft, then stir in sour cream and olives.
Heat gently but do not boil. Add chives and pour over chicken. Serve with rice or small new potatoes and peas.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash and slice cucumbers and onions.
Place in large container and cover with water to which you have added the salt.
Let stand 1 hour, then drain.
Mix vinegar, sugar, celery seed and turmeric in saucepan and heat.
Add cucumbers and onions, boil 3 minutes and pack into prepared jars and seal.
Let stand for several weeks before opening.

title: good neighbor cake
directions: Put in a bowl and mix all together.
Put in a greased angel food pan.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Cut each chicken breast in half and place on each side 1 or 2 slices dried beef rounds.
Roll up and wrap a slice of bacon around each piece.
Mix sour cream and soup (don't add salt and pepper).
Pour over chicken.
Bake 2 to 2 1/2 hours at 250°.

title: heavenly butter roll
directions: In a large bowl combine all ingredients except the last 1/2 cup butter.
Beat with mixer until smooth and not very thick.
Let rise in warm place until doubled.
Stir down and let rise in warm place until doubled.
Stir down and let rise again.
Turn out on floured board and divide into two parts.
Roll each part into circle 1/2-inch thick.
Brush with the other 1/2 cup melted butter. Cut into 16 wedges from the wide end to the small end. Place on greased cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.
Brush tops with remaining butter and let rise until almost doubled.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes or until light brown.
May be frozen and reheated later.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: layer salad
directions: Place in a large salad bowl in order.
Refrigerate for at least an hour or more.
Toss and serve.

title: peanut butter icing
directions: Stir together in a small mixing bowl all the ingredients. Beat until creamy and of a spreading consistency.

title: 3 day coconut cake
directions: Prepare and bake cake according to package directions using 2 layer cake pans.
Split cooled layers horizontally into 4 layers. Combine sour cream, coconut and sugar in bowl; blend well. Reserve 1 1/2 cups coconut mixture.
Spread remainder between layers.
Fold in Cool Whip into reserved mixture.
Frost top and sides of cake.
Refrigerate 3 days before serving.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Chill dough, then roll into small balls, which will flatten when baked.
(May be frozen uncooked).
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Do not brown.

title: meat-mushroom sauce
directions: In a large kettle or Dutch oven, slowly brown sausage and beef.
Add onions and saute until limp.
Drain.
Add garlic, parsley and mushrooms and stir.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Cover loosely and simmer, stirring occasionally, for 3 hours or until reduced to thick sauce consistency.
Skim off any excess fat.
Makes about 3 quarts of sauce.

title: grandma franks lemon meringue pie
directions: Separate eggs.
Pour lemon juice into egg yolks and blend. Add milk and blend until creamy.
Pour in pie crust.

title: stained glass window cookies
directions: Melt margarine in skillet; remove from heat and add chocolate chips.
Stir until melted.
Cool; add marshmallows and nuts; stir well.
Sprinkle nuts or coconut on waxed paper.
Form into any size roll, working with 1/3 of mixture at a time for easy handling.
Chill until set, then slice.
Keeps indefinitely unsliced in refrigerator or freezer.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Mix it all together and put on your chopped up cabbage.

title: pie crust-1 shell
directions: Mix flour, salt and Crisco together until mixture resembles corn meal.
Add enough water to hold together.
Do not work dough too much as it will make crust tough.
Roll out and add favorite filling.

title: orange glazed chicken
directions: Sprinkle 1 teaspoon salt and pepper on chicken and place in baking dish, skin side up.
Brush on butter and bake, uncovered, at 400° for 45 minutes, basting every 15 minutes with drippings.

title: awesome omelet
directions: You can add shrimp, bacon or almost anything you like to the omelet.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: In microwavable bowl (Saran Wrap top), cook at Full power for 3 minutes.
Stir vigorously.
Cook additional 30 seconds or until marshmallows melt.
Stir again quickly and pour immediately over popcorn (about 3 to 4 batches from hot air popper).
Stir quickly to coat evenly.
Pour coated corn on wax paper and cool.
Caramel corn will be like taffy corn, not crunchy.

title: chocolate crackles
directions: Melt chocolate pieces. Combine with brown sugar and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well. Add vanilla. Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to chocolate mixture.
Stir in nuts. Chill. Preheat oven to 350°. Grease cookie sheets.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into powdered sugar and roll to coat.
Place on greased sheets. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: dream cookies(drommar)
directions: Brown butter slightly; pour in bowl and cool.
Add sugar and stir until fluffy.
Add vanilla, then flour and baking powder, sifted together.
Work dough until smooth.
Roll into small balls.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a well-greased dish.
Sprinkle top with paprika and bake about 20 minutes in hot oven at 400°.

title: cheesecake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In medium bowl, combine first 4 dry ingredients.
Pour in butter or margarine; toss with a fork.
Pat mixture evenly into prepared pan.
Bake for 15 minutes.
In mixer bowl, beat the cream cheese, sugar and lemon peel until smooth.
Add eggs, beating well.
Pour over baked crust.
Bake for 25 minutes; cool 5 minutes.
In bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Spoon over cheesecake, spreading evenly.
Bake for 5 to 7 minutes.
Cool; refrigerate at least 30 minutes.
Cut into bars.

title: raspberry parfait pie(dietetic)
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Add raspberries and lemon juice. Stir until thawed.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Blend together cream cheese, Sweet 'N Low, salt and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spread 1/2 of cheese mixture in pie shell.
Top with 1/2 of raspberry mixture.
Repeat layers.
Chill well.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Place rhubarb in pastry shell. Combine sugar, flour and nutmeg.
Add eggs; beat well.
Pour the egg mixture into pastry shell.
To prevent over browning, cover edge with foil.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Remove foil; bake 20 minutes more or until pie is nearly set (pie appears soft in center, but sets upon cooling).

title: beef stew
directions: Cook stew meat in boiling water, to cover, until tender.
Add V-8 juice, onion, carrots and potatoes. Continue cooking until vegetables are tender.
Do not overcook.
Add salt to taste.

title: chickpea stew
directions: Place onion and carrot in medium pan with oil.
Saute over low heat for 5 to 10 minutes.
Add potatoes, tomatoes (with the juice), basil and pepper; stir to blend.
Cover and simmer gently for about 30 minutes, or until potatoes are soft.
Stir occasionally to make sure potatoes do not stick to pan.
Add the chickpeas; warm through gently.

title: chocolate turtles
directions: Mix butter and sugar; add eggs, cocoa, flour and vanilla. Heat waffle iron.
Drop 1 teaspoon dough on each section.
Close cover and bake 50 seconds.
Lift off with a fork and frost. Yields 2 dozen.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Mix and bake cake mix according to package directions in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool.
Slice in half lengthwise.
Bring milk and flour to boil, stirring constantly.
Cool well.
Cream remaining ingredients and add to milk and flour mixture.
Beat until fluffy. Spread on bottom layer and top with other half of cake.
You can refrigerate 2 days before eating.
You can cut cake into individual pieces, wrap in Saran Wrap and put in freezer.
Good to take out and put in lunch pails.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix all
ingredients
together.
Place	in greased loaf pan, 9 x 5
x
3-inches.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Unmold and slice. You may serve celery soup over slices.

title: eggless chocolate cake
directions: Mix together and sift dry ingredients.
Add sour milk and melted shortening.
Add vanilla; beat and add hot water.
Bake at 350° in 9 x 13-inch pan until done.

title: sausage balls
directions: Crumble and cook sausage; drain.
Mix sausage, cheese, Bisquick and water.
Stir until well mixed.
Form into small balls.
Put on cookie sheet and bake at 425° to 450° for about 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: finger licking good chicken
directions: Skin chicken and set aside for at least 4 hours in cold water in the refrigerator.
This allows the chicken to absorb the water and allows the coating to stick better.

title: fried tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes in half and season with salt and pepper.
In a skillet large enough to hold the tomatoes, melt butter and add tomatoes.
Fry until tender, about 8 minutes.

title: crock-pot stew
directions: In the morning, put in crock-pot meat, onion soup and cheese soup.
Pour wine over; do not stir.
Cook on low all day.
Stir just before serving.
Serve over noodles.

title: old fashion tea cakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients well. Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Then add flavoring and milk to dry ingredients.
Blend well. Place dough on floured sheet paper. Place dough on paper and roll to about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutter and place on baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: zucchini cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grate zucchini; sprinkle with 1 teaspoon of salt.
Toss to coat.
Weight with heavy plate, and drain for 30 minutes.

title: veggie platter
directions: Arrange cauliflower, broccoli, and zuchinni on plate and cover with saran wrap.
Microwave approximately 8 minutes.
Let stand for 2 minutes with the wrap still on it.
Drain liquid off. Pour 3 Tbsp. butter with 1/2 tsp. garlic powder over top.
Cover with cheese and add tomatoes.
Microwave uncovered for 1 1/2 minutes.

title: cream fudge
directions: Cook over slow fire, sugar, flour, cream and syrup until soft-ball stage.
Stir only until sugar is thoroughly dissolved. Remove from fire.
Add butter and vanilla.
Let stand a few minutes, then beat with mixer until thick and creamy using high speed.
Pour into a buttered dish.
Cut into 30 pieces while still warm.
Pecans may be added if desired.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Add flour to make soft dough.
Place in large bowl and place in refrigerator overnight.
Bake as biscuits, no need to let rise.
Will keep several days in refrigerator.

title: fudge sundae surprise
directions: Crush and sprinkle graham crackers in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex. Melt chocolate chips and oleo. Add slightly beaten eggs; mix well. Add powdered sugar, pecans and vanilla. Spoon over crackers and freeze.
Soften ice cream and spoon over other mixture. Sprinkle with chopped pecans and drizzle with chocolate syrup.

title: kentucky spoon bread
directions: Mix all ingredients but butter.
Place in greased casserole. Cover with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 min. or until firm and slightly brown.

title: miniature pecan cakes
directions: Mix cream cheese, margarine and flour with pastry cutter. Roll into walnut size balls.
Press into miniature muffin pans. Make a well by pressing on sides and bottom.
Fill well with mixture of eggs, brown sugar and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes about 35 cakes.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Cut sauerkraut strands in shorter pieces with scissors.
Stir in the sugar and let stand 1/2 hour.
Add remaining ingredients. Cover bowl tightly and chill in refrigerator at least 12 hours before serving.
Makes 8 servings (about 1/2 cup to each serving).

title: chicken pot pie with cornbread crust
directions: Cook peas and carrots according to package directions: drain. In a saucepan cook onion and mushrooms in margarine or butter until tender. Stir in flour, salt, sage, marjoram, or thyme, and pepper. Add chicken broth and milk all at once. Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. Stir in drained peas and carrots, chicken or turkey, parsley and pimiento. Heat until bubbly. Pour chicken mixture into 6 round 10 ounce casseroles, or use a 12x7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish. Mix corn muffin mix according to package. Spoon mixture atop the casserole. Bake in a 450 degrees oven for 12 - 15 minutes or until muffin appears done.

title: watermelon sweet pickles
directions: Use thick rind, pare and remove any red part.
Cut in 1-inch cubes.
Use 1/4 cup salt to 1 quart water to make solution.
Add enough water to cover rind.
Let stand overnight.
Drain.
Cover with boiling water and boil until rind is tender, but not soft.

title: dirt
directions: Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese and pudding mix until fluffy. Layer Oreos and pudding mix until
you run out.

title: taco casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown meat and add pepper, taco seasoning and sour cream.
Grease a 9 x 13 pan and cover the bottom of the pan with crescent rolls.
Layer with crushed chips, meat, cheese, salsa and top with chips.
Bake on the bottom shelf for 25 minutes.

title: chicken reuben
directions: Flatten chicken with a meat mallet.
Dust both sides with flour.
Melt margarine in a skillet and saute chicken on both sides until brown.
Remove from skillet and spread 1 tablespoon dressing on each chicken breast.
Spread 1 tablespoon of sauerkraut evenly over each chicken breast.
Top each with a slice of Swiss cheese.
Place on a greased baking sheet and bake in a preheated 375° oven for 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate truffles
directions: Put the cheese, nuts, sugar and cocoa powder in your mixing bowl; stir until well mixed.
Roll the mixture into marble sized balls in the palm of your hands.
Spread the sprinkles on a work surface and carefully roll the truffles in them.
Put each truffle in a paper candy cup.
Serve!

title: sweet potato cobbler
directions: Dissolve sugar and water.
Add margarine, ginger, nutmeg and salt.
Boil until it is like a thin syrup.
Add vanilla.
While syrup comes to a boil, make biscuit dough (any biscuit recipe will do).
Put sweet potatoes and sugar in saucepan; cover with water. Heat to boiling point.
Drain potatoes.
Line bottom and sides with thin strip of biscuit mix.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine softened cheeses; add other ingredients, except pecans.
Mix well.
Divide into 3 balls or logs; roll in pecans. Will keep several weeks.

title: tempting tuna melts(low-fat)
directions: Mix tuna, dressing, onions, red pepper and seasonings.
For each sandwich, top English muffin half with lettuce, tomato and tuna mixture.
Place on cookie sheet.
Broil 1 minute.
Top with 2 Kraft Free singles. Broil 1 to 2 minutes, or until Kraft Free singles begin to melt.
Makes 4 sandwiches.
Each sandwich contains only 2 grams of fat.

title: pizza bubble bread
directions: Sprinkle greased pan with corn meal.
Separate biscuits.
Snip each biscuit into quarters.
Toss with spaghetti sauce.
Put biscuits in pan.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add bacon slices on top.
Cook at 400° until bacon browns.
Taste to make sure it's sweet.
If not, add more brown or white sugar.

title: killer chocolate cake
directions: Mix pecans or walnuts and coconut; put in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Use German chocolate cake mix and mix according to directions. Pour over nut and coconut mixture.

title: fast chicken soup
directions: Mix all ingredients, except rice together, in large pan.
Add about 2 to 3 cups of water and bring to a boil.
Add rice and let simmer until vegetables are done.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Blend lemon juice and milk, gradually stirring in fruit cocktail.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill and serve. Yields one 9-inch pie.

title: play dough
directions: In a very large bowl, mix together the first 3 ingredients. Make a depression in the center of this mixture and add the oil. Boil the water.
To this, add several drops of food coloring and scented extract.
Pour this into the mixture slowly and stir together with a long spoon.
When the mixture has cooled a little, turn it onto a table and knead it until smooth.
Keep play dough fresh by storing it in an airtight container or large plastic bag sealed shut.

title: cheese grits
directions: Combine grits and salt in saucepan with 2 cups water.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Add butter and cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Serve hot.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: mrs. cobb's casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Brown flour slowly in butter.
Add juice from vegetables.
If too thick, add a small amount of water.
Add grated cheese and sherry.
Season with salt, pepper and nutmeg. Combine with other ingredients in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve hot.

title: chicken broccoli delight
directions: Cook chicken and cut into bite-size pieces.
Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix melted margarine, mushroom soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Cover bottom of baking dish with chicken, then broccoli. Sprinkle with stuffing mix and cover with soup-mayonnaise mixture. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sausage cheese turnovers
directions: Cook sausage; crumble and drain. Mix Italian seasoning, mushrooms and Mozzarella cheese. Press each biscuit into 5-inch circle. Spoon mixture onto each circle. Moisten edges with beaten egg. Fold in half and press edges with fork. Brush with beaten egg; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake on greased cookie sheet 10 minutes at 350°.

title: mom's blueberry cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and cream again.
Add eggs, blueberries and flour (sifted with soda and cream of tartar).
Add milk alternately with flour.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Melt butter in saucepan; add sugar.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture gradually, mixing well.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle with chips and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool in pan and cut.

title: brides yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
In separate bowl, pour boiling water over Crisco.
Add sugar and salt.
Cool; add egg and beat. Add yeast mixture to Crisco mixture and stir.
Add flour and stir until a stiff dough is formed.
Knead on a floured board, pinch off and roll into balls.
Let rise in greased muffin tin until double in size.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: brownies
directions: Set oven to 325°.
Grease and flour an 11 x 16-inch jelly roll pan.
Melt chocolate and butter together and set aside to cool. Beat eggs and sugar together until fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Stir in chocolate mixture, flour, salt, and nuts.
Bake 25 minutes or until top looks dry.
Cool before cutting into bars.

title: whoppin butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat butter, 1/2 cup powdered sugar and vanilla at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Add flour and 1 cup of crushed malted milk balls at low speed.
Shape dough around individual whole malted milk balls; place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake cookies for 12 minutes or until cookies are set but not brown.
Let stand for 1 to 2 minutes.
Let cool.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: marinated veggie salad
directions: Combine first seven ingredients in a glass bowl.
Combine the last four ingredients mixing well, pour over vegetables and marinate at least 2 hours or overnight.
If you like you can use your favorite bottled Italian dressing in place of dressing in recipe.

title: 3-vegetable oven casserole
directions: Remove vegetables from packages in frozen state and break into buttered casserole.
When they are partially thawed, mix.
If desired, add a little milk to the mushroom soup before pouring over vegetables.
Top liberally with crushed cheese crackers. Bake for 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix and
pour
in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° until golden brown,
approximately
minutes.
I like to spread a little nutmeg on the top.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, syrup, margarine, vanilla and pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix soup (rinse out can with only 1/2 can water) with onion soup mix and simmer until it is mixed well and no lumps.
Put this aside for later.
Put butter in casserole and melt.
Add 1 cup rice.
Place cut up seasoned chicken on rice.
Pour soup mixture on top.
Cover and bake for 45 minutes or one hour.
Enjoy!
